<HEAD>
<PB REF="00000065.tif" N="[1]">WICLIFFE'S APOLOGY.</HEAD>
<DIV1 TYPE="prologue">
<P>HERE are questiouns and ansueris putte &thorn;at are writun here aftir.</P>
<P>First, I witnes bifor God Almi&yogh;ty, and alle trewe cristunmen and wommen, and &yogh;owe, &thorn;at I haue not ben, nor is, nor neuer schal, of myn entent ne purpos, to sei any &thorn;ing a&yogh;en &thorn;e general fei&thorn;; nei&thorn;er entent to bigile, or deseyue, ani man or womman, in ani vnprofitable to perpetual &yogh;el of soule; ne agein seying to &thorn;e wordis, ne sentence, of ani seint, seying fei&thorn;fulli. But if &thorn;ei sem ani tyme to uari, onli in word, I purpos to take and vndirstond her wordis to veri and fei&thorn;ful witte, and so to acorde hem to gidir, and to acord wi&thorn; ilke of hem in ilke trow&thorn;e. Preying also ilke man to reduce me in to &thorn;e ri&yogh;t wey aftir &thorn;e gospel of our lord <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> Crist, and wey of &thorn;e apostlis, prophetis, and doctours, if I haue gon biside &thorn;e wey, in ani &thorn;ing in &thorn;eis pontis, or in ani o&thorn;er, to be put for&thorn; heraftir; knouing, if I finali abode in error, I were to be punishid perpe|tuali.</P>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="1" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>I. The Pope not the vicar of Crist, nor of Pe|tir.</HEAD>
<P>On &thorn;at is put is &thorn;is; &thorn;at &thorn;e pope is not &thorn;e vicar of Crist nor of Petir. I knowlech to a felid and seid &thorn;us, wan he filli&thorn; not in dede, ne in word, &thorn;e office of Petir in &yogh;er&thorn;, ne doi&thorn; not &thorn;e &thorn;ing in &thorn;at office &thorn;at he is holden to do: but do&thorn; contrarili, and so in dede he is not &thorn;e vicar of Petir in dede. And &thorn;is steri&thorn; me to fele &thorn;us: 
<PB REF="00000066.tif" N="2"> &thorn;e apostil Poul sei&thorn; &thorn;us; If ani man haue not &thorn;e Spirit of Crist, he<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ro. viij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> is not of him; &thorn;at is, as &thorn;e glose sei&thorn;, he &thorn;at ha&thorn; not &thorn;e Spirit<NOTE PLACE="marg">Glose.</NOTE> aftir witt or dedis, he is not of &thorn;e body of Crist. Also &thorn;us sei&thorn; seint Jerom; Noght alle bischoppis in name ar bischoppis in dede;<NOTE PLACE="marg">Jerom.</NOTE> &thorn;u <ABBR>tend<GAP></ABBR> to Petir, but considir Judas; &thorn;u takst vp Steuen, lok ageyn to Nicol; &thorn;e kirkis dignite maki&thorn; not only a cristun man. Corneli centurio, &yogh;et vncristund, is clensid wi&thorn; &thorn;e Hooli Goost. Daniel, &yogh;et a barne, jugid &thorn;e prestis. It is not li&yogh;t to stond in &thorn;e place of Petir and Poule, and hald &thorn;e place of hem &thorn;at regnun in heuen wi&thorn; Crist. Sonnid salt is not wor&thorn;, but &thorn;at it be cast for&thorn;, and soilid of suynne. Also Austeyn sei&thorn;, Nout ilk &thorn;at sei&thorn; pes to<NOTE PLACE="marg">Austeyn.</NOTE> &yogh;ou, is to be hard as colver or a doue. He &thorn;at ha&thorn; not in him &thorn;e resoun of gevernauns, ne ha&thorn; not wipid a wey his defautis, ne mendid &thorn;e crime of his synnes, is more to be seid a vnschamfast hound &thorn;an a bischop. Not alle prestis ar had for prelats, for &thorn;e name maki&thorn; not &thorn;e bischop, but &thorn;e lif. And Gregor sei&thorn;; Poul<NOTE PLACE="marg">Gregor.</NOTE> sei&thorn;, blam &thorn;u not an heldar man; but &thorn;is reule is &thorn;an to be kept in him, wan &thorn;e synne of &thorn;e heldar man drawi&thorn; not be his ensaumple &thorn;e hertis of &thorn;e &yogh;ungar in to de&thorn;; but wan &thorn;e heldar gifi&thorn; ensaumple to &thorn;e &yogh;ong to de&thorn;, &thorn;er is he to be stregun wi&thorn; scharp blamyng, for it is writoun, Al &yogh;e be grynnies of &thorn;e &yogh;ong. And eft, Waried &thorn;e barn of an vndrid &yogh;ere. And &thorn;is is put after in decreis, We&thorn;er &thorn;e priuilege of dignite is not to be tan a wey from<NOTE PLACE="marg">Decreis.</NOTE> hem to wham Austeyn, Jerom, and Gregor tak a wey &thorn;e name of &thorn;e bischop, or heldarman, &thorn;at he may be correctid of wudlowtis. Also Austeyn sei&thorn;, He &thorn;at desiri&thorn; bischophed, he desiri&thorn; a good<NOTE PLACE="marg">Austeyn.</NOTE> werk; he wold expound what is bischophed, for is it &thorn;e nam of werk, and not of honor; it is Grek; and &thorn;er is seid a word, &thorn;at he &thorn;at is maad a prest, tak he &yogh;ed to &thorn;e &thorn;ingis &thorn;at he is maad prest to, doing &thorn;e cure of hem; scopos is locand vp on; &thorn;er for, if we wil, we mai calle bischoppis, locars up on, &thorn;at he &thorn;at lufith to be a prest not fur&thorn;er to, vnderstond him not to be a bischop; &thorn;us sei&thorn; 
<PB REF="00000067.tif" N="3"> Austeyn. But if &thorn;u sei he seki&thorn; ai to fur&thorn;er, it be howfi&thorn; &thorn;at it be schewid in dede; for seynt Jam sei&thorn;, Fei&thorn; wi&thorn; outun werkis is deed;<NOTE PLACE="marg">S. Jam. ij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> so to seke to profit is but deed, but if it be put for&thorn; in dede after power. And as fei&thorn; is for&thorn;fillid of &thorn;e werkis, so is also desir. And ellis desir sle&thorn; &thorn;e soule; &thorn;erfor sei&thorn; Crist to Petre, &thorn;rise, Simon of<NOTE PLACE="marg">Jo. xxi<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> Jon, lufist &thorn;u me? feede my schep. &thorn;erfor as Gregor sei&thorn;, He &thorn;at<NOTE PLACE="marg">Gregor.</NOTE> is chosun in to schepherd, he howi&thorn; to feed wi&thorn; word, and en|saumple, and sustinaunce of body; &thorn;an if he be conuicted not to luf, ne to do &thorn;e office of Crist, in &thorn;is he is conuict not to be his vicar. Also &thorn;us sei&thorn; Crisostom; Sin <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> was temptid, he ouercam<NOTE PLACE="marg">Crisostom.</NOTE> hunger in desert, he despicid auarice in &thorn;e hille, he strak ageyn veyn glorie vp on &thorn;e temple; &thorn;at he schwe to us, &thorn;at he &thorn;at may ageynsey his wombe, and despice &thorn;e goodis of &thorn;is world, and desire not veynglorie, he howi&thorn; to be maad Cristis vicar, and preche Cristis ri&yogh;twisnes, and for &thorn;oo &thorn;re chimneis ich low of &thorn;e fendis blowing is sett in fire. And &thorn;us sei&thorn; an o&thorn;er; It is wel wetun &thorn;at Crist<NOTE PLACE="marg">Another.</NOTE> was mekist man, pure, and moost obedient to God; it is not &thorn;an inconuenient his vicar to be moost lik him in &thorn;eis &thorn;re, namly. Now deme &thorn;is fi&yogh;ting kirke, if &thorn;e pope be moost mek, reseyuing wrongis don til him; if he be purist man as to seculer lordship, moost hatyng to be enpli&yogh;ed wi&thorn; seculer bisines; and &thorn;e &thorn;rid, if he be moost obedient to God, and to his lawe, most content of &thorn;e boundis of his lawe, not presumand to put to his lawe, ne to minys &thorn;erfro. For so&thorn;, if &thorn;e pope do &thorn;eis befor o&thorn;er men, &thorn;an is he, by for o&thorn;er men, &thorn;e folower of Crist; ellis is verified in him &thorn;e sentence of Crist, He &thorn;at is not wi&thorn; me, he is ageyn me. And<NOTE PLACE="marg">Matt. xij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> Crisostom sei&thorn;, He &thorn;at desiri&thorn; primacy in &yogh;er&thorn; schal fynd confusion<NOTE PLACE="marg">Crisostom.</NOTE> in heuen, and he schal not be countid among &thorn;e seruaunts of Crist &thorn;at treti&thorn; of primacy; nor no man hast to be seen more &thorn;an o&thorn;er, but &thorn;at he be seen lower &thorn;an o&thorn;er; for he is not &thorn;e ritwisare &thorn;at is more in honor, but he &thorn;at &thorn;e ri&yogh;twisare, he is &thorn;e more. Ensaumple ledi&thorn; us to &thorn;is same &thorn;us; If a man haue an 
<PB REF="00000068.tif" N="4"> hired plowman in to serueys to dwel wi&thorn; him, to do ani dede, and fei&thorn;fully to serue to him in to &thorn;at werk, and &thorn;at seruaunt obliche him to do so, &yogh;efing fei&thorn; to &thorn;is; if he felle not aftir in dede and tyme aftir his hi&yogh;t and couenaund, but go&thorn; a wey &thorn;er fro, and leui&thorn; to wirke, and do&thorn; contrarily directly, and in to &thorn;e harme of his maistir, it is certayn &thorn;an, &thorn;owe he be his seruaunt of dette and oblisching, na&thorn;les he is not his seruaunt in filling of werk, and so not in dede; but ra&thorn;er aduersari, fals trespasor, and traytor. And &thorn;us it semi&thorn; in &thorn;e propos. If ani chosun of God himselue, and of &thorn;e puple, in to pope, or prelate, and ordend in to vicar of Crist to his office in &yogh;er&thorn;e, and he hi&yogh;t it; whan he filli&thorn; not in dede, but do&thorn; contrarily to his behest in degre, he semi&thorn; not to be &thorn;e vicar of Crist in dede. And so, &thorn;owe he be his vicar vp degre and dignite, and o&thorn;er tyme in dede, wan he do&thorn; &thorn;e dedis of &thorn;e office, &thorn;erfor &thorn;e pope ioi not, or ani prelat, or o&thorn;er in &thorn;e nam of dignite or of state, wan it is not to perpetual blis to &thorn;e soule. But al dred more lest &thorn;ei geit &thorn;er of harme to &thorn;e soule, and tymung for defaut of trespase; for &thorn;i &thorn;at in swelk &thorn;e synne aggregi&thorn; bi resoun of &thorn;e degre; for &thorn;us it is writun, Joi &thorn;u not of &thorn;e vnpitouse<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ecclus. xvi<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> sonis, if &thorn;e drede of God is not befor hem; for better is oon dredan God, &thorn;an a &thorn;ow&yogh;and vnpitouse. And better to die wi&thorn; out barnes, &thorn;an to lef vnpitouse barnis aftir. And efte &thorn;us sei&thorn; Crist; Joi &yogh;e not for spiritis are sogetis to &yogh;owe, but joi &yogh;e &thorn;at &yogh;or namis<NOTE PLACE="marg">Luc. x<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> are writun in heuen. And eft sei&thorn; &thorn;e gospel, Maki&thorn; wor&thorn;i frutis of<NOTE PLACE="marg">Matt. iii<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> penaunce, and wil &yogh;e not sei wi&thorn;in &yogh;or self we haue &thorn;e fadir Abra|ham, for God is mi&yogh;ti of &thorn;e stonis to reise &thorn;e sonis of Habraham; for now is &thorn;e axe sett to &thorn;e rote of &thorn;e tree, &thorn;erfor ilk tree &thorn;at maki&thorn; not good fru&yogh;t, schal be kyt doun, and cast in to &thorn;e fire. And eft Jerom sei&thorn;; It is not li&yogh;t to stond in &thorn;e place of Petir and<NOTE PLACE="marg">Jerom.</NOTE> Poule, and hold &thorn;e chaur of hem &thorn;at regnun wi&thorn; Crist; for &thorn;er of it is seid; &thorn;ei are not &thorn;e sonis of seyntis &thorn;at holdun &thorn;er placis, but &thorn;ei &thorn;at vse &thorn;er werkis. An Gregor sei&thorn;, We &thorn;at are prestis how<NOTE PLACE="marg">Gregor.</NOTE> 
<PB REF="00000069.tif" N="5"> to ask to knowe, not of dignite of place, ne of kirkis, but of nobley of maneris; not bi clerte of citees, but bi purte of fei&thorn;; places ne orderis makun not vs nekist God, but o&thorn;er good meritis ioynun to gidir, or ellis departen, &thorn;at is wit, as to mede merit and blis. And Crisostom sei&thorn;; A cristun man falli&thorn; strongli in to synne for two<NOTE PLACE="marg">Crisostom.</NOTE> causis, o&thorn;er for gretness of &thorn;e synne, or for hei&yogh;t of &thorn;e dignite. Also of &thorn;e dedis of Boneface &thorn;e martir; If &thorn;e pope ben tan rekles<NOTE PLACE="marg">Bonef.</NOTE> of his and his bre&thorn;er's &yogh;ele, vnprofitable and slow in his dedis, more ouer and stille fro good, &thorn;at more noye&thorn; to him and alle o&thorn;er, &thorn;an he ledi&thorn; wi&thorn; him silf going bifore to helle peple wi&thorn; outun nowmbre, to be dongun wi&thorn; him wi&thorn;outen ende, wi&thorn; mani digingis. &thorn;erfor, si&thorn; &thorn;e office of Crist [on] &thorn;e &yogh;erd was to liue most purist and mekly, and to preche bisili &thorn;e word of God to &thorn;e peple, and to calle hem a&yogh;en to &thorn;e lord God, fadir of alle, and in to &thorn;e vnite and prosperite of body, and cam to serue and not be seruid, and to &yogh;if his lif raumsum for mani, and bi &thorn;is ha&thorn; &yogh;efun to vs mani good &thorn;ingis, and to fille &thorn;is ordeynid Petir, seying to<NOTE PLACE="marg">Joh. xxi<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> him, lufist me? feed my schep, and folow me, and in him he biddi&thorn; &thorn;e same to alle successors of Petre, as als in Petir a gaf to hem power of bindyng and lowsing, and &thorn;us ordeynd him his vicar, and &thorn;us his successor; and Petir himsilf &thorn;us fillid &thorn;e office of Crist, in liuing, and in teching, and in &thorn;oling; and &thorn;is same he biddi&thorn; to his successors, as is opun in his pistil. But &thorn;ei &thorn;at do not in dede, it is clere &thorn;at in dede &thorn;ei hald not, ne do, his office, ne office of Crist; and &thorn;us it semi&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;ei are not led be &thorn;e same spirit. &thorn;erfor as be &thorn;e dedis of Crist in his persoun, and bi &thorn;e dedis &thorn;at he dide in Petre, moost goodis are comyn to vs in &thorn;is tyme, and in tyme to come, so it is to drede, &thorn;at bi &thorn;e slownes of &thorn;e pope, and of prelats succedand in his place, and bi her peruerse werkis, moost iuil comi&thorn; to vs, bo&thorn; of synnis and of peyn, now in &thorn;is tyme, and ay to dwell wi&thorn; vs, but if we mend.
<PB REF="00000070.tif" N="6"></P>
<P>And &thorn;us I graunt now, as oft I haue knowlechid bifor mani wit|nes, &thorn;at &thorn;e lawfulli ordenid his Cristis vicar, or wan he do&thorn;, or biddi&thorn;, ony &thorn;ing in &thorn;e nam of Crist, as if Crist do &thorn;at bi him, &thorn;at &thorn;an he is &thorn;e vicar of Crist in dede, and &thorn;an it is to obey to him, as to Cristis vicar, and as to <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> Crist. And so to folow after &thorn;e sentence of &thorn;e apostel seyng; Be my folowars as I am Cristis.<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Cor. xi<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> And eft, &yogh;e tok me, he sei&thorn;, as an aungel, &yogh;e as Crist <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR>, for Crist<NOTE PLACE="marg">Gal. iv<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> speki&thorn; in me, and he &thorn;at dispici&thorn; our teching, dispici&thorn; not man, but God &thorn;at &yogh;af his Holy Gost in vs, for Crist sei&thorn;, he &thorn;at heri&thorn; &yogh;ow,<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Thes. iv<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> heri&thorn; me, and he &thorn;at dispici&thorn; &yogh;ow dispisi&thorn; me, &thorn;at is, wan &yogh;e spek<NOTE PLACE="marg">Luc. x<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> of my spirit. But not so wan &yogh;e spek of a no&thorn;er spirit. But wan &thorn;e pope go&thorn; a wey fro Crist, and do&thorn; &thorn;e contrari, as is be for seid, or do&thorn; &thorn;e contrari, &thorn;an is not he Cristis vicar, ne it is not to obey ne folow him in &thorn;eis &thorn;ingis. &thorn;us haue I oft seid; and, as I suppose, cordandli wi&thorn; holi writ, and fei&thorn;ful doctors, and autentik decreis. And it semi&thorn; me, &thorn;at it be howfi&thorn; me to sey &thorn;us, for it is knowun &thorn;at many popis han synnyd, and ben snibbid; and sum tan in heresy and deposid. And, &thorn;erfor, &thorn;ei are not to be folowid sympli in al &thorn;ing. Also non lyuyng in &thorn;is frel lif is simply wi&thorn;out synne, non but Crist, holi writ witnessi&thorn;. Also ani in popehed aftir Petir is not holier, nor mor confermid in &thorn;at office, &thorn;an he, and he, aftir &thorn;e Holi Gost taking, synnid opunly in si&yogh;t of &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">Gal. ij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> puple, constreyning &thorn;e gentil to be com Jewes in obseruaunce; werfor Poule a&yogh;enstod him in &thorn;e face, and redarguid him, for he was reprouable. &thorn;an it semi&thorn; to me, &thorn;at it is helsum to &thorn;e pope, and to prelatis, and to &thorn;e peple, and worschipful to God, &thorn;at &thorn;e peple be ri&yogh;tly enformid, how &thorn;ei owe to accept &thorn;e pope as &thorn;e vicar of Crist, and how &thorn;ei owe to bowe fro him; &thorn;at &thorn;e peple, deseyuid ani tyme, worschip not God and &thorn;e fend to gidir, ne ani tyme &thorn;e fend in &thorn;e sted of Crist, and &thorn;e wrathe of God com bo&thorn; on &thorn;e peple and on &thorn;e prestis.</P>


</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="2" TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000071.tif" N="7">
<HEAD>II. Indulg. That the Pope sellith indulgence. That he may &yogh;ef non indul|gence nei|ther to man in purga|tori, nei|ther to hem that are prescit.</HEAD>
<P>O&thorn;er two poyntis &thorn;at are put and askid are &thorn;eis. On, &thorn;at &thorn;e pope selli&thorn; indulgence. An o&thorn;er, &thorn;at he may &yogh;ef non indulgence noi&thorn;er to man in purgatori, nei&thorn;er to hem &thorn;at are prescit, &thorn;at is to sey &thorn;at are to be dampnid, or are now dampnid.</P>
<P>To &thorn;eis I seid &thorn;us; I rehersid a doctor &thorn;at seid &thorn;us; We owe not to tak as fei&thorn; indulgencis, now sale wor&thorn;, for &thorn;i &thorn;at are not &thorn;us grauntid of our lord <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> Crist. And, sin sophisticacoun falli&thorn; ofte in &thorn;is matir, fei&thorn;ful men askyn, vnder peyn of &thorn;rowing hem a wey, &thorn;is witnes; fei&thorn; of holi writ is sufficient to reule alle holi kirk, but men redun not &thorn;at ani of &thorn;e apostles grauntid silk indulgencis. And fei&thorn;ful curats owen to sorowe as wel of &thorn;e spoling of &thorn;er sogetis, as also of &thorn;e synne of &thorn;e spoliars, for Crist sei&thorn;, Blessid be &thorn;oo &thorn;at mornun, for &thorn;ei schal be coumfortid.<NOTE PLACE="marg">Matt. ij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> Blessid be &thorn;oo &thorn;at hungrun and &thorn;ristun ri&yogh;twisnes, for &thorn;ei schal be filled. Blessid be &thorn;e merciful for &thorn;ei schal gete mercy. It semi&thorn; to mani, &thorn;at it were wark of mercy to opun &thorn;e trow&thorn; of &thorn;e fei&thorn; in &thorn;is part, &thorn;at &thorn;e pope ha&thorn; not power to graunt silk indulgencis for so li&yogh;t price. Also abodily &thorn;ing of how euer litil price howi&thorn; not to be bout but wi&thorn; &thorn;is wisdam; &thorn;at &thorn;e by&yogh;ar be profhabili sekir of &thorn;e &thorn;ing sold. But &thorn;e pope mai not siker ani man &thorn;at aftir his dede, or be forn, he schal haue so mikil indulgencis; &thorn;er|for prouabily silk marchaundise owi&thorn; to be left. For &thorn;e pope wat not, ne of himsilf, if he be sauid of God, or prescit to be dampnid, &thorn;at if he be prescit, silk indulgencis rennun not for&thorn; a&yogh;en &thorn;e ordinaunce of God, ordeyning aylastingly &thorn;e contrary; &thorn;erfor, wan &thorn;e pope may not procure silk indulgencis generaly to himsilf, it is euident to many &thorn;at silk marchandis are suspect of coueytise of symonie. It is not a&yogh;en &thorn;e fei&thorn;, or prouable a&yogh;en &thorn;e trow&thorn;, &thorn;at mani popis &thorn;at be word onli han grauntid mani large indulgencis are dampnid; &thorn;an how may &thorn;ei defend &thorn;er indulgencis bifor God? Also, a duke, or an &yogh;erle, stonding ny a &yogh;er&thorn;li king, and &thorn;e king grauntid a fredam or priuilege, it is not inferrid of &thorn;is, &thorn;at 
<PB REF="00000072.tif" N="8"> &thorn;e duk, or &yogh;erle, graunti&thorn; &thorn;is fredam or priuilege, but ra&thorn;er it longi&thorn; to &thorn;e kyngis dignite; &thorn;an, sin &thorn;e king Crist is king of kings, heiar wi&thorn; out comparisoun &thorn;an ani pope, &thorn;an &thorn;e king is souereyn to ani &yogh;erle or duke, it semi&thorn; mikil more euident &thorn;at it longi&thorn; to &thorn;e gretnes of God to graunt singlerly &thorn;eis priuilegs or fredam; for it folowi&thorn; not, if a bedel, or criare, schewe &thorn;e fre graunt of his lord, &thorn;an &thorn;at &thorn;is seruaunt, &thorn;us schewand, graunti&thorn; swilke maner of fredam; mikil more if he pronounce wi&thorn; out autorite or lif, con|trariously, a&yogh;ennis &thorn;e lordis wille. And in &thorn;is caas are comynli grauntars of pardoun. Also, a fei&thorn;ful curat owi&thorn; to notify to his sugets, were is pardoun, sikirar, largar, and for les price, to be bout to his sogets. But &thorn;e popes bulle techi&thorn;, as it is seid, a pope to a maad and grauntid, at &thorn;e instaunce of a king, two &thorn;ou&yogh;and &yogh;er, als oft as a nobil man sei&thorn; it bi twex &thorn;e consecracioun and Agnus Dei. And &thorn;us prouabli a fei&thorn;ful man mi&yogh;t in &yogh;ering mani messis geit on a day &thorn;ewenti &thorn;ow&yogh;and &yogh;er of pardoun. Swilk a wis mar|chandis for hel of soul, mi&yogh;t a curat sey to his parischings. Also, putting to ouer for lewid men, &thorn;at can not &thorn;is orisoun, &thorn;at &thorn;ei schal haue as mikil or more indulgencis for &thorn;e pr. nr. as oft as &thorn;ei sey it, and as gret charite and mekenes deseruing indulgens. Also, a&yogh;en swilk feynid and on groundid indulgens, howi&thorn; a fei&thorn;ful prest to multiply quek resouns, weil he hungri&thorn; and &thorn;risti&thorn; ri&yogh;twisnes of &thorn;e law of God, for by suelk sophymis of anticrist, &thorn;e lawe of God is despicid, and ri&yogh;tful is put in veyn hope, and vpon ilk side a liuar in &thorn;is world is falsly iapid. &thorn;erfor, lif a man a iust lif, and tryst he of &thorn;e parting of merit &thorn;at God gifi&thorn; men frely as him liki&thorn;. And alle feynid arguments of anticrist are not wor&thorn;i to be rehersid. God seid to Petir, Wat &thorn;u byndist vpon &yogh;er&thorn;e it schal be<NOTE PLACE="marg">Matt. xvj<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> boundoun also in heuin. And &thorn;e pope is Petir's vicar, &thorn;erfor it be howfi&thorn; to trowe &thorn;at &thorn;is fei&thorn; is verifi&yogh;ed of him. Ilk fei&thorn;ful man graunt of &thorn;e gospel &thorn;e first. And suppose of &thorn;e secound word, &thorn;of it be euident of dede him not be &thorn;e vicar of Petre, syn Petir 
<PB REF="00000073.tif" N="9"> was not hardi to accept &thorn;is foule hardy presumpcoun, but suppose &thorn;at Petre or aungel of heuun accept to lowse or to bynd, he may not do &thorn;is, but in as mykil as it soundi&thorn; to &thorn;e hed of &thorn;e kirk abouyn. And as &thorn;is consonaunt is vnknowen to &thorn;e japer, so &thorn;is fendly marchaundy is vneuident to &thorn;e fei&thorn;ful peple knowend &thorn;is; &thorn;us sei&thorn; &thorn;e doctor. Also a doctor in &thorn;e lawe, Barthelmew in<NOTE PLACE="marg">Barth.</NOTE> casis, sei&thorn; &thorn;at dais or &yogh;eris of indulgens are not daies ne &yogh;eris of heuen ne of purgatory, but &thorn;ei are daies of &thorn;is world. Also &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">Clemen|tins.</NOTE> law sei&thorn;, Pardoneris ow not to graunt indulgens of &thorn;er wil of dede, ne dispens vp on wowis, ne asoil of swering, mansleyng, or of o&thorn;er synnis &thorn;ei &thorn;at schriuis to hem, ne for&yogh;eue &thorn;ingis iuil tan awey and vncerteyn to w&omacr;me to restore for a quantite of money &yogh;yuen to hem, ne for&yogh;eue &thorn;e &thorn;ridde or &thorn;e fourt part of penaunce en|ioinid, ne to draw sum tyme a soule fro purgatorie, as &thorn;ei feynun falsly, ne graunt pleyn remissioun of synnis, ne asoile a pena et a culpa, for alle priuilegis up on &thorn;eis or ani of hem are a&yogh;en callid in. &thorn;e Clementyns de pe. c<SUP>o</SUP>. abus. h. Barth. in Casibus. If it be askid we&thorn;er &thorn;e pope selle indulgencs and merits of seynts, or &thorn;at men of &thorn;e kirke selle &thorn;er orisouns preyours or gostly suf|fragis; here I sey &thorn;us, It semi&thorn; me spedy to aferm no &thorn;ing folily. But it semi&thorn; mekenes to seke how bying and sellyng synfully may falle in swelk &thorn;ings, &thorn;at fei&thorn;ful folk eschew &thorn;e warliar; and &thorn;an &thorn;e dede semi&thorn; and witnessi&thorn; herd and vnderstonden and o&thorn;er circum|stauncs. Ilk man deme &thorn;e sikirliar &thorn;ing &thorn;at semit to him. To selle is &thorn;e hauer to &yogh;eue his &thorn;ing for price tane, and bi his resonable nature to reseyue &thorn;ing for price &yogh;euun, and &thorn;us bying and sellyng dubli grauntid and dubli &yogh;euing. &thorn;er to selle is seid as for to &yogh;eue to selling. Werfor wan I by meit for money, I selle &thorn;e money &thorn;at &thorn;e to&thorn;er man bie&thorn;, as I bye &thorn;ing &thorn;at &thorn;e to&thorn;er selli&thorn;. I bye &thorn;e met; in &thorn;is &thorn;at I reseyue for price &yogh;euun. And I selle &thorn;e money in &thorn;is &thorn;at I giue it for price. And it semi&thorn; &thorn;at bying and selling of man is many fold; &thorn;e first heuinly; vpon &thorn;e rewlis of wis|dam; 
<PB REF="00000074.tif" N="10"> &thorn;e secound is on &thorn;e gespel, vpon &thorn;e rewlis of prudence; &thorn;e &thorn;rid is worldly, up on &thorn;e rewl of mannis lawe; and &thorn;e fourt is fendly. Be &thorn;e first, gostly &thorn;ings ai lastand are bout for temporal &thorn;ings &thorn;at are falling and passing. Of secound is seid, &thorn;at Cristis dis|ciplis went in to &thorn;e cyte to by met. Of &thorn;e &thorn;rid is comyn among men. Of &thorn;e fourt is seid &thorn;at Achab was sold to do iuil in si&yogh;t of &thorn;e Lord. &thorn;eis wel vnderstondun, it seme&thorn; wel &thorn;at popis, cardi|nalis, and o&thorn;er prelats, prestis, and o&thorn;er religiouse, may medfully and graciously selle indulgencis and merits of seynts and preyours and gostli suffrages, as &thorn;ei may graunt be cristun men swilk &thorn;ings or benfets and deds of mercy and o&thorn;er goodis; and &thorn;us may o&thorn;er bye. And mani may not tak part of grace ne of blis but if &thorn;ei bye it vn sum maner, and it be sold hem; it semi&thorn; bi &thorn;is &thorn;at Crist bou&yogh;t us a&yogh;en, and for our good dedis behit vs heuenly kyndom. &thorn;us blessid martirs for gloriouse martirdom deseruid to haue per|petual crounis. &thorn;us &thorn;e apostil did alle &thorn;ings for &thorn;e gospel &thorn;at he schuld be maad perseyuer &thorn;er of. Als &thorn;us seye we, o maruelous marchandies, &thorn;e maker of man kynd takyng a soulid body of &thorn;e virgyn, demd to be borne, and for&thorn;going man wi&thorn; out seed, may gif vs his godhed, swilk fei&thorn; is ai mad in hope trust and charite. And &thorn;us if &thorn;e pope, or ani o&thorn;er, ani tyme fei&thorn;fully and charitably graunt and hi&yogh;t to ani man indulgens, or part of merit of seynts, part of preyours, abstinens, wakyng, obediens, or o&thorn;er deds, iustly, and on Goddis plesaunce, and graciousli, for her good deds, o&thorn;er &thorn;at &thorn;ei be relesid of synnis, or of peynis, or &thorn;at &thorn;ei be &thorn;e more sterid to &thorn;e fei&thorn;, or to plese God, blessidli &thorn;ei selle swilk &thorn;ingis to hem. And a&yogh;en worde swilke &thorn;enkand to do &thorn;e deds of God iustli, and graciously &thorn;e dedis of mercy, &thorn;at he be maad per|seyuar of swilk &thorn;ings, bo&thorn; &thorn;ei bien and sellen blessidli. But if &thorn;e pope, led bi coueytise, or o&thorn;er, as symonie, or wi&thorn; &thorn;e spirit of pride, as if &thorn;ei wi&thorn; here biginning disposid alle &thorn;ings, and graunt swilk &thorn;ingis to ilke man, &yogh;ha wi&thorn; out merit, or wi&thorn; out God ledar before, 
<PB REF="00000075.tif" N="11"> but as if folowid, and schuld proue, and schuld conferme wat &thorn;at him list to be don, as now is presumid of many; or led wi&thorn; &thorn;e spirit of lust of flesche, graunt or behi&yogh;t ani swilk &thorn;ingis, o&thorn;er for mony or o&thorn;er &yogh;er&thorn;li bodili temporal good and fleschly &thorn;ingis, or preyour or fauour of meed, or fleschli &thorn;ings, or for swilk luf, haterad, or drede of swilk men, or for vndeu seruise, or o&thorn;er vndeu cause and vnpertinent, who schal &thorn;an dout but &thorn;at &thorn;e pope and o&thorn;er selle swilk &thorn;ingis synfully, and for symonie, and &thorn;us alle &thorn;at per|sewen for swilke indulgens, or benfices, or o&thorn;er graces, wi&thorn; swilk froward in witt, who douti&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;ei ne bi&yogh;e sinfully, or veriliar en|force to bye &thorn;ing &thorn;at schal not geyt? Also if &thorn;e pope, and o&thorn;er men of &thorn;e kirke, wil not graunt indulgens or benfics to hem &thorn;at &thorn;ei be grauntid to frely, but if money or sum o&thorn;er &thorn;ing be &yogh;euen to hem, or if minstris of &thorn;e kirke wele not frely minster to hem &thorn;at &thorn;ei [schuld?] frely minster to, not but if mony or o&thorn;er &thorn;ing be &yogh;euen to hem, who dowti&thorn; &thorn;at ne swilk men sellen synfully swilk &thorn;ings? &thorn;is semi&thorn; be &thorn;e sawis of fei&thorn;ful doctours, put in &thorn;e canon, so and &thorn;ei &thorn;at wenun to bye indulgens for &thorn;er temporal goods, and wenun to be assoilid or for &yogh;euun be hem, &thorn;of &thorn;ei abi&yogh;d in &thorn;er synnes, nor mak not satisfaccoun dewly of &thorn;er synnis on o&thorn;er syde, but also eft turnun a&yogh;en &thorn;er to; byen synfully, and wenun to haue &thorn;at is takun a wey from hem. And also swilk are in defaut &thorn;at hopen not, ne turnen not to be for&yogh;euun of &thorn;er synnis; wan &thorn;ei mend hem vp on Cristis bidding, &yogh;ha if &thorn;e prest wil not mins|ter to hem, not but if money be gyuen to hem, and for &thorn;is &thorn;ei selle &thorn;is iuil wille. Also how blam wor&thorn;i are &thorn;o minstris &thorn;at wan men and women are foundun in synne, anoon &thorn;ei forbed hem &thorn;e sacra|ments of &thorn;e kirke and comynng of cristun men, and enioyn hem gret penaunce, but if &thorn;at &thorn;ei fynd better grace. But as sone as mony is &yogh;euen &thorn;ei reysen &thorn;e synnars to &thorn;e takyng of &thorn;e sacraments and comyning of &thorn;e folk, and joynun prestis to reseyue hem, and minster to hem, &thorn;of &thorn;ei leue not &thorn;er synne, but contenun it more orribli, and 
<PB REF="00000076.tif" N="12"> oft leue hem tul a tyme to contune &thorn;er inne. A howe cursid mar|chaundise of men of &thorn;e kirke, to selle soulis in synne to &thorn;e deuil for &thorn;er godis! And also &thorn;er oune soule; in part takyng of &thorn;e defaut, and for &thorn;e sacrilege &thorn;at &thorn;ei do in reif of goodis. A howe gret schrewidnes, fraude, gile, and reif, and peruersite now regne&thorn; in &thorn;e kirk, as is opun be &thorn;e dedis! Certis now is fillid &thorn;at is seid in &thorn;e psalme, For I sawe wickidnes and contradiccoun in &thorn;e cyte day<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ps. liv<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> and ny&yogh;t. Wickidnesse schal compasce here vp on her wall, and traueil in her middis, and vnritwisnes and vsere and gile an [are] not fallen from here stretis. In how many gret casis may it be, &thorn;at now regni&thorn; in &thorn;e kirk synful marchondise; bryng to witnes; exa|myn &thorn;e sawis; discusse &thorn;e dedis; opun and comyn fame tra|ueyli&thorn;, &thorn;at in &thorn;e court of Rome mai no man geyt no grace, but if it be bowt, nor &thorn;er is noon grauntid, but if it be for temporal meed; for &thorn;is &thorn;at &thorn;e pope reserui&thorn; to himsilf, and to &thorn;e chaumbre, as graunting of sum benfics, and &thorn;e first fruts of sum o&thorn;er, &thorn;at he gifi&thorn;; and translatyng of bischops; and al &thorn;is is don, as it is seid, for couey|ties, and &thorn;at is seruant of idols; &thorn;ei &thorn;at persuen for indulgencs, exempcouns, and priueylegs, sey how &thorn;ei geyt nowt wi&thorn; out bying; swilk are comynly grauntid to &thorn;e riche and my&yogh;ty of &thorn;e world. Wat of graunting of indulgencs, an abbot of gret riches &yogh;af &thorn;re vndred marke, to geyt to his abbey, &thorn;ries in &thorn;e &yogh;eere, &thorn;e same in|dulgence &thorn;at &thorn;e kirk of Rome is wont to graunt to hem &thorn;at visitun a place &thorn;at is callid porciuncula. Nout only, but also [a] cardi|nal gaf at his dying al his good, to haue &thorn;e same grauntid to a riche abbey were he was be fore monk, as men &thorn;at are hold trewe men witnessen. What more? A clene man was in &thorn;e court, and spak to hem &thorn;at had gret gouernaile in &thorn;e court, and praid him to &yogh;if him ordres frely. Wel, he sei&thorn;, I schal &yogh;eue &thorn;e frely. And &thorn;ou schalt &yogh;eue me foure floreynis, and I schal ordeyn &thorn;e a bischop aftir noon. And he ansuerid, So&thorn;li, I haue but foure katereynis. Forso&thorn;e, he sei&thorn;, and &thorn;u schalt han non ordres here. 
<PB REF="00000077.tif" N="13"> And &thorn;us he went wi&thorn; out ordres. And nowe how &thorn;e pricis are ekid, and how mykil him behowui&thorn; to &yogh;eue &thorn;at schal geit ben|fics, &thorn;ei telle &thorn;at bring swilk new &thorn;ingis fro &thorn;e cowurt.</P>
<P>Nowe ilk man discuse wedir swilk marchaundis be synful, and ai be war of &thorn;e perel, and see &thorn;at we sey no fals witnes a geyn ani man, but ioi we euer to gidir in trow&thorn;.</P>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="3" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>III. Of cursing twey points. 1. &thorn;at &thorn;e ministris of &thorn;e kirk owe not to curse. 2. &thorn;at &thorn;e kirke may not rizt|wisly curse a riztwys man.</HEAD>
<P>Of cursing twey poynts.</P>
<P>A no&thorn;er is &thorn;is &thorn;at is put and askid, &thorn;at &thorn;o minstris of &thorn;e kirke owe not to curse and to wari.</P>
<P>Certs to &thorn;is I sey &thorn;ei owe bo&thorn;e to curse and wari, but neuer for iuil wille ne veniaunce, but for luf of ritwisnes. And ra&thorn;er for &thorn;e breking of &thorn;e bidding of God, &thorn;an for worldli goodis or pride of &thorn;e world and flescli lust.</P>
<P>An o&thorn;er is &thorn;is &thorn;at is putte, &thorn;at &thorn;e kirke may not ri&yogh;twisly curse a ri&yogh;twys man. To &thorn;is I seid &thorn;us, &thorn;at in two maner of &thorn;ing, is seid iust; first sympli, or after trow&thorn;, as &thorn;at vnrytwysnes is not inne. In &thorn;e secound maner is a man seid iust, onli in name or aftir present ri&yogh;twisnes. And &thorn;us as doctors seyn, a sentence of cursyng is seid to be &yogh;euun justli, on two maners. On after trou&thorn;, wan it is don wit just cause, juste ordre, and iust entent. A no&thorn;er, wan it is don onli up on comyn form o lawe. And &thorn;us it may be as it semi&thorn; sum tyme, &thorn;at &thorn;ow &thorn;e kirke curse iustli, as to form, a iust man, ne&thorn;les it [is] not iust as to so&thorn;fastnes; as wan &thorn;er is no cause of &thorn;e fulnes of &thorn;e kirke cursing: vnri&yogh;twisnes of &thorn;e cause is &thorn;o syn going be for of &thorn;e obstinat, wan &thorn;e synnar wil not dewli obey ne amend ri&yogh;t. &thorn;at is &thorn;at &thorn;u dost &thorn;o dom in nam of &thorn;e kirke, fei&thorn;fully wilyng &thorn;e mendment of &thorn;e synnar, helful, to &thorn;e worschip of our Lord <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> Crist, and due ordre procedand up &thorn;e gospel. But suppose her &thorn;at &thorn;is iust is &thorn;at is ordeynid be God to do a &thorn;ing, or to suffre, to comyn, or to minister in ani maner, or &yogh;end in &thorn;e nam of Crist, and he willing to perform obediently and fille &thorn;e wark &thorn;at 
<PB REF="00000078.tif" N="14"> God ha&thorn; &yogh;euun to do, suppose he &thorn;at &thorn;is is iust. And &thorn;an I sup|pose &thorn;e kirke mai not iustli curse him, as he may not sequester him fro &thorn;is &thorn;at God joini&thorn; him to do, but if God wille &thorn;at he be sequestrid; nor &thorn;e kirk may not iustli priue &thorn;e comyning of cristun men, nor taking of &thorn;e sacraments, nor part taking of good &thorn;ings, wyle he is iust, not but if God wil &thorn;at it be done; nor &thorn;e kirke may not iustli punisch nor bid punische swilk on, bifor &thorn;at God bid; nor non may denounce swilk on cursid, not but in &thorn;e forme &thorn;at he is cursid; nor &thorn;e kirke mai not iustli lede ani man in to synne, nor bid do synne, ne contune &thorn;er inne, &thorn;e wilk he putt owt of comyn and harmi&thorn;, as it semi&thorn; bi &thorn;e speche of fei&thorn;ful men; nor mai not iustli wari him, ne pray iuil to him, ne punisch him, for he will do wel and fille Godds bidding, and amend his mis. In ani swilk maner &thorn;ei mai not curse ani swilk iust man.</P>
<P>But it seme&thorn; me &thorn;at it spede&thorn; a litil to seeke &thorn;e witte and &thorn;e sawis of fei&thorn;ful men, owe [how?] &thorn;ei speke of cursyng, for &thorn;er is mani maner of cursyng. &thorn;e first and &thorn;e warst, and &thorn;at is dedely synne, bi &thorn;e wilk a man synning, putti&thorn; him self out of cominyng of fei&thorn;ful men, &thorn;at is to sey, vndisposi&thorn; himsilf to tak part of &thorn;e merits of &thorn;e kirk, as it is of ilk man deed bi synne; and &thorn;us owi&thorn; no man to curse ani man, for God may not autorise &thorn;at actyfe cursyng; nor Crist was not &thorn;us cursid, for he synnid neuer. But passyue cursyng, &thorn;at is peyn be it self wi&thorn; synne folowand, is iust; wilke is proper God to &yogh;eue, and is iust medicyn &thorn;at &thorn;o synnar owi&thorn; for to take &thorn;ankfuly, and be sory for &thorn;e cause &thorn;erof: &thorn;er is also a no&thorn;er cursing, &thorn;at is preying of iuil or effectual warying or cursyng &thorn;at is iust, departing fro comyning of fei&thorn;ful men, and fro &thorn;e taking of &thorn;e sacraments. And a no&thorn;er by wilk a man cursi&thorn; a no&thorn;er contrarily to &thorn;e lawe of Crist, and &thorn;at but only in nam or pretendid.</P>
<P>&thorn;erfor to spek of &thorn;e cursyng of &thorn;e kirke, [by] &thorn;e wilk &thorn;e kirk de|nounci&thorn; opunly a synnar to be put out of comynyng, and be for|fendid 
<PB REF="00000079.tif" N="15"> him &thorn;o comyn feleschip of fei&thorn;fulmen, and taking of sacraments, &thorn;at he do &thorn;e ra&thorn;er penaunce, and infect not o&thorn;er, and &thorn;at &thorn;is be ritful bo&thorn; up &thorn;e side &thorn;at is cursid and up on &thorn;e kirk side cursing, be howfi&thorn; &thorn;e kirk to temt warly. For as &thorn;re condicouns mak martirdom faire, &thorn;at is to sai, ri&yogh;twisnes of &thorn;e cause, charita|ble pacience of &thorn;e martir, an vnri&yogh;twisnes of &thorn;e persewar, and so &thorn;at cursing be ri&yogh;twyse longen in a contrari maner; &thorn;at is to say, ri&yogh;twisnes in the kirk cursing, cause of vnri&yogh;twisnes in &thorn;e man cursid, and enemy of &thorn;e obstinat. And &thorn;us it may be, &thorn;of &thorn;e kirk curse a iust man iustly, as to form of vsing of lawe; na&thorn;les it is not iustly as to &thorn;e cause of so&thorn;fastnes, nor it may not, wyle &thorn;er is no cause of vnri&yogh;twisnes in &thorn;e man, ne obstynacy, ne ritwisnes in &thorn;e kirk, &thorn;us doing; &thorn;at is, wile God biddi&thorn; not &thorn;e kirk curse, &thorn;us &thorn;e vnri&yogh;twisnes of &thorn;e cause is synne going biforne, for wilk &thorn;e man schuld be cursid. Enemy of &thorn;e obstinat, wan &thorn;e synnar wil not dewli obey ne a mend. Ri&yogh;twisnes of &thorn;e kirk doing execucoun is wan &thorn;e kirk a cordi&thorn; wi&thorn; Crist, and &thorn;e kirk aboue; of mek charitable fei&thorn;ful entent, &thorn;enkyng helful correccoun of &thorn;e synnar to &thorn;e honor of God, procedi&thorn; in dewe ordre up &thorn;e gospel.</P>
<P>But, for to haue &thorn;e more clere and vndeceyuid knowyng of &thorn;is mater, cursing and assoling in mater of domis, and geuing of sentence in ani maner of dome, priuey or comyn, and in mater witnessing, and in materis to be don, &thorn;olid, susteynid, aprouid, confermid, canoni&yogh;id, autenkid, or to be helpid, in ani maner of cause a geyn ani man, or for ani &thorn;ing, me semi&thorn; now spedy to sey summe &thorn;ings.</P>
<P>First, I tak as fei&thorn;, &thorn;at no creature mai do iustli, wele, meri|torili, perfitly, vnsinfully, effectuali, ne perseuerantli ani &thorn;ing, not but if God wirk &thorn;at &thorn;ing bi him, and in him; &thorn;at if he do, or pre|sume to do &thorn;is &thorn;at God wirki&thorn; not bi him, he synne&thorn;, and his wark schal be in veyn, and idil, and schal not stond in profit. &thorn;is semi&thorn; &thorn;us, Crist mi&yogh;t not, &thorn;an mikil more non o&thorn;er creater mai &thorn;at Crist 
<PB REF="00000080.tif" N="16"> mi&yogh;t not, semi&thorn; &thorn;us; for he sei&thorn; in the gospel, &thorn;e Sone mai not of<NOTE PLACE="marg">Jo. u<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> himsilf ani &thorn;ing, nor nou&yogh;t, but as he se&thorn; &thorn;e Fadir doing; &thorn;at if he schuld do ani &thorn;ing &thorn;at God schuld not bi him, schuld do vniustly. For &thorn;us he sei&thorn;: If I bere witnes of misilf, mi wittnes is not trewe, it is Fadir &thorn;at beri&thorn; wittnes of me; and as &thorn;e Fadir beri&thorn; witnes of him, and biddi&thorn; him bere witnes and speke, so he beri&thorn; witnes and speki&thorn;. War for he sei&thorn;; &thorn;e words &thorn;at I speke, I speke not of misilf, but &thorn;e Fadir dwelling in me he do&thorn; &thorn;e dedis, and as he gaf me bidding so I spek. And so is ilk man holdun to spek, and do, and witnes, as &thorn;e Fadir giffi&thorn; bidding to hem. And &thorn;at no creater mai do iustli ani &thorn;ing, not but if Crist do it bi him, semi&thorn; &thorn;us. Ilk power in heuen and in &yogh;er&thorn;e is &yogh;euen to Crist. Also &thorn;e Fadir ha&thorn; &yogh;euen al dome to &thorn;e Sone, and al wysdam is of &thorn;e Lord God. &thorn;erfor wi&thorn; out Crist is no iust power, dome, ne wisdam; he ha&thorn; &thorn;e key of Dauid; he closi&thorn;, and &thorn;an no man<NOTE PLACE="marg">Apoc. iij.</NOTE> opunni&thorn;; he opunni&thorn; and &thorn;an no man closi&thorn;. If he dyng down, &thorn;an no man biggi&thorn; vppe. If he close, &thorn;an is &thorn;er no man &thorn;at may opun, ne iustli a&yogh;enstond him, nor no man mai sey &thorn;is schal be don, but if he bidde. And he giffi&thorn; power, and wisdam, and sei&thorn;: Wi&thorn; outen me &yogh;ee mai no &thorn;ing do. And for &thorn;is sei&thorn; Poule: We<NOTE PLACE="marg">Joh. xu<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> may not of our self &thorn;enk ani &thorn;ing as of ourself, but our sufficiens<NOTE PLACE="marg">2 Cor. iij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> is in God; and no werkis in vs and no &thorn;ing mai we a&yogh;en &thorn;e trow&thorn;,<NOTE PLACE="marg">2 Cor. xiij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> but for &thorn;e trow&thorn;. And for &thorn;is sei&thorn; &thorn;e prophet: Lord, &thorn;u hast wrout al our warkis in vs. And mani swilk witnes. And so, sin<NOTE PLACE="marg">Is. xxuj<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> no creater mai do iustli ani &thorn;ing wi&thorn; outun Crist, &thorn;an &thorn;e kirk may not, no&thorn;er general kirk, ne particuler; &thorn;e kirk in heuen, ne &thorn;e kirk sleping in purgatory, ne &thorn;e kirk fi&yogh;ting in &thorn;is world, aggregat, or gedred to gidre in on of Crist, and of al chosun to be blessid wi&thorn; him wi&thorn; outen ende, lepun vp to gidir in to oo spirit and con|corporel and conperseyuers and felows of &thorn;e hei&yogh;est of Crist, and of his godly kynd. As Petre sei&thorn; in his epistil, and Poul of Colo|censes: We&thorn;er it be &thorn;e kirk particuler, as were two or &thorn;re are 
<PB REF="00000081.tif" N="17"> gedrid to gidir in Cristis name, and of &thorn;e kirk; or if it be a per|sone ordeynid to do ani &thorn;ink in &thorn;e name of Crist and of &thorn;e kirk, he mai no &thorn;ing do iustli, but in maner befor seyde, &thorn;at Crist do it bi him.</P>
<P>And &thorn;us is opun &thorn;at &thorn;e kirk mai not iustli curse ne bles, but as he ha&thorn; befor ordeyned to be doun, and do it be &thorn;e kirk; &thorn;e kirk mai not ellis curse iustli, &thorn;at is no&thorn;er sequester ani man fro comyning of fei&thorn;ful men, ne fro part takyng of sacraments, ne for bid him ne to do ani &thorn;ing, ne joyn him penaunce, ne denounce, put out of comyn, ne bid iuil to him, ne curse him in ani maner, be wat nam &thorn;at cursing be callid; &thorn;e kirk may not do it iustli, ne vnblamfully, not but in als mikil as Crist ha&thorn; ordeynid to be doun, and doi&thorn; it bi &thorn;e kirk, and confermit it. And ri&yogh;t so of soiling; o&thorn;er wis may not &thorn;e kirk bring a man out of synne, ne for&yogh;ef &thorn;e peyn, nor man siker, ne pronounce, ne hi&yogh;t him to be soylid, in ani maner for ani cause. Ne o&thorn;er wyse howi&thorn; ani man to dred ani curse, not but in als mikil as it is &yogh;euen vp Cristis bidding, ne o&thorn;er wise ioi of assoiling; ne reste hemsilf siker &thorn;er for. O&thorn;er wyse ow &yogh;e not to drede it; &thorn;at is, &yogh;e ow not to drede it &thorn;at it schal greue &yogh;ow, or noy &yogh;ow, as at God to mak &yogh;ow sinful, or to be punischid, nor &yogh;e ow not cesse, ne abstene fro ani good wark, but vp &thorn;at Crist for bedi&thorn; it him. &thorn;is sentence is clere of manifold witnes of &thorn;e fei&thorn;ful opunning of holi writt, and publischid expresly and ympli&yogh;e&thorn;ly, and of &thorn;e sawis of fei&thorn;ful doctours, witnessing and expounding; and of &thorn;e decreis of &thorn;e kirk conferming. In canoun it is writun &thorn;us, of &thorn;e words of &thorn;e pope Leoun; &THORN;e priuylege of<NOTE PLACE="marg">Leoun.</NOTE> Petre dwelli&thorn; were euer &thorn;e dome is &yogh;euen aftir his equite, &thorn;at &thorn;e fersnes be no&thorn;er to mikil ne to litil, were no &thorn;ing schal be bounde ne lowsid, not or Petre byndi&thorn; or lowsi&thorn;. Who euer deserue to tak &thorn;e sentence of daming, if he wele perseyuer in his wit, no man mai relesse him. And also Jerom sei&thorn;, If ani man be put out<NOTE PLACE="marg">Jerom.</NOTE> nou&yogh;t be ri&yogh;t dome of hem &thorn;at are abouen to &thorn;e kirk, if he went 
<PB REF="00000082.tif" N="18"> not out be forne, &thorn;at is, dide not so &thorn;at he deseruid to be put out, he is no &thorn;ing hurt in &thorn;is &thorn;at he semi&thorn; to be put out fro men be dom not ri&yogh;t. And &thorn;us it is don &thorn;at sum tyme his [he?] is wi&thorn; inne &thorn;at is cast out, and he is wi&thorn; out &thorn;at semi&thorn; wi&thorn; inne. &thorn;us sei&thorn; he. And Gela&yogh;i &thorn;e pope sei&thorn;, He &thorn;at sentence is &yogh;euen a&yogh;en do he<NOTE PLACE="marg">Gelazi.</NOTE> awey &thorn;e error and it is voyd, and if it be vniust, so mikil he owi&thorn; to charge it &thorn;e lesse as at God and at his kirk. Wickid sentence mai greue no man, and so disire &yogh;e not to be assoilid &thorn;er of be wilk &yogh;e holdun &yogh;ou not boundon. &thorn;us sei&thorn; he. And Austyn sei&thorn;,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Austeyn.</NOTE> Vp on &thorn;e general fei&thorn;, no man mai noi &thorn;e kynd of God, ne &thorn;e kynd of God mai not noi ani man vniustly, ne &thorn;ole ani be noi&yogh;ed vniustly; he &thorn;at noi&thorn;, as &thorn;e Apostel sei&thorn;, schal reseyue &thorn;is &thorn;at he<NOTE PLACE="marg">Col. iij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> noi&thorn;. To &thorn;is acordi&thorn; Rabanus and o&thorn;er doctours mani; of wilk<NOTE PLACE="marg">Rabanus.</NOTE> &yogh;et it is spedi to rehers summe. &thorn;er is a cursing &thorn;at is dedli synne &thorn;e wilk &thorn;e man synning putti&thorn; himsilf out of comoun; &thorn;at is, vn|disposi&thorn; himsilf to tak part of merits of &thorn;e kirk, os it is of ilk ded be synne, and be swilk cursing is man waried to God. And &thorn;us no man ow to curse ani man, sin God mai not autorise &thorn;is cursing actif, for &thorn;us was neuer Crist cursid, for he synnid not. But cursing of peyn be it self folowand is iust, &thorn;e wilk longi&thorn; to God to &yogh;ef. &thorn;er is ano&thorn;er cursing, bi wilk &thorn;e kirk denounci&thorn; opunly a synnar put out of comyn, and forbedi&thorn; him comyn feleschip of cristun men, and &thorn;e takyng of sacraments, &thorn;at he mend &thorn;e ra&thorn;er, and smot not o&thorn;er. And of &thorn;is curse &thorn;e kirke speki&thorn; most famously. And &thorn;is is callid &thorn;e cursyng of &thorn;e kirk. To whas ri&yogh;tful ratifiyng, als wel on his syd &thorn;at is cursid, os on &thorn;e side of &thorn;e kirk cursing, &thorn;e kirk be houui&thorn; to tent to &thorn;re condicouns &thorn;at are requirid to &thorn;is lawful cursing; &thorn;at is, vnri&yogh;twisnes in the cause, enuy of a&yogh;en stonder, and ri&yogh;twisnes of &thorn;e kirke doing execucoun. &thorn;e first semi&thorn; &thorn;at no man is &thorn;us cursid but materaly for synne. Ilk synne is vnri&yogh;twysnes or brynging it in, &thorn;erfor to &thorn;is lawful curse is re|quirid &thorn;e vnri&yogh;twisnes of &thorn;e cause; ne it is a&yogh;en &thorn;is, but acording 
<PB REF="00000083.tif" N="19"> &thorn;at man be cursid, for &thorn;e honor of God, and profit of himsilf, and of &thorn;e peple, wi&thorn; mani final leful leke causis os it semi&thorn; of &thorn;e peyn of dampnid men. &thorn;e secounde circumstaunce semi&thorn; of &thorn;is, &thorn;at to lawful cursing is requirid &thorn;refald bro&thorn;er correcting, and but he dwel obstinat to &thorn;e fourt peyn &thorn;at is dede of &thorn;e kirk; for it is a pre|scripcoun fro comyning of fei&thorn;ful men; ellis &thorn;is cursing is not lawful. &thorn;e &thorn;rid circumstaunce semi&thorn; of &thorn;is, &thorn;at is it [it is?] not possible to be put of comyn of men, but &thorn;at if it be &thorn;erfor &thorn;ow a persoun prescit curse bi autorite of &thorn;e [kirk], neuer &thorn;e lesse he presupponi&thorn; &thorn;e kirk. And &thorn;us it semi&thorn; al onli in effect an heretik schuld vnderly &thorn;e curse of &thorn;e kirk; but it semi&thorn; &thorn;at ilk synning to &thorn;e de&thorn; is an heretik; as a&yogh;en ward a heretik is he &thorn;at synni&thorn; to &thorn;e de&thorn;, for ilk swilk pertinatly contrarily techi&thorn; to holi writte. And swilk curse, syn it is iust medicyn of &thorn;e gilty, schuld be tane &thorn;ankfully, for he is not perid &thorn;erby, but betteryd, or ellis his malice swagid. But he schuld do a wey &thorn;er of, and take &thorn;e medicyn, schakyng a wey synne from him be absolucoun of sacra|ment, and mekly taking a no&thorn;er absolucoun of iurisdiccoun of him &thorn;at cursid, by was vertewe he my&yogh;t comyn wi&thorn; cristun men and tak sacraments. And &thorn;ow &thorn;at medicyn be good for &thorn;e tyme, neuer&thorn;eles &thorn;e hele folowand is fare better. And bi resoun of &thorn;at prohibicoun fro comyng of fei&thorn;ful men and reseyuing of sacraments, syn it is not a sacrament supposid &thorn;at is it leful to a lewyd man in &thorn;e vertew of &thorn;e kirk to curse and louse; but wan ani after &thorn;e &thorn;ridde correpcoun dwelli&thorn; inobedient, he owi&thorn; not only to be de|nouncid a cursid, &thorn;at of sume is callid &thorn;e lesse curse; but comyn of fei&thorn;ful men and takyng of sacraments owun to be defendid him; &thorn;at is callid &thorn;e more curse &thorn;an &thorn;e kirke ha&thorn; ordeyned re|sounably; &thorn;at &thorn;e kirk performe it solemply, candel slekennid, bell rogun, and &thorn;e cros turnid vp so doun. neuer&thorn;eles it intendi&thorn; &thorn;e good of him &thorn;at is cursid charitabli, and profi&yogh;t of &thorn;e kirk. And it semi&thorn; be a no&thorn;er doctor to bring for&thorn; a no&thorn;er curse, be wilk it 
<PB REF="00000084.tif" N="20"> is leful to curse &thorn;e iust man, wi&thorn; outun his demerit, of forbeding him comyn of men, and taking of sacraments, &thorn;at he geit mede of his obedience, and &thorn;e sinnar be mad redy, or for summe o&thorn;er swilk cause. But certeyn I am &thorn;at &thorn;is curse may not be done wi&thorn; outun resounable cause; ne &thorn;e nakyd wille of &thorn;e prelat is not inowe &thorn;erto; ne a man is not holdun for swilk curse to leef &thorn;ing &thorn;at he is holdun to do bi Godds bidding. Neuer&thorn;eles he mai medulfully cesser fro summe dedis for a tyme, and deserue for obediens. And if ani can ground &thorn;is maner of cursyng I consent.</P>
<P>But how &thorn;at we spek of curse oi&thorn;er it &thorn;at is dedly, or peyn con|sequent &thorn;er of, or ellis warying, or it &thorn;at is sequestracoun of &thorn;e iust man fro comyn, or it be wilke &thorn;e iust man be cursid as contrari to Godds lawe, &thorn;at is but only in name or pretendand, or ani o&thorn;er, it semi&thorn; &thorn;at noun owi&thorn; to curse ani principali for money, for his proper cause or wrong don til him.</P>
<P>&THORN;is semi&thorn; bi ensaumpul of Crist and Moyses, and swilk o&thorn;er; and also be doctors and laws of &thorn;e kirk: for bi lawe canoun no man howi&thorn; to curse in his owne proper cause; for vnder &thorn;e autorite of Gregor &thorn;e kirk writi&thorn; &thorn;us; Among mani quarells a nobil man,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Gregor.</NOTE> Ysidore, pleynid him to be cursid of &thorn;e [thy] bro&thorn;er hed, and wan we lere of &thorn;e [thy] clerk &thorn;at was present for wat cause &thorn;is was don, he maad knowen for non o&thorn;er cause, but for he had greuid &thorn;ee. Wilk &thorn;ing noi&yogh;i&thorn; vs ri&yogh;t gretly, if it be so; &thorn;u schewist &thorn;ee to &thorn;enk no &thorn;ing of heuenly &thorn;ings, but tokunist &thorn;ee to haue an &yogh;er&thorn;li conuer|sacoun, til &thorn;u haue done cursing for venging of &thorn;i selue; &thorn;at is defendid bi holi rewlis. Werfore fro hene for&thorn; be wel bisy abowt. And presume &thorn;u neuer to do aftur swilk &thorn;ingis, for defence of &thorn;i noune iniurie; for if &thorn;u do ani swilk &thorn;ing, wyte &thorn;u wel it to vengid after in &thorn;i self. Werfor &thorn;e glose of Ion sei&thorn;, &THORN;e bischop<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ion.</NOTE> mai not curse ani man for wrong don to him, nor mai not be iuge in his oune cause, &thorn;at is to vnderstond, namly, it is leful to no man to curse principali for his o une proper cause.
<PB REF="00000085.tif" N="21"></P>
<P>&thorn;is semi&thorn; be ensaumple of Crist, for he wold not curse hem &thorn;at denoied to him harborow and lifelod, but reprouid his disciplis<NOTE PLACE="marg">Luc. ix.</NOTE> askyng veniawns; and wan he was waried he waried not a&yogh;en,<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Pet. ij.</NOTE> wan he was punischid, he manest not a&yogh;en, but mekly be toke him|silf to him &thorn;at iugid him vniustly; and &thorn;e peyn of o&thorn;er synne bare, and prayed for his cruciars.</P>
<P>Also be ensaumple of Moyses, wan &thorn;e peple synnid in to God, he vengid it; and wan &thorn;ei greuid him he &thorn;olid, and &yogh;aue &thorn;e cause to God.</P>
<P>Also it be howui&thorn; &thorn;o synne to be notory and greuows, for wilk cursyng schuld be done. Were &thorn;e Archedecoun sei&thorn;, &thorn;at &thorn;e more<NOTE PLACE="marg">Archede|coun.</NOTE> curse is to be &yogh;euun for contumacy alone; and &thorn;is he groundi&thorn; be mani lawis. And al o&thorn;er lawis &thorn;at semen to sey, &thorn;at man how to curse for crime of vowtre, &thorn;eft, and swilk o&thorn;er; so &thorn;at vndir|stond for contumacy descendend of swilk crime. And he sei&thorn; Lincoln to be of &thorn;e same sentence, and Innocent, seing &thorn;at man is<NOTE PLACE="marg">Lincoln.</NOTE> not to be cursid only for &thorn;e crime, if he wil amend him. And &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">Innocent.</NOTE> sentence of Crist acordi&thorn; in &thorn;e gospel; were cursing is groundid. Were for &thorn;e kirk sei&thorn;, None of bischoppis priue ani man fro comyn|ing of &thorn;e kirk, wi&thorn; outun certeyn and opun cause of synne.<NOTE PLACE="marg">The kirk.</NOTE> And resoun is &thorn;is, for ilk cursing vniustli also cursi&thorn; himsilf, for he synni&thorn; dedly. And Austeyn sei&thorn;, as is be for seid: No man mai<NOTE PLACE="marg">Austeyn.</NOTE> noye kynd of God.</P>
<P>Of &thorn;e wilk semi&thorn; &thorn;re notable conclusiouns: first, &thorn;at God mai not curse ani man ne suffur him to be noi&yogh;ed to his pering, but himsilf be first in cause; for &thorn;e curse of &thorn;e kirk taki&thorn; not a wey ri&yogh;tfulnes ne vertu, ne inferri&thorn; not synne, but schewi&thorn; departing fro comyn of seynts, and defendi&thorn; medicinable comyning wi&thorn; &thorn;e kirk or sacraments of it. Were for sei&thorn; Archedecoun, efter &thorn;at he<NOTE PLACE="marg">Archede|coun.</NOTE> schewi&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;e keyes of &thorn;e kirk only byndun and lousun, wan &thorn;ei are confermid to &thorn;e keyes of Crist, &thorn;at bynding or lousing of &thorn;e prelat is not &thorn;e cause why ani is lousid or boundun in heuin. But 
<PB REF="00000086.tif" N="22"> &thorn;us it is seid, for oft &thorn;ei felow hemsilf to gidir and for &thorn;ei how to<NOTE PLACE="marg">Decreis.</NOTE> felow hemsilf to gidir, os it semi&thorn; bi &thorn;e decreis and sentence of doctors cording to gidir, is, &thorn;at &thorn;e keyes erring noi&thorn;er bindun ne lowsoun as to God. &thorn;e &thorn;rid is &thorn;is, &thorn;at he &thorn;at vniustly cursi&thorn; as to &thorn;e face of &thorn;e kirk, noi&yogh;&thorn; principali himsilf, for he misusi&thorn; his powar. Werfor<NOTE PLACE="marg">Decre.</NOTE> &thorn;e decre sei&thorn;, We are not dampnid wi&thorn; out dom, wan we are cursid<NOTE PLACE="marg">Archede|coun.</NOTE> vniustly. Archedecoun sei&thorn;, &thorn;at he &thorn;at cursi&thorn; his sugetis vniustly incurri&thorn; sacrilege, for sacrilege is to file holy &thorn;ing; &thorn;erfor he &thorn;at cursi&thorn; vniustly fili&thorn; &thorn;e holi body of &thorn;e kirk, fro wam he pulli&thorn; out vniustly his membre. And I deme not but &thorn;at ilk curse is to be deede, for &thorn;at he is cursid vniustly, howi&thorn; to examin him diligently after holi writte, &thorn;at he be not gilty in ani &thorn;ing. &THORN;e secounde he houi&thorn; to drede of &thorn;e perel of him &thorn;at cursi&thorn; vniustly. And &thorn;e &thorn;rid of harm of &thorn;e bro&thorn;er &thorn;at may cum of &thorn;e forbodun of &thorn;e comunicatise doc|trine<NOTE PLACE="marg">Lincoln.</NOTE> of bro&thorn;er. And &thorn;is dede Lincoln, &thorn;at he calli&thorn; to &thorn;e popis cowrt, wan he was manifold greuid &thorn;ore, he appellid stalliwor&thorn;li fro &thorn;e court of Innocent &thorn;e fer&thorn;e, vn to &thorn;e barre of Crist. Ne&thorn;eles it is not to deme &thorn;at ne it is leful to curse accessorily; for &thorn;at tendi&thorn; but to men lifing actifly; syn &thorn;at execucoun of &thorn;is curse<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Cor. vi<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> saueri&thorn; seculer cause, and &thorn;e Apostil biddi&thorn;, If &yogh;e han seculer nedis, ordeyn &thorn;oo &thorn;at are contemptible, &thorn;at are in &thorn;e kirk, to deme. And<NOTE PLACE="marg">Decre.</NOTE> &thorn;is is notable to wite, in &thorn;e decre vndre autorite of &thorn;e sen&yogh;e and of seint Jerome, were after &thorn;at he schewi&thorn; &thorn;at vnleful curse hirti&thorn; not him &thorn;at is notid &thorn;er wi&thorn;, os innocents, he sei&thorn;, mai not be condempnid wi&thorn; &thorn;e crime of a no&thorn;er, he obiecti&thorn; vnder &thorn;is forme, Crist sei&thorn;, and &thorn;e Apostil: Blesse and wil &yogh;e not curse. Mischel was not hardi to &yogh;eue dome of blasfemy to &thorn;e fend, most wor&thorn;i<NOTE PLACE="marg">Jude j<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> curse, as &thorn;e Apostil sei&thorn;, howe mykil more howe we to be clene of al cursyng. &THORN;e fend seruid curse; but blasfemie howi&thorn; not to go out of &thorn;e aungelis mou&thorn;. Rede &thorn;e holde bokis, and see wilk lynage were sett in &thorn;e hille of Gari&yogh;ym to bles &thorn;e puple; and wilk in &thorn;e hille of Hebal to curse. Ruben &thorn;at filid his fadir bedde, and Zabloun 
<PB REF="00000087.tif" N="23"> &thorn;e last son of Lia, and &thorn;e sonis of &thorn;e wengis were sette in &thorn;e hille of Hebal to curse hem &thorn;at were wor&thorn;i curse. And wan we are taw&yogh;t gostly of alle storis of &thorn;e wold testament how it is to do in tyme of grace, it semi&thorn; &thorn;at half of &thorn;e linage blessing betokyn hem &thorn;at charitabli purli for desire of hietis of Crist comyn to &thorn;e hille; &thorn;e to&thorn;er half cursing meni&thorn; hem &thorn;at for drede of torment filling &thorn;e lawe comun to &thorn;e hille. Also &thorn;ei tokun actifis and contem|platifis; &thorn;at sterun to vertewe be &thorn;er two maneris. &THORN;e souereynes of &thorn;e kirke howun not to curse for temporal &thorn;ingis; ne bisy a bowt hem, but bles and preche. &THORN;at it is leful for to curse semi&thorn; of &thorn;e oold stori, and of &thorn;e newe testament; but &thorn;e canoun distingui&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="marg">Canoun.</NOTE> &thorn;us; Cursing &thorn;at is forbidon is &thorn;is &thorn;at procedi&thorn; of wille of veniaunce or hate of &thorn;e perseware, not purli of &thorn;e luf of ri&yogh;twisnes; and proui&thorn; &thorn;is of mani witts of seyntis. &THORN;erfor it is certeyn &thorn;at iche man cursing, wi&thorn; out stering of &thorn;e Holi Goost first cursing, or not &thorn;enkyng charitabli good of him &thorn;at is cursid, and good of &thorn;e kirk, he synni&thorn; greuowsly; &thorn;erfor sei&thorn; &thorn;e canoun, vnder autorite of Gre|<NOTE PLACE="marg">Canoun.</NOTE> gori, Prestis synnen not in &thorn;at curse, in wilk &thorn;ei discord not fro &thorn;e innare iuge. And after, vnder &thorn;e autorite of Austeyn, Sogets<NOTE PLACE="marg">Austeyn.</NOTE> ben correctid of o&thorn;er prouastis wi&thorn; correccoun comyng of charite, and for &thorn;e diuersite of synnis. But now it semi&thorn; to men wel be haldyng &thorn;at prelats and prestis &thorn;eis daies in &thorn;e court of pleet, and &thorn;ei &thorn;at persewen causis a&yogh;en &thorn;er neybors, enfectun and warioun hem silf manifold and sinfully foilun ilk o&thorn;er. Also &thorn;at mani cursing now blowun in &thorn;e kirk are not to be dredde, not but in als mikil of &thorn;ei smotte &thorn;e curse or o&thorn;er of cause on o&thorn;er side. And til is concordyng to &thorn;e first curse of God. It is semyng be &thorn;is wan it is no&thorn;er foundid in holi writt, ne in &thorn;e lif of Crist, ne of his Apostlis. But alle &thorn;ings &thorn;at prelats owun to do are sufficienly groundid &thorn;er, and &thorn;an si&thorn;en &thorn;ei curse not &thorn;us, it is not to drede o&thorn;er wise, &thorn;an as is seid before in &thorn;e strong autorite. Also for Crist forbedi&thorn; swilk maner of cursing, os now in case is vsid in &thorn;e 
<PB REF="00000088.tif" N="24"> kirk. As &thorn;e gospel of Luc telli&thorn;, and absteni&thorn; &thorn;erfro as it semi&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="marg">Luc.</NOTE> of Schario&thorn;, and neuer&thorn;eles in him was more cause of cursing &thorn;an in sum &thorn;at to day are blawun in &thorn;e kirk. It vali&thorn; not to seie &thorn;at Petre cursid Anani, and Poule &thorn;e fornicary, for &thorn;ei cursid be a cursing &thorn;at mani prelats to day kan not, nor han not power to. Petre be tok Anani bi dede going be for to &thorn;e fend to be tormentid perpetuali. And Poule be toke &thorn;e fornicari to sa&thorn;anas til a tyme, &thorn;at his spirit schulde be saue. But mani prelats are out of part of &thorn;is maner of cursing. Also bi &thorn;e fei&thorn; of &thorn;e gospel no man owi&thorn; to curse a no&thorn;er not but of charite &thorn;at he ha&thorn; to him, for of &thorn;e fei&thorn; we owe to luf our enmies, and also for to do alle &thorn;ings in charite, for mani man cursi&thorn; now not for charite, and &thorn;erfor not fei&thorn;fully. A part prouid of &thorn;is signe, &thorn;at &thorn;ei curse more souare and horribe|lare hem &thorn;at &thorn;ei hatun, as it semi&thorn; of hem &thorn;at are cursid for &thorn;ei wil not &yogh;ef money or reuerens to &thorn;e mynisteris of &thorn;e kirk. And &thorn;us it semi&thorn; &thorn;at prelats mai mikil drede of &thorn;er cursyng hem silf, and o&thorn;er ioi of &thorn;er cursyng, and dred mikil &thorn;er blessing; for Salamon sei&thorn;, Cursing veinli brout schal pletesuowsli descende in<NOTE PLACE="marg">Salamon.</NOTE> to summe man; &thorn;at is as &thorn;e glose sei&thorn;, in to him &thorn;at bringi&thorn; it<NOTE PLACE="marg">Glose.</NOTE> for&thorn;. And sei&thorn; &thorn;e salm, He lufid cursing, and it schal cum to him.<NOTE PLACE="marg">Salm. cviii<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> And he dede on cursyng os a clo&thorn;, and entred as water in to his inword &thorn;ings, and as oyly in to his bonis. Be it made to him a clo&thorn;e &thorn;at he is helid wi&thorn;, and as belt &thorn;at is he ai gird wi&thorn;. And Poul sei&thorn;, Cursars schal not weld &thorn;o kyndam of God. And bi &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Cor. vi<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> Prophet God sei&thorn; &thorn;us, Nowe to &yogh;ow prestis &thorn;is sonde, if &yogh;e wil not<NOTE PLACE="marg">Mal. ij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> sett to &thorn;e hert to &yogh;ef glory to my name, sei&thorn; &thorn;e Lord, I schal sende hunger vn to &yogh;ow, and I schal curse to &yogh;or blessing, and I schal curse to hem, for &yogh;e sett not to &thorn;e herte. And on &thorn;e to&thorn;er side &thorn;e salme sei&thorn;, &thorn;ei schal curse, and &thorn;u Lord schalt blesse. And so sei&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="marg">Salme cviii<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> Crist, &yogh;e schal be blessid wan men schal curse &yogh;ow, and persew<NOTE PLACE="marg">Mat. u<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> &yogh;ow, and sey al iuel a&yogh;en &yogh;ow, and reproue &yogh;ow, and cast out &yogh;oure name as iuel, liand vp on &yogh;ow for me, and for &thorn;e gospel; ioie&thorn; and 
<PB REF="00000089.tif" N="25"> be&thorn; glad, for &yogh;or mede is plentiuous in heuen. God bring us to his. And prelats mai sore drede, &thorn;at her vniust and iuilwilly cursing be in cause whi &thorn;e puple dredi&thorn; not cursing, nor mendi&thorn; not, but a&yogh;enstondi&thorn; and risi&thorn; a&yogh;en hem; and &thorn;is is cause of al iuil, for ilk crature wi&thorn; God au&yogh;t to &yogh;enstond falshed: for &thorn;us is writun in &thorn;e Psalme, Who schal rise to gidre wi&thorn; me a&yogh;enis &thorn;e iuil willid, or<NOTE PLACE="marg">Psalme xciii<SUP>o</SUP>. Sap. u<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> who schal stonde wi&thorn; me a&yogh;en &thorn;e wirking wickidnes. And &thorn;e wise man, &THORN;e gelousy of him schal tak armor, and arme &thorn;e crature to venge him on &thorn;e wickid, and wi&thorn; him al &thorn;e world schal fi&yogh;t a&yogh;en &thorn;e vnwitti, and &thorn;e spirit of vertu schal stond a&yogh;en, and as a wirlwynd schal diuide hem; and wickydnes schal bring al &yogh;er&thorn; to wildrenes, for cursing &thorn;e &yogh;er&thorn; swelli&thorn;, and iuil wille schal turne out &thorn;e setis of &thorn;e mi&yogh;ti. And as seynt Jame sei&thorn;, As &thorn;e welle mai not bring<NOTE PLACE="marg">Jac. iii<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> for&thorn; of o pitte bitter water and swete; so mai we not blesse God wi&thorn; &thorn;e mou&thorn;, &thorn;at we curse man made to his lekenes.</P>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="4" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>IV. Crist was cursid.</HEAD>
<P>&THORN;is is a no&thorn;er point, for I seid &thorn;at Crist was cursid. But &thorn;ei toke heuely at &thorn;e worde, &thorn;erfore I preied to excuse me or spare me in termis; and neuer&thorn;eles to trewe vnderstonding me &thorn;inki&thorn; it mai be seid so&thorn;li, and wi&thorn; out blame: for we schal vnderstond bi Holi Writte, and bi teching of seynts and bi resoun, and bi comyn experiens, &thorn;at in &thorn;re maners is a man seid cursid. Ffirst<NOTE PLACE="marg">1<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> and warst be synne, wan he cursi&thorn; himsilf, and bi his wickid dede go&thorn; out of comyn of holi men, and vndisposi&thorn; him to tak part of merits of &thorn;e kirk. And &thorn;us mai not God curse ani man, ne bid ani man curse, ne a proue it, ne &thorn;us was Crist neuer cursid, for he synnid neuer. In &thorn;e secound maner is man cursid iustli, wan<NOTE PLACE="marg">2<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> God wordeyni&thorn; him for &thorn;is synne to be putte to peyn, and out of comyn, and to be waried, or denouncid, or schewid, as cursid and haldun swilk. And &thorn;us is man iustli cursid and wor&thorn;ili, wan men curse him bi Godds biddyng, and &thorn;an &thorn;ei do it medefully. And &thorn;us God cursi&thorn; men, and &thorn;e &yogh;er&thorn;, and bests, and o&thorn;er &thorn;ings in mannis wark, wan he ordeyni&thorn; &thorn;eis &thorn;ings to be noyous to man, and 
<PB REF="00000090.tif" N="26"> punisch him, and not to bring for&thorn; frut; and &thorn;us he sei&thorn; he wille curse to her blessing, wan &thorn;ei wil not kepe his bidding; for wan &thorn;ei prey for plentey, and pees, and swilk o&thorn;er &thorn;ings, and delitun in &thorn;eis &thorn;ings, and &yogh;ekun &thorn;er synnis &thorn;ar by, he wil send hem skarnes and noi&yogh;es, and &thorn;ole hem to haue debate, and punische hem in mani wyes, and ay &thorn;e moo lusts &thorn;at &thorn;ei haue here, ay &thorn;e more schal ben &thorn;er peyn. And &thorn;us he cursi&thorn; to &thorn;er blessing. And so &thorn;is &thorn;at mani callun blessing is cursing. And a&yogh;en ward; &thorn;us we prayen iuil and cursing to our neybor iustli, wan we desire &thorn;at discese and o&thorn;er enuyes be to hem to lette hem of iuil and to mak hem to drede synne and to do bettar. And &thorn;us we blame childre and misdoars. And &thorn;us Iob cursid his day. And Jeremy &thorn;at man &thorn;at<NOTE PLACE="marg">Iob 3<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> callid his fadre &thorn;at a son was born to &thorn;im, and as bi ioy gladid him,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Jer. 20<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> for &thorn;ey desirid &thorn;at &thorn;eis schuld lette men fro doing of iuil and be in a maner to stere men to be heuy of &thorn;er mysse and to desire to be heyne; for &thorn;us were good to mani a man, &thorn;at &thorn;ings were in desesse to him, &thorn;at now are in mikil leking. But &yogh;et in &thorn;is maner of curse &thorn;at men curse man iustli for his misdede, was Crist not cursid, for he seruid not to be cursid, nor God bad not men curse him, ne &thorn;ei dede not &thorn;is iustly to him. But in &thorn;e &thorn;rid maner a &thorn;ing is seid<NOTE PLACE="marg">3<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> cursid wan men cursun man &thorn;ow &thorn;ei do it vniustly, or bannun him, or puttun him out of comyn, or haldun him cursid, or denounce, or schew him cursid. And &thorn;us comyn speche calli&thorn; men cursid. And bi lawis of &thorn;e kirk men are &thorn;us cursid, and bidun to be holdun cursid, wan &thorn;ei are wel good, and &thorn;e more blessid of God. And &thorn;us Crist was cursid of men, and olden cursid, and put out of comyn of men, and put to de&thorn; as cursid man. And &thorn;us sei&thorn; Poule,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Gal. 3<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> He was mad for vs &thorn;at cursid &thorn;ing, &thorn;at we schuld be mad blessid in him. And &thorn;e prophet Ysaye, &thorn;at we arettid him as smitun of<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ysa. 53<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> God and lafte, and &thorn;us he sei&thorn; bi &thorn;e prophet &thorn;at alle men cursun to him. But for &thorn;is is he mikil &thorn;e bettar and not &thorn;e wars. And we schuld luf him &thorn;e bettar and desire &thorn;us to be cursid wi&thorn; &thorn;im, 
<PB REF="00000091.tif" N="27"> as Poule dede, and Moyses, and odir, as Holi Writt sei&thorn; of hem; for Poule sei&thorn; he desirid to be cursid of Crist for his bre&thorn;er, to<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ro. 9, a.</NOTE> make hem saue. And Moises praied to for&yogh;eue &thorn;e puple &thorn;er<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ex. 32<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> synne, or ellis to do him out of his book; not &thorn;at &thorn;ei desirid to do synne and be cursid wor&thorn;ily; but &thorn;at &thorn;ei wold &thorn;us wi&thorn; out desert be punischid as cursid for &thorn;e peple, to make &thorn;em saue. And &thorn;us schuld we alle if we were in charite, as me &thorn;inki&thorn;.</P>
<P>And it semi&thorn; bi sindre resouns it mai be seid &thorn;at Crist was<NOTE PLACE="marg">1<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> cursid; first bi &thorn;is &thorn;at he was made man wi&thorn; outun synne &thorn;at was cursid of God, and iustli put out of lordschip and comyn for a tyme. &thorn;e secound, for he was in his persoun &thorn;us wi&thorn; out desert punischid,<NOTE PLACE="marg">2<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> as if he had ben cursid. &thorn;e &thorn;rid, for he is cursid in his membris &thorn;at<NOTE PLACE="marg">3<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> are oon wi&thorn; him. After &thorn;is &thorn;at he sei&thorn;, &thorn;is &thorn;at &yogh;e dede til ani of hem lest of myn good or iuil, &yogh;e did it to me. And &thorn;at &yogh;e ded not to hem &yogh;e ded not to me. And &thorn;is schuld maak men rad to do ani iuil to ani good man, or to curse him, or to gruch a&yogh;en him, for it soundi&thorn; in to Crist. And &thorn;erfor seid Moyses, &yogh;or grucching<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ex. 16<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> is a&yogh;en &thorn;e Lord. &thorn;us as he is seid cursid &thorn;at men cursun. And as al men of a comynte berun punisching for &thorn;e defaut of two or on, &thorn;us it is be twen Crist and vs, for &thorn;us was he punischid for vs. And &thorn;us sei&thorn; Peter &thorn;at he bare our synnes, for he bare &thorn;e peyn of<NOTE PLACE="marg">Pe. 3<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> hem. And &thorn;us he calli&thorn; our synnis and our defauts his. And &thorn;us he sei&thorn; in &thorn;e Salm, God my God loke in to me, why hast &thorn;u<NOTE PLACE="marg">Salm. 22.</NOTE> left me, fare fro my heyle, &thorn;o wordis of my defauts. And God &yogh;et left neuer Crist, but ay is wi&thorn; him, for he do&thorn; ai &thorn;o &thorn;ingis &thorn;at plesun God, os himself sei&thorn;. But for he &thorn;olid him &thorn;us be punischid, and for he left sum membris of &thorn;e kirk at a tyme, for &thorn;is he sei&thorn; &thorn;at he left him. And &thorn;us was Crist callid a synnar and blasfemer, and &thorn;e cursidist man in &yogh;er&thorn;e, for &thorn;ei seid &thorn;at he was a deuowrar, and &thorn;at he blasfemid. And &thorn;us, as we sey &thorn;at man a &yogh;efe blasfeme or cursid, wan he is &thorn;us iugid and rettid of men, &thorn;ow he be not so in so&thorn;nes, in &thorn;is maner we sey of Crist &thorn;at he was blasfem, synnar, 
<PB REF="00000092.tif" N="28"> and cursid, and &thorn;at he &yogh;et was not; for he blasfemid not, ne synnid, ne did no &thorn;ing wor&thorn;i curse; and &thorn;at Crist wold &thorn;ole al &thorn;is schuld we be glad, and leren to &thorn;ole wi&thorn; him; and &thorn;an bi &thorn;at we schal be holdun of God &thorn;e more blessid, and be &thorn;e more blessid, and be so perceyuers of Cristis meritis.</P>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="5" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>V. Ich prest may vse the key.</HEAD>
<P>An o&thorn;er is &thorn;is &thorn;at is put and askid, &thorn;at ilk prest may vse &thorn;e key in to ilk man. To &thorn;is, me &thorn;inki&thorn;, I may wel sey &thorn;us, syn al power is of God, and, as &thorn;e gospel sei&thorn;, &thorn;er is no power but of God, ne man may do no &thorn;ing, but if he &yogh;eue him &thorn;e mi&yogh;t; as Crist sei&thorn;, &yogh;e may wi&thorn; out me do no &thorn;ing, &thorn;at onely a man vse his power in to<NOTE PLACE="marg">Joh. 15<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> ilk &thorn;ing, as God werki&thorn; bi him, and lefi&thorn; him to vse it vnblamfully, and no for&thorn;er, and fro &thorn;at may no man lette him. And &thorn;is is &thorn;at we sey, &thorn;at we may of ri&yogh;t so, if &thorn;er be ani vsing of power, or callid power, &thorn;at is not bi Crist, &thorn;at is no power, but fals pride, and presumid, and onli in name, and as to &yogh;end and effect is now&yogh;t. Neuer&thorn;eles, a man is seid to haue power, and leue to vse power, in many wyse, as sum bi lawe and ordre of kynd, sum bi lawe and ordre of grace, and some bi lawe and ordre made and writun. And so it is seid bi lawe &thorn;at is mad of &thorn;e kirk, &thorn;at ilk prest ha&thorn; &thorn;e same power to vse &thorn;e key in to ani man in &thorn;o poynt of de&thorn;, as &thorn;e pope; but not ellis, not but autorite in special be &yogh;euun to him of &thorn;e kirk &thorn;er to. But if it be askid, if ilk prest mai vse &thorn;e key in to ilk man, &thorn;at is to sey, to assoile him, or ellis to bind him fro grace, it semi&thorn; opunly &thorn;at ilk prest may not asoile ilk to bring him to heuyn; for &thorn;e gospel sei&thorn;, &thorn;at Crist in a coost of &thorn;e Jewis mi&yogh;t<NOTE PLACE="marg">Matt. 13<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> not do ani vertu &thorn;er, for &thorn;e vntrou&thorn;, not but helid a few seek, &thorn;e handus leyd vpon, and he maruelid for &thorn;er vntrow&thorn;; &thorn;an, wan Crist, &thorn;at is God Almi&yogh;ty, and of his absolut power may al &thorn;ing, and no &thorn;ing is vnpossible to him, nor no &thorn;ing may a&yogh;en stond him, and &yogh;et may not of his ordinat power &yogh;ele &thorn;e folk for &thorn;er ontrow&thorn;, and vndisposicoun, and vnabilite to reseyue, mich more ani o&thorn;er bene&thorn; may not help, but after &thorn;e disposicoun of him &thorn;at receyui&thorn;. 
<PB REF="00000093.tif" N="29"> Al so it semi&thorn; bi &thorn;is, &thorn;at &thorn;e pope may not bring in to grace, ne bles, him &thorn;at lasti&thorn; in vntrow&thorn;, and in &thorn;er synnis; os it semi&thorn; bi Jewes and Saracenis and o&thorn;er swilk, os is witnessid, and of fei&thorn;ful witnes. Also God &yogh;aue him no farrer power, not but asoyl hem &thorn;at wil leue &thorn;er synne, or to bynd hem and curse &thorn;at wil dure &thorn;er inne. And bi so &thorn;e same resoun none o&thorn;er prest may not excede. And if it be axid we&thorn;er ilk prest ha&thorn; as mykil power as &thorn;e pope, as a nenist God, it semi&thorn; to me &thorn;at is foly to a ferme in &thorn;is case oi&thorn;er &yogh;ie or nay, be for &thorn;at it mai be schewid out of Holi Writte. And so it semi&thorn; al so to me it is foly ani prest to presume him to haue euyn power wi&thorn; ilk o&thorn;er, be for &thorn;at he may ground him in &thorn;e fei&thorn;; and foli it were to deme to ani man any power &thorn;at God ha&thorn; &yogh;euun to him, or &thorn;e vsyng &thorn;er of; for certeyn I am, how euer ani man tak power to him, or vse power, it profi&thorn; not, but in as myche as God &yogh;eui&thorn; it, and wirki&thorn; wi&thorn; it, and confermi&thorn; it; and certayn I am, &thorn;at &thorn;e power &thorn;at God &yogh;aue Petre, he &yogh;aue it not to him alone, ne for him alone, but he &yogh;aue it to &thorn;e kirk, and for &thorn;o kirk, and to edifying of al &thorn;e kirk; os he &yogh;eui&thorn; &thorn;e si&yogh;t of &thorn;e ee, or &thorn;e act of ani membre of &thorn;e body, for help and edifying of al &thorn;e body. And Sent Jerom sei&thorn;, Sum tyme &thorn;e prest was &thorn;at ilk &thorn;at &thorn;e bischop.<NOTE PLACE="marg">Jerom.</NOTE> And bi for &thorn;at bats were made in religioun bi stinging of &thorn;e fend, and was seid in &thorn;e peple, I am of Petre, I of Poule, I of Apollo, I of Cephas, &thorn;e kirkis were gouernid bi &thorn;e comyn of prestis coun|seil. But after &thorn;at ilk man callid him &thorn;at he bapti&yogh;id his, and not Crists, &thorn;an was in al &thorn;e world wordeynid &thorn;at on of &thorn;e prestis schuld be made chefe, and &thorn;e seedis of scysmis schuld be tan a wey. &thorn;er as prestis wit hem to be to &thorn;er souereynis sogets be custum of &thorn;is kirk, so knaw bischopis hem to be more of custum &thorn;an of dispensacoun of Goddis trow&thorn;, to &thorn;er sogets, &thorn;e more &thorn;er souereyns, and in comyn &thorn;ei owe to gouern &thorn;e kirk. Lo I sey bischops present, and &thorn;at &thorn;ei stondun nere him, prests mai in &thorn;e autere mak &thorn;e sacrament. But for it is writun, Prestis &thorn;at<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Tim. 5.</NOTE> 
<PB REF="00000094.tif" N="30"> prestun wel bi &thorn;ei wor&thorn;i had dowble honor, most &thorn;at &thorn;ei trauel in word and teching: it semi&thorn; hem to preche, it is profit to bles, it is congrew to sacre, it cordi&thorn; to hem to &yogh;eue comyn, it is necesari to hem to visit &thorn;e sek, to pray for &thorn;e vnmi&yogh;ti, and to fele of &thorn;e sacraments of God. &THORN;erfor non of &thorn;e bischopis, enblawen wi&thorn; enuy<NOTE PLACE="marg">Jerom.</NOTE> of &thorn;e fendis temptacoun, wra&thorn;, if prestis ouerwile exort or monest &thorn;e peple, if &thorn;ei preche in kirk, if &thorn;ey blesse &thorn;e floc, for I schal sey &thorn;us to hym &thorn;at werni&thorn; me &thorn;eis &thorn;ings, he &thorn;at wil not prestus do &thorn;ing &thorn;at &thorn;ei are bidun of God, sey he wat is more &thorn;an Crist? or wat may be put beforn his flesch and blode? And if &thorn;e prest sacre Crist wan he blessi&thorn; &thorn;e sacrament of God in &thorn;e auter, awi&thorn; he not to blessi&thorn; &thorn;e peple, &thorn;at dredi&thorn; not to sacre Crist? A &yogh;e vniust prestis &thorn;orow &yogh;or bidding &thorn;e prest of God stinti&thorn; &thorn;e office of bless|ing, a bowt lewid men and women; he stinti&thorn; &thorn;e wark of tong, he ha&thorn; no tryst of preching, he is dockid on ilk part, he ha&thorn; only &thorn;e name of prest, but he holdi&thorn; not &thorn;e plente ne &thorn;e perfeccoun &thorn;at falli&thorn; to his consecracoun. I pray &yogh;ow prestis wat honor is &thorn;is to &yogh;ow, &thorn;at &yogh;e bring in &thorn;e damage of alle &thorn;e folke? for wan wor&thorn;i diligence is taken a wey fro prestis bi power, sum smiting of mis|chef rysi&thorn; in &thorn;e flok; and &yogh;e geyt harme of &thorn;e Lordis patrimoyn, til &yogh;e alon wil be potentats in &thorn;e kirk. And for &thorn;i seyn o&thorn;er men &thorn;us, if a bischop in conferming &thorn;at he appropri&thorn; to him silf wi&thorn; out ground of &thorn;e Scripter, &yogh;eui&thorn; grace, whi not a simple prest &thorn;at in merit is more at God, of mor merit, gefe mor wor&thorn;i sacraments? Sum tyme was no resoun, wan &thorn;e same was bischop and prest. And bi forn &thorn;at presthed was hied, or veriliar filyd cursidly bi &thorn;e world, ilk prest of Crist was callid indifferently prest and bischop, as it semi&thorn; be &thorn;e wordis of Jerom.</P>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="6" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>VI. Iche prest is aldun to preche.</HEAD>
<P>An o&thorn;er is &thorn;is, &thorn;at ilk prest is holdun to preche. &thorn;is haue I seid of &thorn;e wordis of Gregor, Austeyn, and o&thorn;er. And &thorn;is steri&thorn; me to seye &thorn;us, for ilk man is olden to do &thorn;ing &thorn;at Crist enioyni&thorn; him to do. And it semi&thorn; bi witnes of seyntis, &thorn;at Crist enioyni&thorn; ilk prest 
<PB REF="00000095.tif" N="31"> to preche, and &thorn;an he is boundun &thorn;er to. And &thorn;is semi&thorn; bi &thorn;e gospel &thorn;at sei&thorn; &thorn;us. After &thorn;at Crist had ordeynid his apostlis, and<NOTE PLACE="marg">Luc. 10.</NOTE> sent hem to preche; after he assignid seuenty and two disciplis, and sent hem be forn his face, two and two, in to ilk place and cite widir he was to com, and bad hem preche &thorn;e kyndum of God; vpon wilk sei&thorn; an expositor &thorn;us. Crist sent his two and seuenty disciplis, and &yogh;aue power to performe it. And sin it is prouable &thorn;at &thorn;ei were not prests, for &thorn;an had &thorn;ei ben bischopis, and apostlis, but &thorn;ei were dekunis, lowar &thorn;an prestis, as Steuyn, and silk o&thorn;er &thorn;at is redd of in apostlis dedis, it semi&thorn; &thorn;at Crist, sending hem to &thorn;is office, sendi&thorn; in his ordeyning al o&thorn;er heiar, as prestis, to &thorn;e office; to &thorn;e same soundun &thorn;e wordis of &thorn;e prelat ordening dekunnis. Were fore in &thorn;e fourt book of sentence, &thorn;e fowr and twenti distinc|<NOTE PLACE="marg">Mag. sent. li<SUP>o</SUP>. 4. 24 d.</NOTE> coun, &thorn;us is writun; To &thorn;e decoun it perteni&thorn; [to] stond ni&yogh;e &thorn;e prest, and minister to him all &thorn;ings &thorn;at are don in &thorn;o sacraments of Crist, to bere &thorn;e crose, to preche &thorn;e gospel, and &thorn;e pistil; for as &thorn;e olde Testament to &thorn;e redars, so is bedun to dekunnis to prech &thorn;e newe. And &thorn;is same sei&thorn; Seint Ysidor, as it is put in &thorn;e decrees.<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ysidor.</NOTE> For &thorn;i sei&thorn; Seint Gregori, Poule sei&thorn; to Thimo&thorn;e, &thorn;at &thorn;e prest be<NOTE PLACE="marg">Gregor. in past. c. 5. and dt. 43.</NOTE> mi&yogh;ti to exort in al doctrin, and argu hem &thorn;at a&yogh;en seyn &thorn;e fei&thorn;. &thorn;er for is seid bi &thorn;e prophet Malachie, &thorn;e lippis of &thorn;e prest schal<NOTE PLACE="marg">Mal. 2<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> kepe sciens, and men schal ask &thorn;e law of his mow&thorn;e, for he is &thorn;e aungel of &thorn;e Lord of hostis, &thorn;er for &thorn;e Lord monesti&thorn; be &thorn;e prophet Ysaie seing, Crie, cese not, vphauns &thorn;i vois os a trompe. Who<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ysaie 58<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> &thorn;at niy&thorn; to prest hed he taki&thorn; &thorn;e office of a criar, &thorn;at he go criing for &thorn;e goming of &thorn;e iuge &thorn;at ferfulli folowi&thorn;. Werfor &thorn;e prest, going in and out, die&thorn; if he go wi&thorn; out &thorn;e sound of preching. But here sum glosun and seyn, &thorn;at preching is her vnderstonden reding at &thorn;e messe, and &thorn;at Gregori spak &thorn;is of curats; but swelk men be howuen tak hede, &thorn;at bi &thorn;is are not curats excusid &thorn;at prechun not; and it folowi&thorn; not &thorn;er of &thorn;at simple prestis are excusid bi &thorn;is, for he spak to curats, and be &thorn;ei ware &thorn;at &thorn;ei knitt not falsly a wey 
<PB REF="00000096.tif" N="32"> &thorn;e witt fro &thorn;e lecture, and bere fals witnes vpon seynts, and diseyue simple prestis bi &thorn;er fraudis, wening &thorn;us to be excusid; for God sei&thorn; bi Ysaie, &thorn;i fadir &thorn;e first synnid, and &thorn;in enterpretors han<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ysa. 43<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> brokyn &thorn;e lawe a&yogh;enis me. And tak &thorn;ei &yogh;ed how Gregor sei&thorn; to presthod; he sei&thorn; not to cure. And &thorn;ei &thorn;at seyn &thorn;is preching is takun for reding, take &thorn;ei &yogh;ede to preche, for in a langwag vnknowun ilk man and womman mai rede, and mani are for bodun to prech. And if ilk man mai prech it, it were but foly to go to &thorn;e hordres to geit more iarche. And also take &thorn;ey &yogh;ed how to preche; &thorn;e holde Testament was bodun dekunis, we&thorn;er not in tong &thorn;at &thorn;e peple vnderstode; for so&thorn; to preche is in siche maner to a monest good &thorn;ingis, as Crist bad his disciplis do, wan he sent hem to preche, &thorn;er for be &thorn;ei ware &thorn;at &thorn;us wenun to excuse prestis, for Austeyn sei&thorn; &thorn;us, fewe are &thorn;e prestus &thorn;at prechun iustli &thorn;e Word<NOTE PLACE="marg">Austeyn.</NOTE> of God, but many are stille dampnably, sum of vnkunning, &thorn;at refuse to be tau&yogh;t, oi&thorn;er of neligens, &thorn;at despice Goddis Word, but noi&thorn;er &thorn;ei nor &thorn;ei mai be excusid of &thorn;e syn of &thorn;er stilnes; sin &thorn;ei how not to be prests &thorn;at can not preche, ne &thorn;ei to be stille &thorn;at can, &thorn;ow &thorn;ei be not curatis. And &thorn;us sei&thorn; Crisostum, it semi&thorn; &thorn;at<NOTE PLACE="marg">Crisost.</NOTE> God enioni&thorn; to doctors and dekunis &thorn;e minstri of presthed, and of dekunhed, &thorn;at are ri&yogh;tful, and it semi&thorn; &thorn;at men han ordeynid hem &thorn;at are vniust, and not curatis. And so of &thorn;e &thorn;ing issewe is knowun who is ordeynid of God, and who of man; he &thorn;at do&thorn; wel his minstri, &thorn;at semi&thorn; &thorn;at he is ordeynid of God, and he &thorn;at do&thorn; it not wel, is ordeynid of man, &thorn;e wilk so&thorn;li as to God, is nei&thorn;er dekun ne prest. &thorn;erfor sei&thorn; Isidor, kunne &thorn;er prestis Holi Writt,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Isidor.</NOTE> and &thorn;e canouns, and &thorn;at al &thorn;er wark be in preching, and in doc|trin, and edify &thorn;ei alle men, as wel of sciens of &thorn;e fei&thorn; as in dis|ciplyn of dedis, &thorn;erfor &thorn;e prestis, but &thorn;ei make opun al trow&thorn; in &thorn;e peple, &thorn;ei schal &yogh;eue resoun at &thorn;e day of dome; as God sei&thorn; bi &thorn;e prophet, Lo I haue sett &thorn;e a be holdar to &thorn;e hows of Israel, if<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ezech. 3<SUP>o</SUP></NOTE> &thorn;ou sey not to &thorn;e wickid man, &thorn;at he go fro his wickid weies and 
<PB REF="00000097.tif" N="33"> lefe he schal dye in his synnis, and I schal seek his blod of &thorn;in hond. And for so&thorn; prestis schal be dampnid for wickidnes of &thorn;e peple, if &thorn;ei lere hem not wan &thorn;ei are vnkunand, nor snyb hem not wanne &thorn;ei synne. And as it cordi&thorn; to argu &thorn;e synnar, so it falli&thorn; to not do veniaunce to &thorn;e iust man. &THORN;is sei&thorn; Seynt Isedor. And &thorn;us it semi&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;ei are boundun her to vnder &thorn;e peyn of dedly synne and dampning to helle. And for obieccouns and sophims &thorn;at men may mak and obiect, it semi&thorn; to me &thorn;at &thorn;ei are bounde &thorn;us; ilk man taking presthed, he taki&thorn; him mater to mak him holy, body and soule and spirit, and so to be holy and halow o&thorn;er, be en|saumple of lyuing, word of teching, and ministring of sacraments, after &thorn;e sentence of Poule, in &thorn;e ordening of prestis, seyng &thorn;us,<NOTE PLACE="marg">2 Tim. i<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> Wil &thorn;u not tak reclesly &thorn;e grace of God &thorn;at is in &thorn;ee bi &thorn;e putting vp on of my honds. And &thorn;us he sei&thorn; to Titus, For &thorn;is I left &thorn;e at<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ad Titum i<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> Crete, &thorn;at &thorn;u mend &thorn;ingis &thorn;at wantun, and ordeyn bi sy&yogh;t prestis, as I haue ordeynyd &thorn;ee, and disposid to &thorn;e; if ani is man wi&thorn; out wif of synne, hauing fei&thorn;ful sones, not in accusing of lechery, or not soget, for &thorn;e bischop be howui&thorn; be wi&thorn; out crime, as a dis|pensar of God, nor proud, ne wra&thorn;ful, ne &yogh;euin to drink, ne strikar, ne coueytous of foul wynning, but to holde hospital, and to be bening, sobur, just, holy, chast, biclipping &thorn;e fei&thorn;ful word &thorn;at is after doctrin, &thorn;at he be mi&yogh;ti to exort or monest in his doc|trin, and snib hem &thorn;at a&yogh;en seyn &thorn;e so&thorn;e. Also dekunis to be<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Tim. iij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> chast, not dowble tongid, not &yogh;euun to mikil to drink, ne fowlow|ing fowle wynning, hauing &thorn;e priuey witt of &thorn;e fei&thorn; in a pure con|sciens; and first be &thorn;ei prouid, and so, hauing no crime, minister &thorn;ei; be &thorn;ei &thorn;e man of a wife, &thorn;at goueren wel &thorn;er sonis and &thorn;er housis, and &thorn;at ministre&thorn; wel, schal geit him a good decre in mikil trist in &thorn;e fei&thorn; &thorn;at is in Ihu Crist. And be &thorn;u ensaumple of fei&thorn;ful<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Tim. iv<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> men in word, in leuing, in charite, in fei&thorn;, in chastite; take to reding, and to exorting, and to theching, and to be stonding in hem; &thorn;enk &thorn;eis &thorn;ingis oft, be &thorn;u in &thorn;eis &thorn;ings, &thorn;at &thorn;i going for&thorn; be made opun. 
<PB REF="00000098.tif" N="34"> And doing &thorn;eis &thorn;ings, &thorn;u schalt mak &thorn;i seluen sane, and hem &thorn;at herun &thorn;e. And prestis &thorn;at prestun wel be &thorn;ei hade wor&thorn;i dowble<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Tim. v<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> honor, and most &thorn;ei &thorn;at trauelun in word and in dede, teching. &thorn;us it semi&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;ei are bound to hold &thorn;is forme of liue in hemsilue, and ai to be redy to ken o&thorn;er and to minister to hem. And were euer bi oportunite, or conpetent acordauns, to be redi to fil it in dede, wi&thorn; out dispensacoun, and wi&thorn; out excusacoun, but if our Lord Ihu Crist despens wi&thorn; hem, and excuse hem, or for bed hem. For no man sett a no&thorn;er ground &thorn;an it &thorn;at is sett, &thorn;at is Crist Ihu,<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Cor. xi<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> &thorn;at ha&thorn; &thorn;e key of Daui&thorn;, and he closi&thorn;, and &thorn;an no man opuni&thorn;, he<NOTE PLACE="marg">Apoc. iij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> opuni&thorn;, and &thorn;an no man sperri&thorn;, ne&thorn;er is no man wor&thorn;i to opun &thorn;e lasing of his scho; &thorn;at is &thorn;us to vnderstond: as no man is wor&thorn;i to opun &thorn;e priueite of his incarnacoun, ne to fynd &thorn;e resoun of al his warkis, so is no man wor&thorn;i to mak a letter or title of his to go by vnfillid, ne to put more &thorn;er to, ne to draw &thorn;er fro, ne to chaunge it, noi&thorn;er to lowse &thorn;at he byndi&thorn;, ne to bynd &thorn;at he lowsi&thorn;, befor &thorn;at he &yogh;eui&thorn; &thorn;e key, and kenni&thorn; to opun and to steyke; &thorn;erfor tent &thorn;ei so, and here &thorn;ei al &thorn;ing &thorn;at ni&yogh;e&thorn; to presthed, and alle &thorn;at admitten o&thorn;er &thorn;erto, and &thorn;at enforcyn to excuse hem fro dede of preching, and to excuse hem in pride of lif, worldly coueiteis, coueiteis of een, and coueiteis of flesche, tent &thorn;ei to &thorn;eis &thorn;ingis be for seid. And to &thorn;oo &thorn;at God sei&thorn; bi &thorn;e profet, son of<NOTE PLACE="marg">Eze. xliv<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> man, putt to hert, and see wi&thorn; &thorn;in een, and here wi&thorn; &thorn;in heris, alle &thorn;ings &thorn;at I spek to &thorn;e, of al cerimoynis of &thorn;e house of &thorn;e Lord, and of lawis &thorn;er of, and &thorn;u schalt sett &thorn;in hert in &thorn;e weyes of &thorn;e temple, bi al &thorn;e issewis of &thorn;e sanctuari; and &thorn;u schalt sey to &thorn;e house of Israel stering me to wra&thorn;, &thorn;eis &thorn;ings sei&thorn; &thorn;e Lord God; suffici&thorn; to &yogh;ow al &yogh;or felonies hous of Israel; for &thorn;at he bring in alien sonis vncircumsicid in hert, and vncircumsicid in flesch, &thorn;at &thorn;ei be in my sanctuari, and fyle myn house, and &yogh;e offer my lofis, mi gres, and my blod; my couanant &yogh;e dissoluen in al &yogh;or felonyes, and han not kepid &thorn;e biddings of mi sanctuari, and han put kepars 
<PB REF="00000099.tif" N="35"> of my sanctuari obseruaunce to &yogh;or silf; &thorn;eis &thorn;ings sei&thorn; &thorn;e Lord God, Ilk alien kynd and vncircumsisid in hert, and vncircumsisid in flesch, schal not go in to my sanctuari, ilk alien son &thorn;at is in medil of &thorn;e hous of Israels sonis. But and &thorn;e leuits, &thorn;at han gon a wey fro me in error of &thorn;e sonis of Israel, and ha&thorn; errid fro me after &thorn;er idols, and ha&thorn; born &thorn;er wickidnes, &thorn;ei schal be in my sanctuari huschers, and portars of &thorn;e &yogh;atis of &thorn;e house, and minis|tres of &thorn;e hous; &thorn;ei schal sle &thorn;e bernt offrings and offrings of vic|tories of &thorn;e peple, and &thorn;ei schal stond in &thorn;er si&yogh;t &thorn;at &thorn;ei minister to hem; for &thorn;i &thorn;at &thorn;ei ministred to hem [in] &thorn;e si&yogh;t of &thorn;er idols, &thorn;ei are mad in &thorn;e house of Israel in to offens of wickidnesse, aftir I haue liftid vp my hand vp on hem, sei&thorn; &thorn;e Lord God, and &thorn;ei schal bere &thorn;er wickidnes, and schal not ni&yogh;e to me, &thorn;at &thorn;ei vse presthed to me, ne nye to al my sanctuari, bi &thorn;e sancta sanctorum, but &thorn;ei schal bere her confusioun, and her felonyes &thorn;at &thorn;ei haue done; and I schal &yogh;eue hem portars of &thorn;e hous of Iuda, and al ministery &thorn;er of, and al &thorn;ings &thorn;at ben don &thorn;er in. But &thorn;e prestis and &thorn;e leuits, sonis of Sadok, &thorn;at han kepit &thorn;e cerymonis of my sanctuari, wan &thorn;e sonis of Israel errid fro me, &thorn;ei schal ni&yogh;e to me, &thorn;at &thorn;ei minister to me, and stond in my si&yogh;t, &thorn;at &thorn;ei offre my grece to me, and my blod, sei&thorn; &thorn;e Lord God. &THORN;ei schal go in to my sanctuari, and &thorn;ei schal to mi bord ni&yogh;e, &thorn;at &thorn;ei minister to me and kepe mi cery|moynis. Certeynli &thorn;o hous of God her is tane &thorn;e congregacoun<NOTE PLACE="marg">Moral.</NOTE> of fei&thorn;ful men, in onhed of spirit wi&thorn; Crist, &thorn;at is &thorn;e general kirk, and gostly body of Crist, &thorn;at is foundid in fei&thorn;, reisid in hope of lif, and couerid wi&thorn; charite, and ful mad in good werkis; &thorn;at ha&thorn; for &thorn;e ground, &thorn;e fei&thorn; of Crist, &thorn;at is &thorn;e ston vp on wilk &thorn;e kirk is groundid; hope for &thorn;e fowre walls, hoping al iuel to turne to joy to seynts, be vertu of Crists pascoun, and al &thorn;ings to cum in to blis, be vertu of &thorn;e first geyting of Crist to vs al &thorn;ing a boue us frutfully, and to vse al &thorn;ing be ne&thorn; man blessidly; of &thorn;e wilk groui&thorn; charite heling al &thorn;e bigging. To &thorn;e bigging of &thorn;is &thorn;e prest 
<PB REF="00000100.tif" N="36"> howi&thorn; to trauel, and to be bisi, to ding doun of &thorn;e contrari; &thorn;e cerymoynis and &thorn;e lawis of &thorn;is hous are &thorn;e biddingis and &thorn;e conseyl of &thorn;e gospel, &yogh;euun be Crist and his Apostls, and ensaumplied be life, to &thorn;e wilk &thorn;e prest schuld put to &thorn;e hert, &thorn;at is &thorn;e streng&thorn; of his luf, and wi&thorn; &thorn;e eeris and een of his hert, he schuld vnderstond hem, and kepe hem in himsilf, and ken &thorn;e peple to kepe al &thorn;ingis &thorn;at Crist ha&thorn; comoundid. But alien sonis vncircumsicid in hert and flesch, are &thorn;ei &thorn;at serue not Crist in spirit, ne in fleschly dedis gostly. For &thorn;ei enter not to &thorn;e lif bi &thorn;e maner of Crist in meknes, pouert, paciens, and labour, and o&thorn;er vertuus dedis: but &thorn;ei enter for to lif in prid of &thorn;e world, and worldly riches, and lustis of &thorn;e flesch, and &thorn;erfor &thorn;ey are alien, and wi&thorn; swilk cursidnes &thorn;ei polewt &thorn;e hous, for &thorn;ei leede mani in to synne, and sterun God in to wra&thorn;, and causun &thorn;at God is holdun vniust. And &thorn;us &thorn;ei vndo &thorn;e couenaunt; wil &thorn;ei kepe not &thorn;e office of presthed in &thorn;at maner &thorn;at Crist bad, but &thorn;ey putt &thorn;e kepars of &thorn;e obseruaunce to hemsilf. Wen &thorn;ei welun &thorn;at &thorn;ei kepe more specialy &thorn;e &thorn;ings, and &thorn;e biddingis enioynid of men, and streytar &thorn;an biddingis and &thorn;ingis enioynid of God; and namly, wan &thorn;ey putt kepars to gedre temporal &thorn;ings to hem, after &thorn;er decre, [rather] &thorn;an to gedre souls to Ihu Crist. But here wat folowi&thorn;. Sich alien and vncircumsisid schal not enter in to &thorn;e sanctuary, for as &thorn;e Lord forbedi&thorn; swilk to be ministris, so he stori&thorn; hem her &thorn;at &thorn;ei schal not accept grace, wil &thorn;ei are swilk, ne schal not minister grace to &thorn;e puple, but swilk &thorn;at han gon a wey fro God in to error and ignoraunce, and swilk idolatrie, worschiping man a&yogh;en Goddis bidding, and doing o&thorn;er iuel: &thorn;ei schal bere &thorn;er wickidnes, as &thorn;ei han synnid, so schal &thorn;ei be punischid, and &thorn;ei schal be huscheris and portars; for as &thorn;ei opunid synnis to &thorn;e peple and brout hem ine, so schal &thorn;ei enduce hem in to peyn, and &thorn;us schal &thorn;ei scle &thorn;e brent offrendis. But prestis and leuits, &thorn;e sonis of Sadok, &thorn;at han kepid &thorn;e cerymoynis of &thorn;e sanctuari, &thorn;ei schal ni&yogh;e to minister to me; but swilk be 
<PB REF="00000101.tif" N="37"> prestis of Crist, &thorn;at entren be him in spirit, soule, and dede, and kennen &thorn;e peple to kepe his comaundments, and schal ni&yogh;e in to grace, and at &thorn;e last in to ioy. And as &thorn;ei opunid &thorn;e wey of trow&thorn; to &thorn;e peple, so schal &thorn;ei bring hem to ioi, syne and wrechednes slayn. &THORN;us we vnderstond; and wan &thorn;is comi&thorn; &thorn;at is now seid, &thorn;an schal we wit it; &thorn;erfor schuld bischopis dred to ordeyn vnwis prestis, and ioi to seek &thorn;e good, for Jerom sei&thorn;, &thorn;at &thorn;e vnwise sone<NOTE PLACE="marg">Jerom.</NOTE> is schemschip to &thorn;e modir, and &thorn;e wise sone glori of &thorn;e fadir; &thorn;erfor glory &thorn;e bischop, wan he ha&thorn; chosun wise prestis, for &thorn;e cause of ruyn of &thorn;o peple are iuil prestis.</P>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="7" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>VII. The messe of a fornicary.</HEAD>
<P>An o&thorn;er is &thorn;is, If ani &yogh;ere &thorn;e messe of a prest &thorn;at leui&thorn; in lechery, and knowi&thorn; him to be swilk, [he] synni&thorn; dedely. To &thorn;is I sey &thorn;us; I rehersid oft &thorn;e word of seynt Poule, &thorn;at forbedi&thorn; us to<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Cor. vi<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> tak meit or comyn wi&thorn; &thorn;eis manslears, for sworn men, cursars, drunksum men, rauenors, fornicarers, and swilk o&thorn;er; for &thorn;ey &thorn;at do swilk &thorn;ings, schal not haue &thorn;e kyndum of God, for &thorn;ei are wor&thorn;i &thorn;e de&thorn;; not onli &thorn;ei &thorn;at done, but and &thorn;ei &thorn;at consentun wi&thorn; &thorn;e doars, or &thorn;ei &thorn;at wirkun wi&thorn;, or defendun, or &yogh;euen conseyl or confort, and &thorn;at autoryse it, ne helpun not to a mend, ne reproue it not, as &thorn;ei schuld. Al so I rehersid &thorn;e decre of &thorn;e kirk, bidding<NOTE PLACE="marg">Decre.</NOTE> &thorn;at no man here &thorn;e messe of &thorn;e prest &thorn;at he wot dowtles ha&thorn; a concubyn, or a womman suspect preueyli browt vndre. &THORN;an seyd ani &thorn;us to me, But wat if I wot not him swilk, what syn haue I &thorn;an? I answerid, frend perchauns &thorn;u hawtist to wete and enquire; wan &thorn;u dost not, how wilt &thorn;u be excusid? And to &thorn;is I led him be sensible ensaumple. And wan he tok it heuily, and wold not vnderstond, I &yogh;af him &thorn;is ensaumple; &yogh;if &thorn;u cum til a frend, and he sett rawe meyt be for &thorn;e, and sey it is rostod i now, or sodyn, if &thorn;u heyt it, and tak &thorn;i de&thorn;, how art &thorn;u &thorn;an not dede? And &thorn;us it semi&thorn; in mani casis, it mai be susteynid &thorn;at it is so&thorn;, &thorn;ow it be not in ilk case. Namli sin Crist sei&thorn;, He &thorn;at knowi&thorn; his lordis<NOTE PLACE="marg">Luc. xii<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> wille, and maad him not redy to do &thorn;er after, schal be dongun wi&thorn; 
<PB REF="00000102.tif" N="38"> mani dingings, and he &thorn;at cnowi&thorn; not, and dede &thorn;ings wor&thorn;i betings, schal be dongun wi&thorn; few dingings. And as Austeyn sei&thorn;, Not ilk<NOTE PLACE="marg">Austeyn.</NOTE> vnkuning schal be excusid of synne, but he mai be excusid &thorn;at fond not wat for to lere. But he mai not be excusid &thorn;at fond what he mi&yogh;t lere, and &yogh;af not wark &thorn;er to; and &thorn;erfor we pray God for &yogh;eue vs our ignoraunce. And &thorn;er for men schuld not tak &thorn;is word ouer egirly, &thorn;er for prestis flee fornicacioun, not onli for hemsilf, but also for all o&thorn;er, &thorn;at &thorn;ei make hem not to synne dedly; for &thorn;e gretnes of &thorn;e synne in prestis, ouer &thorn;e synne in o&thorn;er men, is schewid be many resouns; and for it is mikil greuowsare &thorn;an simple fornicacoun bi thwex an onlepy man, and an onlepi womman, and it is grettar &thorn;an spouse brokun of seculer men bodily, and neuer &thorn;e lese bo&thorn; thwo are dedly synne. And &thorn;at it be &thorn;e more semi&thorn; bi &thorn;is; for ai &thorn;e heiar degre, &thorn;e sarrar is &thorn;e falle, but presthed is heiar degre &thorn;an bodili matrimoyn, and &thorn;us &thorn;e prest in doing fornicacoun do&thorn; sacrile, and breki&thorn; his wow; for bi &thorn;e vertu of his degre, he made &thorn;e vow of chastite. Also &thorn;e gretnes of &thorn;is synne is schewid bi &thorn;e lawis and peynis &thorn;at are made &thorn;er a&yogh;en; for &thorn;us is writun in &thorn;e decreis, &THORN;e prest or dekun &thorn;at is tan in fornicacoun, &thorn;eft, or<NOTE PLACE="marg">Decreis,</NOTE> mansleyng, or forswering, be he deposid. And eft, If ani are<NOTE PLACE="marg">Dist. 81.</NOTE> prestis, dekunis, or sodekunis, &thorn;at li&thorn; in &thorn;e sin of fornicacoun, we<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ibid. c. si qui.</NOTE> forbede him in almi&yogh;ti Goddis behalue, and bi autorite of Peter and Poule, &thorn;e entre of &thorn;e kirk, til &thorn;ey repent and amende; and if &thorn;ei last in &thorn;er synne, &thorn;at noon of &yogh;ow presewme to here &thorn;er office, for &thorn;er blessing is turnid in to cursing, and &thorn;er prayor in to synne; as God sei&thorn; bi &thorn;e profi&yogh;t, I schal curse to &yogh;our blessing; and who<NOTE PLACE="marg">Mal. ij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> so wil not obey to &thorn;is helsum bidding, he synni&thorn; in &thorn;e synne of ydolatrie, as Samuel witnessi&thorn;, and seynt Gregor enformi&thorn;;<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Reg. xv<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> synne of wichcraft is to not obey, and &thorn;e felowny of ydolatrie to<NOTE PLACE="marg">Gregor.</NOTE> not wel assent. And eft &thorn;us, Bidding we comaund, &thorn;at no man<NOTE PLACE="marg">Dist. 32.</NOTE> here &thorn;e messe of &thorn;at prest &thorn;at he wot dowtles &thorn;at ha&thorn; a concubyn, or a womman suspect brout in vndir. Werfor in &thorn;e holy seyn is 
<PB REF="00000103.tif" N="39"> ordeynid &thorn;is capitul, vnder &thorn;e peyn; seying: If ani of prestis, dekunis, or sodekunis, after &thorn;e ordinaunce of &thorn;e good memorie of our predecessor seynt Leoun, and pope Nicol, of &thorn;e chastite of clerk, hold concubyn opunly, or leui&thorn; not heer &thorn;at he holdi&thorn;; vpon almi&yogh;ti Goddis half, and bi autorite of Peter and Poule, princis of postlis, we bid him, and a&yogh;en sey him, &thorn;at [he] syng no messe, ne rede no gospel, ne pistil, at &thorn;e messe, ne dwel not wi&thorn; prestis, ne tak no part of &thorn;e kirk. And as &thorn;e decretals declarun, in &thorn;re maneris<NOTE PLACE="marg">Decretals.</NOTE> is &thorn;is callid notory; Oi&thorn;er wat it is lawfuly conuictid bi witnesses, or bi his oune cnowleching, or ellis bi &thorn;e dede &thorn;at mai not be weypid a wey, as &thorn;e dwelling to gidre of &thorn;e man and &thorn;e womman, and &thorn;e bringing for&thorn; of barnis. And eft &thorn;e decre sei&thorn;, If ani bischop, or<NOTE PLACE="marg">Decre.</NOTE> ani of prestis, or dekunis, consent to fornicacoun, or to crime of incest in his parische, for price or prayour, or amendi&thorn; not &thorn;at is done bi &thorn;e autorite of his office, be he suspendid. And eft writi&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="marg">Decretal.</NOTE> &thorn;e pope to &thorn;e bischop, We bid to &thorn;i bro&thorn;erhed, &thorn;at &thorn;u steer bisili &thorn;e clerkis of &thorn;i jurisdiccoun, &thorn;at are wi&thorn; in &thorn;e ordre of sodeken, or a boue, &thorn;at han concubins, &thorn;at &thorn;ei moue hem fro hem, and reseyue hem no more a&yogh;en; and if &thorn;ei wernid hold hem stille, suspend hem fro office; and &thorn;ei suspendid if &thorn;ei wel dwel stille in &thorn;er iuel, do &thorn;ey bisines to moue hem fro office for euer. And as &thorn;e doctor sei&thorn;,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Doctor.</NOTE> &THORN;is schal be heuen wi&thorn; deposing. And forso&thorn; sei&thorn; the pope, We wel &thorn;at &thorn;e bischops &thorn;at are necligent in &thorn;is, vndir go &thorn;e same peyn. And eft &thorn;e decre biddi&thorn;, Receyui&thorn; no wey &thorn;e office of him &thorn;at &yogh;ee<NOTE PLACE="marg">Decre.</NOTE> wot lie&thorn; in synne of fornicacoun, and of symonye, and als mikil as &yogh;ee mai, forbedi&thorn; swilk fro holi ministres; for it is nedeful, for &thorn;ow &thorn;e sacraments han &thorn;e dignite of &thorn;er vertu, neuer&thorn;eles &thorn;ey noy &thorn;us mikil bo&thorn; to &thorn;e ministring, and to &thorn;e receyuing hem, a&yogh;en &thorn;e ordi|naunce, &thorn;at bo&thorn; &thorn;e ministring and to [? &thorn;e] receyuer vnwor&thorn;ily are wi&thorn; hem verrey idolatrers; &thorn;er for sacraments are forbidun to be reyciuid of &thorn;e handis of such prestis, &thorn;at wan such prestis see hem dispicid of &thorn;e peple, &thorn;ei be &thorn;e licliare callid to penaunce, and &thorn;us 
<PB REF="00000104.tif" N="40"> seyn we to our prestis bi &thorn;eis witnes, and o&thorn;er moo do &thorn;us oft idolatrie, and are vnfei&thorn;ful, and &thorn;us in mani o&thorn;er crimes, what wondir if we be wounded in ilk sid, in many peynful wrechidnes.</P>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="8" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>VIII. To curse a man that is not cursid.</HEAD>
<P>A no&thorn;er poynt putt is &thorn;is: he &thorn;at cursi&thorn; ani man, or denounci&thorn; him cursid, wan he is not cursid, he breki&thorn; Goddis binding, beri&thorn; fals witnes a&yogh;en his ne&yogh;bore. &THORN;is schewi&thorn; it self so&thorn;, and o&thorn;er resouns prouun it wele. And for so&thorn;, as he li&yogh;&thorn; &thorn;at sei&thorn; a&yogh;en mend, as wan he wot how a &thorn;ing is if he denay and afferm in &thorn;e contrari; or ells he &thorn;at presumi&thorn; and weni&thorn; to wete verily of a &thorn;ing, and properli denai&thorn; &thorn;at, and affermi&thorn; &thorn;e contrari, wening him to li&yogh;e in &thorn;is, so li&yogh;&thorn; he &thorn;at chargid to afferm of a &thorn;ing os it is aftur witing, and he affermi&thorn; a&yogh;en &thorn;e so&thorn;e, and a &thorn;ing os it is, for in &thorn;is he sei&thorn; a&yogh;en God, and so a&yogh;en his mynde; for &thorn;e trou&thorn; of his mynd affermi&thorn; not to him &thorn;e &thorn;ing to be but os it is; for &thorn;e to&thorn;er is fals presumpcoun. And &thorn;us wan he affermi&thorn; him to wite &thorn;ing &thorn;at he wot not, he affermi&thorn; a&yogh;en his mynd, and namly wan &thorn;e &thorn;ing is nowt, for he mai not wet but &thorn;ing &thorn;at is, for if he wene to wit &thorn;ing &thorn;at is not, &thorn;at is but fals presumcoun; and for &thorn;is sei&thorn; Crist in sentence, if I denoy &thorn;is &thorn;at is, I schuld be lik &yogh;ow a lier. On &thorn;is schuld here witnes hang &thorn;at &thorn;ei witnes not a&yogh;ens God, nor be not disseyuid hemsilf, nor disseyue non o&thorn;er men.</P>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="9" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>IX. Of pouerte.</HEAD>
<P>&THORN;is is a no&thorn;er: it is a taking of dampnacoun &thorn;at a man lede his lif in pouert. Certs &thorn;is is contrari to &thorn;is, &thorn;at noon is Cristis dis|ciple but if he forsak al &thorn;ing for him. Alas he &thorn;at putti&thorn; for&thorn; &thorn;is &thorn;ing noi&thorn;er dredi&thorn; ne schami&thorn; to lette, ne sclaunder o&thorn;er men. Alas &thorn;at oi&thorn;er throwi&thorn; his lesings a&yogh;en &thorn;e bidding of God, wer to bring &thorn;ei for&thorn; suche &thorn;ings, si&thorn; Crist ledde his bodili lyfe in most heyest pouert, as diuers doctors declaren. And he was riche, he was mad nedy for vs, pore and helples, as &thorn;e psalm sei&thorn; on him,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Psal. xxxix<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> &thorn;at we bi his pouert schuld be mad riche. Pore he was, for he had<NOTE PLACE="marg">2 Cor. viii<SUP>o</SUP>. Matt. viii<SUP>o</SUP>. Jame. ii<SUP>o</SUP>. Matt. v<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> not were to hied his heuid, and he chase &thorn;e pore in &thorn;is world, &thorn;at are riche in &thorn;e fei&thorn;, as Jame sei&thorn;. And &thorn;e pore he blessid, as &thorn;e 
<PB REF="00000105.tif" N="41"> gospel sei&thorn;, and his apostlis led &thorn;e porest lif; and &thorn;us he reprouid &thorn;e rych, and seid many iuel to cum to hem, and neuerles to sum pouert is not only a &thorn;ing of saluacoun, but also of dampnacoun. &THORN;erfor hem see pore men &thorn;at &thorn;ei grucche not a&yogh;en God, but be glad of &thorn;er pornes; for &thorn;us sei&thorn; &thorn;e psalm, Lord, good is to me for &thorn;u<NOTE PLACE="marg">Psal. cxviii<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> hast lowid me, &thorn;at I lere &thorn;i ri&yogh;twisnes. And ilk man see &thorn;at he bring not him self synfully in to pouert, nor bide not synfully &thorn;er in. And se hem religious, &thorn;at &thorn;ei feyn not falsly pouert, nor mak &thorn;ei not heyet voyd, &thorn;at &thorn;ei purchas hem not peyn but meed. And see &thorn;ei &thorn;at &thorn;ei oblesche no man to &thorn;er maner of pouert, but &thorn;at God ha&thorn; callid &thorn;er to. And alle prelats and prestis vse &thorn;ei hemsilf in wat pouert &thorn;ei schuld folow Crist; for &thorn;ei schuld folow Crist as holi doctors declaren, bo&thorn; Jerom, Ambrose, and o&thorn;er. And for &thorn;e clerar declaring of &thorn;is mater we schal vnderstond &thorn;at pouert is a forme, a &thorn;ing &thorn;at is seid pore, or litil, or haldun litil in sum maner. And &thorn;us sum are gostly pore, and sum bodily; sum vertuously, and sum vicously, or synfully; and sum peynfully; and ilk on of hem in syndry degrees and maners. Gostly pouert is sum tyme wan a &thorn;ing ha&thorn; litil of sum spirit; and &thorn;us was Crist most pore, for he had lest of &thorn;e spirit of prid, or o&thorn;er sinful spirits, &yogh;he lesse &thorn;an euer had ani o&thorn;er man; for al had sum synne but he; and lest he coueited of &thorn;is world, bo&thorn; of hienes of lif, coueitise of flesche, lest of lordschep, lest of honour worldly, or worldly serueyse. And litil he tuk or coueytid of &thorn;is worlds goodis, or worldly seruice, for he tuk of hem but in comyn, as &thorn;ei weren holden to do seruice to him, in &thorn;e performing of &thorn;e wark &thorn;at God &yogh;aue him to do. But and wan men wold haue reeft him to haue maad him kyng, he fled it; and ouer &thorn;is he porid him self ouer alle o&thorn;er; more alle o&thorn;er mi&yogh;t for taking hede to his kynd and degre &thorn;at he is of, and to traueyl &thorn;at he toke, and &thorn;e seruice &thorn;at he dede, and to &thorn;e sorow &thorn;at he &thorn;olid. Was &thorn;er neuer creature so pore, ne &thorn;at porid him so mich; for ouer hem alle he chesid to be maad &thorn;e 
<PB REF="00000106.tif" N="42"> lowist, as it semi&thorn; to him &thorn;at beholdi&thorn;. And as be titil of &thorn;is world, and of worlds lawe, he was moost pore, for he cleymyd no &thorn;ing be &thorn;at titil, nor no &thorn;ing to be proper to him, ne wold he not be iuge in &thorn;er &thorn;ings, nor wan men wold not &yogh;eue him, he sowt no veniaunce vp on hem, but went his wey to o&thorn;er place. And &thorn;is techi&thorn; his pouert. And his pouert was bi &thorn;is mikil &thorn;e more, as he is &thorn;e richist &thorn;ing &thorn;at mai be, and grattist Lord; for his is God, &thorn;at is al riches; and in him he is riche gostly in mercy, ri&yogh;twisnes, and pees, power, science, and al gostly &thorn;ingis. And rich is seid, as he &thorn;at chefly ha&thorn; a &thorn;ing; and Crist is rich, for he ha&thorn; chefly and richli alle &thorn;ingis, and gouerni&thorn;, and ledi&thorn; ouer alle o&thorn;er creaturis. And bi &thorn;is we mai see, how alle &thorn;ings are his most properly; and to holdyn of him, and bi his lawe, and his seruice to be don to him &thorn;er for. And bi &thorn;e state of innocence he is verray Lord, for man was maad to lord in alle creaturis, and forfetid not &thorn;at wyche synni&thorn; not; and Crist kepid ai &thorn;at state, so he had titil to be Lord; and bi &thorn;us mikil ouer Adam, as God is aboue man. And &thorn;us is opun, how Crist is at onis bo&thorn; richist and porist. And for &thorn;is sei&thorn; doctors, &thorn;at to defend &thorn;e contrary pertinatly is heresy, contrary to &thorn;e fei&thorn;. And &thorn;us he tau&yogh;t his disciplis, to flee synful pouert, and to folow him in medful pouert; forbad hem to flee prid, and al fals coueyteis, and veyn glory, and to be mek and suget, and seruiciable, obedient and buxum to ilk man, and to hold hem paied of fode and helyng, and bisily to labor &thorn;er fore; and &thorn;ole deseyce of body in wantyng, and taking a wey, wi&thorn; out ani euynes, or sekeng to do veniaunce a&yogh;en; and who &thorn;at wold be &thorn;e more, to be minister and seruaunt to alle, and nowt glad to mikil of &thorn;er power, or witte, or o&thorn;er &thorn;ings, but glad in &thorn;is, if God haue chosun hem to grace, and &yogh;eue &thorn;e &thorn;ank til him for alle &thorn;ingis. &THORN;us he tawt hem to do, and fle prid, and o&thorn;er synnes, &thorn;at maken man pore synfully; to ocupie o&thorn;er mennis &thorn;ingis synfully, and &thorn;us to be rich, and falsly holde ryches. And so many wyse to renne 
<PB REF="00000107.tif" N="43"> in to &thorn;e wrat of God. And &thorn;us doctors declaren &thorn;e apostols so louid Crist in heyest pouert; and Jerom and o&thorn;er seynts kennun how &thorn;at prestis now schuld folow Crist in pouert. &THORN;us sei&thorn; Jerom,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Jerom.</NOTE> It be howui&thorn; vs clerks to not mishews &thorn;e sygnes of our cleregye, for alle &thorn;e tokenis of clerks, crien and presenten vertewes to be in hem; &thorn;e croun crie&thorn; pouerte; &thorn;e clo&thorn;ing honeste of soule; &thorn;e state purte; &thorn;e honoring, chastite; &thorn;e professioun, religioun; &thorn;e office, deuocoun; &thorn;e stody, contemplacoun. And &thorn;erfor but if we schyn in &thorn;eis vertues, &thorn;e croun lie&thorn;, &thorn;e clo&thorn;ing, &thorn;e honoring, &thorn;e professioun, &thorn;e office, &thorn;e stody, &thorn;e contemplacoun. And &thorn;er for be &thorn;eis we are but peyntid clerks and lied clerkis. And if God schal tyne alle &thorn;oo &thorn;at spek lesyng, and &thorn;at are lesing, and not only hare clerks dampnid, for &thorn;ei spek lesing, but also for &thorn;ei luf it moost, and putten hemsilf for it to &thorn;e de&thorn;. And eft, &thorn;e clerk &thorn;at serui&thorn; to Crists kirke, first schuld interpret &thorn;e calling of his nam, and enforce to be &thorn;at he is seid; for a clerk in our speche is seid sort, and &thorn;er for are men seid clerkis, for &thorn;ei are of &thorn;e Lordis sort, or for &thorn;e Lord is &thorn;er part; and for he is &thorn;e Lordis part, or ha&thorn; &thorn;e Lord his part, he haut to haue him silk &thorn;at he haue &thorn;e Lord, and be had of &thorn;e Lord. He &thorn;at ha&thorn; &thorn;e Lord, and is had of &thorn;e Lord, and sei&thorn; wi&thorn; &thorn;e prophet, Mi part &thorn;e Lord, may no &thorn;ing haue wi&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="marg">Psal. xv<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> out &thorn;e Lord; &thorn;at if he haue ani &thorn;ing bi syd &thorn;e Lord, &thorn;e Lord schal not be his part; as if he haue gold, or siluer, or diuerse instru|ments, or possessouns, wi&thorn; &thorn;er parts, &thorn;e Lord denaie&thorn; not to be his part. If I am &thorn;e part of &thorn;e Lord, sei&thorn; Jero, and a litil cord of his heritage, I take not part wi&thorn; o&thorn;er linagis, but, as a decoun and prest, I life on ti&thorn;is, seruing &thorn;e auter, I am susteynd of offryng of &thorn;e auter; and fode and heling hauing, wi&thorn; hem I schal be content,<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Tim. vi<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> and nakyd I schal folowe &thorn;e nakid cros. And Bernard sei&thorn;, It is<NOTE PLACE="marg">Bernard.</NOTE> iust &thorn;at he &thorn;at serui&thorn; &thorn;e auter lif &thorn;er of, noi&thorn;er to do lechery ne prid, nor be richid, noi&thorn;er in clerked of pore to be maad riche, ne gloriouse of &thorn;e vnnoble, big not to him of &thorn;e goodis of &thorn;e kirk 
<PB REF="00000108.tif" N="44"> large palayce, nor gedre not baggis to gidre, nor wast not &thorn;e goodis in vanite, nor in superfluite, bere him not hi&yogh;e of &thorn;e facultees of &thorn;e kirk, nor gif not to wenddingis his coseynis nor his childre. It is grauntid to &thorn;e if &thorn;u serue wel &thorn;e auter to lif &thorn;er of, not to do lechery, nor to be gilt bridils, peyntid sadels, ne siluern sporis, nor perpulid aray, ffor so&thorn; wat &thorn;u holdist to &thorn;e of &thorn;e auter ouer necesary liflod and simple aray, it is not &thorn;in, it is &thorn;eft and sacrilege. &THORN;is sei&thorn; he.</P>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="10" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>X. Of fasting.</HEAD>
<P>An o&thorn;er poynt putt is &thorn;is: Fastingis are not necesary, wil man absteni&thorn; him fro o&thorn;er synne. And as to &thorn;is I sey &thorn;us, &thorn;at fasting generaly is not onli in forbering of meit and drink, but in forbering of iuel, and al iuel spite, and in doing of good dedis. &THORN;is semi&thorn; &thorn;us bi &thorn;e scripture; for &thorn;us sei&thorn; &thorn;e prophet, Halow &yogh;or<NOTE PLACE="marg">Joel ii<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> fasting. Wat is it, sei&thorn; Gregory, to halow fasting, but to schew<NOTE PLACE="marg">Gregory.</NOTE> due or wor&thorn;i abstinens of flesch, wi&thorn; o&thorn;er good verteuis ioined &thorn;er to; do a wey prid, wra&thorn;, strif, and o&thorn;er vices; for in veyn &thorn;u foilist &thorn;i flesch wi&thorn; abstinens, if &thorn;i soule be not refreynid fro synnis. And as sum fastingis are but of ordinaunce of &thorn;e lawe, so bi &thorn;e lawe are mani excusid &thorn;er of; as wymmen wi&thorn; childe, and waxit folk, wold, and &yogh;ong, sek, and feble. And &thorn;e pore are excusid bi &thorn;e lawe. And neuer&thorn;eles fasting is mikil profitable bo&thorn; to grace and to blis; for &thorn;us we sey to God, by bodyli fasting &thorn;u berist doun vices, liftist up &thorn;e mynd, and &yogh;efyst vertu and medis. And eft &thorn;us, &thorn;e clere fairnes of fasting is schewid to &thorn;e world heuenly, &thorn;at Crist, autor of al &thorn;ing, abstening richid. By &thorn;is Moyses, dere to God, was makid &yogh;euar of &thorn;e lawe; &thorn;is liftid up Hely bi &thorn;e aire in a chare of fire; for &thorn;is Daniel, ouercomer of lyowns, saw misteris of priui &thorn;ingis; bi &thorn;is Ion, &thorn;e inward frend of &thorn;e Spows, was clere; &thorn;ise are opun in &thorn;e stories. God graunt in vs to folow &thorn;eis ensaum|plis of abstinence.</P>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="11" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XI. Of horis.</HEAD>
<P>An o&thorn;er poynt putt is &thorn;is, &thorn;at &thorn;e prest is not holden to his horis canoni&yogh;id, not but if he be to syng. To &thorn;is I answere &thorn;us, I denoy 
<PB REF="00000109.tif" N="45"> me not to haue seid &thorn;is, for perel falling in forme of lawe; for if it were witnessid a&yogh;enis me, &thorn;of it wer fals, if I denoyed, I schuld be condempnid as gilty. Ne I graunt not &thorn;at I seyd it, &thorn;at I lie not on mysilf, for I wot not &thorn;at I seid it, and mannis mynd is sclendre. If I haue fautid, I aske for&yogh;eunes, and I wel mend. But o &thorn;ing I wot wel, if prestis are bounde to &thorn;er horis bi &thorn;e lawe &thorn;at hem silf han maad, &thorn;ei howen be bound be &thorn;e charge &thorn;at Crist ha&thorn; &yogh;euen hem. And if &thorn;ei haue streit conscience to faile in &thorn;is &thorn;at hemself ha&thorn; bound hem to, &thorn;ei schuld haue mikil more to faile in &thorn;is &thorn;at Crist ha&thorn; bound hem to, if &thorn;ei lofid and trostid him aboue &thorn;e wark of &thorn;er hondis. But if &thorn;ei haue bounden hemself, &thorn;er as he maad hem free, and setten mikil bi &thorn;er oun tradicouns, and litil bi his, and puttyn his bidding to for&thorn;fil &thorn;er, and folowen wickid coueitis and o&thorn;er iuel, &thorn;an schal &thorn;is be verified in hem &thorn;at Crist sei&thorn; in his gospel, &THORN;e Holi Goost wan he comi&thorn; schal find &thorn;is world<NOTE PLACE="marg">Joh. xvj<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> of dome; and eft, Whi brek &yogh;e &thorn;e biddings of God, to kepe &yogh;or own tradicouns? ypocritis, wel is prophecied of &yogh;ow, &thorn;is peple honori&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="marg">Mat. xv<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> me wi&thorn; &thorn;er lippis, but &thorn;er hert is far fro me. In veyn &thorn;ei honor me, teching &thorn;e biddings and &thorn;e maundments of men; leuing &thorn;e biddingis of God, for to kepe &thorn;er oune tradicouns. And eft, Wo wor&thorn; &yogh;ow &thorn;at ti&yogh;en mynt, aneis, and comyn, and ilke herbe, and leuen &thorn;e sadder &thorn;ings of &thorn;e lawe, dome, fei&thorn;, and mercy; &thorn;eis &thorn;ings howen to be done, and &thorn;oo not be left. Blind foolis, clensing for&thorn; &thorn;e knatt, but swelowyng &thorn;e camely. And for so&thorn;, as Ambros<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ambros.</NOTE> sei&thorn;, Till &thorn;u lefe &thorn;is &thorn;at &thorn;u art bodun bi &thorn;o bidding of Crist, what &thorn;ing &thorn;at &thorn;u werkyst is vn&thorn;ankful to &thorn;e Holi Goost. And mani prestis in &thorn;er horis byddyn hem self Goddis curse, for &thorn;us &thorn;ei sey, Lord, &thorn;u hast blamid &thorn;e prowd, cursid bi &thorn;ei &thorn;at bowen doun fro &thorn;i<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ps. cxviii<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> biddings.</P>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="12" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XII. Sa|crament of the Auter.</HEAD>
<P>An o&thorn;er poynt is putt &thorn;us; in &thorn;e sacrament of &thorn;e auter, aftir &thorn;e consecracoun, dwelly&thorn; &thorn;e substaunce of &thorn;e brede. And &thorn;is is so&thorn;e, for &thorn;e body of Crist [which] is &thorn;e bred &thorn;at he &yogh;af for &thorn;e lif of &thorn;e 
<PB REF="00000110.tif" N="46"> world dwelli&thorn; &thorn;er ine, and &thorn;erfor &thorn;is substaunce of bred dwelli&thorn; &thorn;er ine. And in &thorn;is mater I remembre &thorn;at I haue spokyn and rehersid &thorn;e wordis of &thorn;e apostil, and o&thorn;er doctors, &thorn;at &thorn;ei speke on &thorn;is<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Cor. x<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> mater; for Poule sei&thorn;, &THORN;e brede &thorn;at we breken is &thorn;e part taken of &thorn;e body of Crist. And Austeyn sei&thorn;, &THORN;is &thorn;ing &thorn;at is seen is breed,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Austeyn.</NOTE> and &thorn;at &thorn;at &thorn;e fei&thorn; aske&thorn; to be enformid &thorn;e bred is &thorn;e body of Crist. And &thorn;e decre, and o&thorn;er doctors mani, a corde. And syn &thorn;er wordis<NOTE PLACE="marg">Decre.</NOTE> are canoni&yogh;ed, and approuid of holi kirk, oi&thorn;er be houi&thorn; to graunt &thorn;er wordis, or to denay &thorn;e canoni&yogh;ing and aprouing of &thorn;e kirk; and &thorn;at semi&thorn; not good. &THORN;er for I sey as &thorn;eis seyncts doun, and trowe as holi kirk trowi&thorn;, and techi&thorn;; &thorn;at &thorn;e sacred host is verreyli &thorn;e body of Crist, for Crist sei&thorn; soo; and &thorn;us sei&thorn; Poule, Bre&thorn;er, fle<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Cor. x<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> fro worschipping of idols; I speke to &yogh;ow as to wyse men, demi&thorn; &thorn;is &thorn;ing &thorn;at I sey; &thorn;e cuppe of blessing &thorn;at we blesse, is not it &thorn;e comining of Crists blood? and bred &thorn;at we brek, is it not &thorn;e part taken of &thorn;e body of &thorn;e Lord? for we mani are oo body, and a life &thorn;at alle taken part of oo lofe, and of oo cuppe; forso&thorn;, I tok &thorn;is of<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Cor. xi<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> &thorn;e Lord, &thorn;at I be tok to &yogh;ow; for &thorn;e Lord Ihu, in &thorn;e ni&yogh;t &thorn;at he was betrayed, tok bred, and blessid, and brake, and &yogh;af his disciplis, and seid, Take and eete all of &thorn;is; &thorn;is is my body &thorn;at schal be trayed for &yogh;ow, do &thorn;is in my conmemoracoun. Also he tuke &thorn;e cuppe, after &thorn;at he sopid, seying, &THORN;is cuppe is a newe testament in my blod; do &thorn;is, als oft as &yogh;e schal take it, in to my conmemoracoun; for als oft as &yogh;e schal ete &thorn;is bred, and drink &thorn;e cuppe of &thorn;e Lord, &yogh;e schal schew &thorn;e de&thorn; of &thorn;e Lord, til &thorn;at he cumme. And so, who &thorn;at schal ete &thorn;is brede, and dring &thorn;is cuppe vnwor&thorn;ily, he schal be gylty of &thorn;e body and blood of &thorn;e Lord. &THORN;erfor man proue him selue, and so ete he of &thorn;is bred, and drink of &thorn;is cuppe, for wo &thorn;at eti&thorn; and drinki&thorn; vnwor&thorn;ily, eti&thorn; and drinki&thorn; dome to hymsilf, not deming wisely &thorn;e body of &thorn;e Lord. And upon &thorn;is sei&thorn; Ambrose<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ambrose.</NOTE> &thorn;us, It is a gostly medicyn, and memory of raunsom, bi wilk we deserue greiter &thorn;ingis, to wilk we are tau&yogh;t to ni&yogh;t; not but drery of 
<PB REF="00000111.tif" N="47"> &thorn;e ni&yogh;t of oure synnes, of &thorn;is &thorn;at in &thorn;e ni&yogh;t he was be tan for our synnis, wan his sowle was drery to &thorn;e de&thorn;. And also in &thorn;e mynd of &thorn;e same de&thorn;, he &yogh;af his disciplis &thorn;is bred, and &thorn;e cuppe of &thorn;e new testament, and monest to take it, and ete it, doutles to be made like to him, and innewid in to him; he meni&thorn; as mani as wil be in vnite of his body &thorn;at is &thorn;e kirk. And &thorn;is mete is prophita|ble to vs dwelling in &thorn;is vnite, bo&thorn; to body and to sowle; ffor &thorn;e flesch of Crist was peynid for the hele of our body, and his blod was &yogh;euen out for &thorn;e &yogh;ele of our soule, but profiti&thorn; not to hem &thorn;at are out of vnite; werfor &thorn;e apostel sei&thorn;, He &thorn;at eti&thorn; or drinki&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Cor. xi<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> vnwor&thorn;ily, &thorn;at is, oi&thorn;er wi&thorn; out deuocoun, or o&thorn;er wyse &thorn;an it is of &thorn;e Lord ordeynd, or dwelling in &thorn;e filli&thorn; of synne, he schal be gilty of &thorn;e body and blod of &thorn;e Lord; &thorn;at is, he schal &yogh;eue peyn for &thorn;e de&thorn; of Crist, as if he had slayn him, and he drawi&thorn; spot of good &thorn;ing to an iuel. And Austeyn sei&thorn;, We sey &thorn;is &thorn;ing &thorn;e body and<NOTE PLACE="marg">Austeyn.</NOTE> &thorn;e blod of Crist, &thorn;e wilk tan of &thorn;e &yogh;er&thorn; fro &thorn;e frutis, and halowd bi gostly praiors, we tak ritli to gostli &yogh;ele, in to memory of &thorn;e Lordis passioun; &thorn;e wilk, wan it is browt be handis of man to &thorn;at inuisible spice, is halowid not but bi &thorn;e Spirit of God wirking inuisibily; for God wirki&thorn; al &thorn;ingis &thorn;at are done in &thorn;is wirk bi bodily styrings. &THORN;is is &thorn;at we sey, and in all maneris striue to proue &thorn;e sacrifice of &thorn;e kirk to stond to gidre in two &thorn;ingis, and to be maad in two &thorn;ingis to gidre: &thorn;at is, &thorn;e visible spicis of elements, and inuisible flesch and blod of our Lord Ihu Crist; sacrament and &thorn;ing of &thorn;e sacrament, &thorn;at is &thorn;e body of Crist; as &thorn;e persoun of Crist stondi&thorn; to gidre of God and man, for he is verrey God and man; for ilk &thorn;ing conteni&thorn; in it silf &thorn;e trow&thorn; and &thorn;e nature of &thorn;oo &thorn;ings &thorn;at it is maad of; &thorn;is &thorn;ing &thorn;at is seen is breed, and &thorn;e cuppe &thorn;at &thorn;e &yogh;een schewen; but &thorn;is &thorn;at &thorn;e fei&thorn; aski&thorn; to be enformid &thorn;e bred is &thorn;e body of Crist. Also &thorn;e decre sei&thorn;, I Beringary concent to &thorn;e holi<NOTE PLACE="marg">Decre.</NOTE> kirk of Rome, and as &thorn;e apostil sei&thorn;, I cnowlech of mow&thorn; and hert, me to hold &thorn;e same fei&thorn; of &thorn;e sacrament of &thorn;e Lordis bord, &thorn;e 
<PB REF="00000112.tif" N="48"> worschipful sir Nicol pope in heys holi seyne&yogh;, he ha&thorn; be tane me of autorite of &thorn;e gospel, and of &thorn;e apostil, and ha&thorn; fermid to me &thorn;e bred and wyne, &thorn;at are putt in &thorn;e auter, to be after &thorn;e consecra|coun not onli sacrament, but verrey body and blod of our Lord Ihu Crist sencibly, not onli in sacrament, but in trow&thorn; to be tretid; wi&thorn; handis of &thorn;e prest to be brokyn, and wi&thorn; &thorn;e te&thorn; of fei&thorn;ful men. And mani o&thorn;er seingis of doctors a corden to &thorn;is.</P>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="13" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XIII. Worschip|ing of kirkis.</HEAD>
<P>An o&thorn;er poynt is &thorn;is; kirks are not to be worschippid, nor sergs to be multiplied &thorn;er in. I wot wat I seid. Wil &thorn;u offir a candil &thorn;at &thorn;u geyt merit and grace; &yogh;eue to &thorn;e pore, &thorn;at he may see go to his bedde, or to do sum good werk; or to wold womman, &thorn;at scho spynne, or teese her wolle, or do sum good wark. And &thorn;at &thorn;is be &thorn;e profitabler, concorden all fei&thorn;ful doctors, and cristen men. And oft &thorn;u reproue hem &thorn;at drawen a wey help fro &thorn;e pore to bigge deade warkis. In Ysay &thorn;us is writun; Refresch &thorn;e pore, and<NOTE PLACE="marg">Isaye.</NOTE> &thorn;at is my refresching, sei&thorn; &thorn;e Lord God. And Seint Jerom sei&thorn;,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Jerom.</NOTE> Mani biggen wall, and drawen a wey pilars of kirk, &thorn;e marblis shinen, &thorn;e bondis schinen wi&thorn; gold, &thorn;e auter is vmbeset wi&thorn; stonis, but of &thorn;e ministris of Crist is no chesing. No man sett a&yogh;en me &thorn;e riche temple in &thorn;e iewes, &thorn;e bord, &thorn;e lanternis, censars, pannis, cuppis, mortars, and o&thorn;er forgid wi&thorn; gold, ffor &thorn;eis were &thorn;an aprouid of &thorn;e Lord, wan prestis slow &thorn;e offringis, and bests blod was re|missioun of synnis; &thorn;ow alle &thorn;eis went bifor in figer; &thorn;ei writun for us in to wom &thorn;e &yogh;endis of &thorn;is world are comyn. But now wan &thorn;e Lord ha&thorn; halowid &thorn;e pouert of his hows, bere we &thorn;e cros, and kownt we gold as cley. To reue ani &thorn;ing fro a frend is &thorn;eft; to defraude &thorn;e kirke is sacrilege; to haue tane &thorn;ing to be &yogh;euen to &thorn;e pore and mani hungry, and to reseue it, is vile or fals drede, or of opunyst felony; to wi&thorn; drawe ani &thorn;ing &thorn;er of, it passi&thorn; &thorn;e cruelte of all robbars. Hector Thebanus a man sum tyme richist, wen he went to vse philosophie at Athenis, he kest a wey a gret peise of gold; he gessid &thorn;at he mi&yogh;t not haue to gidre, riches and vertu; 
<PB REF="00000113.tif" N="49"> we stoffid and farsid wi&thorn; gold, folowen pore Crist; and a color of takyng of almis, we chouche a boue our mikil riches, how may we trewly depart o&thorn;er mennis &thorn;ingis, &thorn;at dredfully reseruen our owne. &THORN;e fulle womb disputi&thorn; litly of fastyng. Vp on &thorn;e wilk sei&thorn; William de Seynt Amour, Swilk maner of men bigging &thorn;us<NOTE PLACE="marg">William de Seynt Amour.</NOTE> biggings semen to turne bred in to stones; &thorn;at is to sey, &thorn;e bred of &thorn;e pore, &thorn;at is almis beggid, in to hepis of stonis, &thorn;at is in to stonen howsis costlew and superflew; and &thorn;erfor &thorn;ey semen werrar &thorn;an &thorn;e fend, &thorn;at askid stonis to be turnid in to bred. Wer for Jerom<NOTE PLACE="marg">Jerom.</NOTE> kenni&thorn; wel simple men seying, Gif no &thorn;ing to no man, ouer liflod and opun necessaries; &thorn;at howndis ete not &thorn;e bred of children; forso&thorn;, he sei&thorn;, &thorn;e sowle of &thorn;e trewe man is &thorn;e temple of Crist; honor it, clo&thorn; it, gif it &yogh;eftis, and tak vp Crist in it. Wat profit is it &thorn;e wallis to schine wi&thorn; precious stonis, and Crist to di&yogh;e in &thorn;e pore man for hunger. Also &thorn;us sei&thorn; Crisostom, Men bigging &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">Crisostom.</NOTE> memoryes of martres, and honoring kirkis, semen to do a good dede: but and if &thorn;ey kepe o&thorn;er ri&yogh;tfulnes of God; if &thorn;e pore ioi of &thorn;er goodis; if &thorn;ey mak not o&thorn;er mennis goodis here bi violence or bi fraude; who so is vnwyse &thorn;at he vnderstondi&thorn; not, for &thorn;ei mak &thorn;er biggings, not to &thorn;e glory of God, but to mannes dome. And vniustly &thorn;ei bigge memories were pore men, &thorn;oling violence of hem, crien a&yogh;en hem; for martirs ioien not &thorn;at &thorn;ei are honorid so of &thorn;e money of swilk pore men greten; what ri&yogh;tfulnes is &thorn;is to &yogh;ef &yogh;eftis to &thorn;e dead, and spoyle &thorn;e quek; taken of &thorn;e blod of wrecchis, and offre to God? &THORN;is is not to offre to God, but to wylen to mak God felow of &thorn;is violence, &thorn;at if he tak gladly money &thorn;at is offrid to him of synne, he consent to synne. Wel &thorn;u bigge &thorn;e howse of God? &yogh;ef to &thorn;e fei&thorn;ful pore werof &thorn;ey may lif, and &thorn;u hast biggid a resounable howse of God. Men dwellen in biggings, but God dwelli&thorn; in holy men; &thorn;erfor wat men are &thorn;ey &thorn;at spoylen men, and makyn biggings of marters? &thorn;ey aray &thorn;e dwell|ings of men, and disturblun &thorn;e habitacouns of God. Ihu &yogh;ed in to &thorn;e biggings of &thorn;e temple, and sowt &thorn;e holines of &thorn;e temple, but 
<PB REF="00000114.tif" N="50"> wan he fond in &thorn;e temple &thorn;e properte of &thorn;e temple, he went out; for &thorn;e bigging stod &thorn;at man had reysid, but &thorn;e holines &thorn;at God had ordeynid was fallen; &thorn;e temple of man is biggid of stonis of faire composicoun, but &thorn;e temple of God is &thorn;e congregacoun of men leuing religiously. A man deli&thorn; [in] &thorn;e bigging of wallis, but God in &thorn;e conuersacoun of seynts. &THORN;e prophet sei&thorn;, Lord, I haue<NOTE PLACE="marg">Dauid, Ps. xxv<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> louid &thorn;e fairnes. Wilk fairnes? Not &thorn;is &thorn;at diuersite of schining marbles maken, but &thorn;is &thorn;at &thorn;e barianns of gracis of louing me maki&thorn;; &thorn;at fairnes deliti&thorn; &thorn;e flesch, but &thorn;is quekeni&thorn; &thorn;e soule; &thorn;at for a tym desceyui&thorn; and iapi&thorn; &thorn;e &yogh;ee, but &thorn;is biggi&thorn; &thorn;e vnder|stonding perpetual. &THORN;is sei&thorn; he. &THORN;erfor it semi&thorn; good, spedi, and meritori, &thorn;at &thorn;e kirk be honorid, neuer&thorn;eles not to mikil nor super|flue, ne curiously, nor proudly, for glory of &thorn;e world, noi&thorn;er in biggings, noi&thorn;er in li&yogh;ts, noi&thorn;er in instruments, nor minstris ne|cessarijs in to vse &thorn;er of; but honestly and mesurabli honorid and kepid in alle &thorn;ings, and mikil honestliar &thorn;an it is nowe in mani placis; and specialy &thorn;at feyris nor markets had no place in &thorn;e kirk, in solempne tymis, wan men schuld tent to preyers and to Goddis seruys; and &thorn;at in silk tyme men tent not to idil talis, foul spechis, harlotries, bakbityngis, or conuenticlis, purposing iuel, as &thorn;eft, or manslawt, or swilk o&thorn;er; so no synnis were vsid in &thorn;e kirk; &thorn;at &thorn;e house of God be not maad a den of &thorn;efis. &THORN;us schuld &thorn;e kirk be honorid; but in &thorn;e quek gostly kirk, &thorn;at is &thorn;e congrega|coun of cristun men, au&yogh;te honestly to be honorid, first in vertuis, and vertuis dedis, good maneris, and ritful warks, clensid of alle crimis and dedis forbeden hem in holi writt, and fei&thorn;ful doctors, and ordinaunce of &thorn;e kirk; and &thorn;us schuld God haue a gloriouse kirk, &thorn;at is now pollutid and fylid wi&thorn; many vnleful &thorn;ings. Whe&thorn;er is it not writun in &thorn;e lawe of &thorn;e kirk &thorn;us? Forso&thorn; it is an horrible<NOTE PLACE="marg">Decretal.</NOTE> &thorn;ing &thorn;at in sum kirkes is witnessid marchaundis to haue place; so &thorn;at ani &thorn;ing be askid for bischoppis, abbots, or o&thorn;er personis, to be putt in &thorn;er segis, or prestis to be induyd, or inled in kirks, or for sepulturis, or exequies, diriges of &thorn;e dead, or blessingis of wed|dings, 
<PB REF="00000115.tif" N="51"> or o&thorn;er sacraments. And sum demen to be leful, for &thorn;ei deme not &thorn;e lawe of &thorn;e dede for to harme by cause of long custom, not takyng heed &thorn;at synnis are so mikil greuowsare, euer &thorn;e lengar &thorn;ei hold bound &thorn;e vncely sowle; &thorn;erfor we forbede more strengliare &thorn;at &thorn;eis &thorn;ings be no more do &thorn;us; so no &thorn;ing be askid for personis of &thorn;e kirk to be browt in to &thorn;er segis, nor for presthed to be institut, nor for dead to be byried, nor weddings to be blessid, nor o&thorn;er sacraments. And if ani presume a&yogh;en &thorn;is, know he him to haue porcoun wi&thorn; Gie&yogh;i. And als after &thorn;e decre, in an o&thorn;er place: No<NOTE PLACE="marg">Decre.</NOTE> man presume to &yogh;eue for ani custom, noi&thorn;er to &thorn;e taking of symonyently, &thorn;at is to sey, for coueytise, for his labour tak ani &thorn;ing, for who &thorn;at selli&thorn; ei&thorn;er of &thorn;is &thorn;ings wi&thorn; wilk &thorn;o comi&thorn; not for&thorn;, he leui&thorn; noi&thorn;er vnsold. And schame it is &thorn;at a man be con|streynid to &yogh;eue his money for nowt. Of silk &thorn;ings is &thorn;e kirk to be purgid, for mani causis: forso&thorn; as Symon Magus, bicause of coueytise, wold haue bowt of &thorn;e apostel his power, &thorn;at he schuld &thorn;e Holy Goost receyue to hele hem &thorn;at he put &thorn;e handis to, &thorn;at he mi&yogh;t haue gotun money of &thorn;e selling of signis; as &thorn;e decre<NOTE PLACE="marg">Decre Saluator.</NOTE> Saluator witnissi&thorn;. And &thorn;erfor he was reprouid of Petre, for he demid to possede &thorn;e &yogh;eft of God bi money, and &thorn;erfor he had no part in &thorn;at &thorn;ing. It semi&thorn; &thorn;at prestis are nowe in &thorn;e same chapi|ter, takyng goostly grace or ordres &thorn;at &thorn;ei geyt &thorn;er of superfleu riches, prid of world, and lust of flesch, and &thorn;ey &thorn;at minstren to o&thorn;er in &thorn;at entent, &thorn;at &thorn;ei habunde in &thorn;er &thorn;ings. And it semi&thorn; &thorn;at lewid men hiring prestis, in &thorn;at entent, deming to by &thorn;e goostly &thorn;ings so, or &thorn;at &thorn;ei eke riches to hem, or &thorn;er o&thorn;er &thorn;ings befor seyd, are greuid in &thorn;e same synne. And &thorn;us it semi&thorn; to sume, &thorn;at wat euer clerk taki&thorn; priate, religioun, bischophed, or dignite of &thorn;e kirk, &thorn;at he life lustili, or habunde after hienes of &thorn;e world, or to lord in &thorn;at maner &thorn;at Crist forbedi&thorn; his disciplis to lord in, he synni&thorn; deadly. And &thorn;at &thorn;e parentis of swilk a clerk are [or?] worldly frends helping him to ani artis or sciens, prelats promouing, or secular 
<PB REF="00000116.tif" N="52"> lordis procuring &thorn;at &thorn;at clerk lord in &thorn;at maner, &thorn;ei synnun deadly;<NOTE PLACE="marg">The Ca|noun Sunt quidam.</NOTE> &thorn;is is opun bi &thorn;e canoun, i. q. i. <I>Sunt quidam</I>. Of silk &thorn;ings be howui&thorn; &thorn;e kirk to be clensid.</P>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="14" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XIV. Sy|monie of prestis.</HEAD>
<P>An o&thorn;er poynt is her putt, &thorn;at prestis to sing may not first mak couenaunt wi&thorn; out symonie. Of &thorn;is mater &thorn;us seyn fei&thorn;ful doctors of diuinite, and doctors in lawe of &thorn;e kirk, &thorn;us: A prest we&thorn;er he be beneficid or not, he howi&thorn; not to sett to hire his gostly warks; nor it is not leful to him to reseyue ani &thorn;ing of couenaunt to a day or &yogh;ere for Goddis seruyce to be seid; for wo &thorn;at selli&thorn; ani of &thorn;o &thorn;ings wi&thorn; wilk &thorn;e to&thorn;er com<SUP>t</SUP> not, he leui&thorn; noi&thorn;er vnsold, as &thorn;e decre sei&thorn;; &thorn;is bi Ihoun. Neuer&thorn;eles he may sett to hire his<NOTE PLACE="marg">Decre.</NOTE> bodily werks; &thorn;at is, he may astreyn himsilf a &yogh;er to dwel wi&thorn; a man to serue him, as writ, or teche children; and &thorn;us he may lefuly, sauid his ordre; so &thorn;at he outtak fro his generalite, bo&thorn; in mynde and in worde, his goostly warks, wilk he may graunt frely wi&thorn; out couenaunt or price, after &thorn;e wille of God. And &thorn;us &thorn;e couenaunts how to be seuerythly, &thorn;at &thorn;e goostly &thorn;ings be done frely. But for &thorn;e synne of symonye may vnnese or neuer be fled in swilk &thorn;ings, &thorn;erfor conduct prestis are reprouid of &thorn;e lawe, after Hostiensis, and Innocent; and eft Hostiensis sei&thorn; of hem &thorn;at &yogh;euen<NOTE PLACE="marg">Hostiensis. Innocent.</NOTE> a peney, or peyneyes, to prestis, for to do aniuersaries, or to syng a messe of &thorn;e Holi Gost, or swilk maner, or for to syng trentaylis, in alle swilk casis, to tak or &yogh;ef temporal &thorn;ing for goostly &thorn;ing, of for&thorn;word, or certeyn couenaunt, it is symonye. We&thorn;er it be &yogh;euen for &thorn;e sacrament, we&thorn;er for &thorn;e office. After &thorn;is word for noti&thorn; or taki&thorn; appreciacoun. &THORN;is sei&thorn; he. &THORN;erfor ilk man see why he taki&thorn; &thorn;e money, &thorn;at is to sey, what he do&thorn; &thorn;erfor. And ilk man see why a&yogh;enne, for what cause principaly. And see after for he &yogh;eue for Goddis mede, lok how God biddi&thorn;. If he &yogh;eue it for labor, lok what it is. And if he gif it for sustinaunce, lok what mede it is. Sum men seyn &thorn;us, &thorn;at symonie is a studiouse wille to by or selle, or on ani maner to haue goostly power, or &thorn;e office 
<PB REF="00000117.tif" N="53"> &thorn;er of, for temporal price, in entent of chaunging to gidre &thorn;e toon for &thorn;e to&thorn;er, as it semi&thorn; bi holy writt, and bi &thorn;e lawe, for Symon<NOTE PLACE="marg">Act. uiij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> Magus seyng &thorn;e apostil &yogh;euing &thorn;e Holy Goost bi leying vpon his handis, offrid him money to bye &thorn;e gostly power, &thorn;at &thorn;ei schuld tak &thorn;e Holy Goost &thorn;at he schuld putt hands to; but Peter seid to him, &thorn;i money be wi&thorn; &thorn;e in to perdicoun, for &thorn;u gessest to haue &thorn;e gift of God for money. And in &thorn;e lawe it is seid, &thorn;at Symon wold haue bout &thorn;e Holi Gost in &thorn;at entent, &thorn;at of selling of synnis &thorn;at schuld be do bi him, he schuld wyn money. And &thorn;us of him it taki&thorn; &thorn;e name of symonye. And &thorn;erfor &thorn;ei &thorn;at sellen gostly &thorn;ings, and &thorn;ei &thorn;at bien hem, so folowing Symon are callid Symon|ients. And &thorn;us sei&thorn; Parisiensis in his bok; Prestis singing for<NOTE PLACE="marg">Parisiensis.</NOTE> money sellen Crist, and are werrer &thorn;an Judas in &thorn;eis fiue points. Judas sold him onis dedly, and not glorified, for &thorn;ritty penies, wen he trowid him not God, but a deadly man walking in &yogh;er&thorn;e; and after, he repentid, and browt a&yogh;en &thorn;e penis. But &thorn;ei selle him vndeadly, and glorified, and ofte and for lesse price, wan &thorn;ei trowen him God, regning in heuen vndedly, and til &thorn;ey cum to penaunce &thorn;ei restore not &thorn;e money. &THORN;us he sei&thorn;. And Jerom sei&thorn; &thorn;us;<NOTE PLACE="marg">Jerom.</NOTE> Als oft of men are seid singing for menis fauor, and temporel wynning, or hope of ani temporel profet, so&thorn;ly Crist is sold and be trayd, and wen &thorn;e body and blod of Crist is tretid wi&thorn; foul hands, and polutid conciens, Crist is trayd and crucified. And Ambrose<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ambrose.</NOTE> sei&thorn;; He [&thorn;at] &yogh;eti&thorn; and drynki&thorn; &thorn;is sacrament wi&thorn; out deuocoun, or o&thorn;erwise &thorn;an it is ordeynid of &thorn;e Lord, synging messe, or dwelling in lust of synning, he schal be gilty of body and of blod of Crist, and schal &yogh;eue peynis for de&thorn; of Crist, as if he had slayn him, and he schal draw spott of good &thorn;ing iuel tane. &THORN;is sei&thorn; he, and more afterword.</P>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="15" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XV. The pope, car|dinalis, bischopis, and other prelatis are disciplis of anticrist.</HEAD>
<P>&THORN;is is a no&thorn;er poynt, &thorn;at &thorn;e pope, cardinalis, bischopis, and o&thorn;er prelats be ne&thorn;e, are disciplis of anticrist, and sellars of merit. I wot what I haue rehersid &thorn;e wordis of doctors &thorn;at spekin on &thorn;is 
<PB REF="00000118.tif" N="54"> mater. Crist seid to &thorn;e Jewis, &yogh;e ben of &thorn;e fader &thorn;e fend, and wel do &thorn;e desir of &yogh;or fader, for he was manslear fro &thorn;e biginning. And so to &thorn;e propos, Whas doctrine any folowi&thorn;, his disciple he is. And Crist sei&thorn;, he &thorn;at is not wi&thorn; me, he is a&yogh;enis me. And so&thorn;ly my<NOTE PLACE="marg">Matt. xij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> warks a cordyn not to &thorn;e warks of Sathanas, for I a cord in no &thorn;ing wi&thorn; him, but al vtterly we are contrari; for I mak beningne wyl saue sowlis; he prowd, enuious, couetous, to tyn hem; I gedre to gidre vertuys wi&thorn; my preching; he scateri&thorn; and departi&thorn; fro &thorn;e vnite of &thorn;e kirk. &THORN;is sei&thorn; &thorn;e glose. &THORN;erfor who &thorn;at vsi&thorn; swilk werks<NOTE PLACE="marg">Glose.</NOTE> is disciple of anticrist, and anticrist. For Jon sei&thorn; in his epistle,<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Jo. ii<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> Sonnis is it &thorn;o last hour, and as &yogh;e han herd for anticrist comi&thorn;, now are many anticristis maade, werfor we wot &thorn;at is it &thorn;e last hour. Ilk spirit &thorn;at vndo&thorn; Ihu Crist is not of God, and &thorn;is is anticrist,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ibid. iu<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> of wom &yogh;e han herde &thorn;at he comi&thorn;, and now he is in &thorn;e world. Wer &thorn;e glose; os Austeyn sei&thorn;: Ilk man axe her his conciens we&thorn;er<NOTE PLACE="marg">Austeyn.</NOTE> he be anticrist. Ilk one contrary to Crist is anticrist, and &thorn;e tung a lone is not to be axid, but &thorn;e lif. Poul sei&thorn;, &THORN;ei witness hem to<NOTE PLACE="marg">Tit. i<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> know God, but in dedis &thorn;ey denay. Als many as &thorn;e kirk ha&thorn; for sworn men, fraudars, misdoars, sortylogers, spousbrekars, drunk|unsum men, vsurers, and who euer is contrari to &thorn;e doctrin, and to &thorn;e word of God, he is anticrist. If &thorn;u luf synnis, be [&thorn;u] wi&thorn; in, be &thorn;u wi&thorn; out, and if &thorn;u be contrari to Crist, be &thorn;u wi&thorn; in, be &thorn;u wi&thorn; out, &thorn;u art anticrist, be &thorn;u wi&thorn; in, be &thorn;u wi&thorn; out, &thorn;u art caff. &THORN;is sei&thorn; Austeyn. And &thorn;us sei&thorn; Lincoln, in a sermoun: &THORN;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">Lincolne.</NOTE> office of prelacy passi&thorn; alle o&thorn;er in charge, syn &thorn;e principale and &thorn;e finale wark of Crist &thorn;at he cam for in to &thorn;is world is &thorn;e quiking of soulis; and &thorn;e proper wark of Sathanas, and moost entent of him, [who] is a manslear fro &thorn;e biginning, as [is?] sleyng and mortifying of sowlis: werfor scheperds, clepid &thorn;e persoun of &thorn;e verrey schep|herd Ihu Crist, nou&yogh;t schewing &thorn;e gospel, &thorn;of &thorn;ei ekid not o&thorn;er malice ouer, &thorn;ey are anticrists, and Sathanas transfigurid in to an aungel of li&yogh;t; &thorn;euys priuey and opun slears and traytors of &thorn;e schep, 
<PB REF="00000119.tif" N="55"> makyng &thorn;e hous of prayors a den of &thorn;euis. Also &thorn;ey &yogh;ekun al kynd of brekyng of law, &thorn;at now &thorn;er is not opun what &thorn;ing &thorn;e Lord hem a towere. And &thorn;at I passe ouer schortly, wi&thorn; al kynd of syn, felony, and abhominacoun, and new aduencouns. And in &thorn;er aduencouns &thorn;ey are filid as &thorn;e prophet sei&thorn; to God, and to &thorn;e court of heuen are &thorn;ey moost abominable, and hateful maade; for bi hem &thorn;e nam of God is blasfemid in alle folk. Wen &thorn;e lesynd of &thorn;e herd is a bok of &thorn;e schepe, and &thorn;ei are opunly maistris of alle iuelis; how are &thorn;ey not heretyks? namly sin, &thorn;e word of dede, is more effectuos in werkyng &thorn;en &thorn;e word of &thorn;e mou&thorn;. And wen &thorn;ei of &thorn;er office are gederers of euerlastyng lif, how euen &thorn;ey are &thorn;us misusing &thorn;is generatif streng&thorn;e, are &thorn;ei not, a cordantly to &thorn;e wordis of &thorn;e prophets, werr, and abhominabler &thorn;an carnal sodomits? namly wan &thorn;e misusing of &thorn;e better vertu is werr, and more abho|minable. And &thorn;us &thorn;eis scheperds are, of office, li&yogh;t and sun of &thorn;e world, li&yogh;tning and quickning it; but a&yogh;enword, wan &thorn;ei mak and &yogh;etten out for li&yogh;t &thorn;ickest derknes, and so lifly &yogh;et corrumping cold and blakning, opunly are traytors of &thorn;is world. But wo is &thorn;e formar and original cause, wel, and biginning of &thorn;is &thorn;us gret iuel, I drede ungly to sey, tremel and quake. Neuer&thorn;eles I dar not hold it stille, &thorn;at I falle not in to &thorn;is woo &thorn;at &thorn;e prophet sei&thorn;, Woo to<NOTE PLACE="marg">Isa. uj<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> me for I haue be stille, for I am a man pollutid in lippis. &THORN;e cause, welle, and biginning of &thorn;is iuel is &thorn;e court of Rome; not only for it scateri&thorn; not his &thorn;ings, and purgi&thorn; not his abhomina|couns, wen it a lone myth, &thorn;is moost and heiast is haldun &thorn;er to; but &thorn;us mikil &thorn;e more &thorn;at it silf bi his prouisiouns, dispensacouns, and &yogh;euing of pastoral curis, ordeyni&thorn; in &thorn;e een of &thorn;e sun, swilk as are towchid bifore, hyrdis, &yogh;a traytors of &thorn;is world, &thorn;at it peruey to &thorn;e temporal lif of sum man, it ha&thorn; be taken to &thorn;e deuowring or swelluing of alle bestis of &thorn;e feld, &thorn;at is to al &thorn;e fendis to ay lasting de&thorn; many &thorn;ow&yogh;andis; for &thorn;e wilk lest of alle to be quicknid &yogh;end|lesly, &thorn;e Son of God wold be condempnid to fowlist de&thorn;; for [he] 
<PB REF="00000120.tif" N="56"> &thorn;at &yogh;eui&thorn; &thorn;e cur of sowlis til an vnmi&yogh;ty, or vnkunning, or not weling to kepe, is gilty of alle &thorn;oo, &thorn;of ani schape; as he &thorn;at &yogh;eui&thorn; &thorn;e gouerning of a schip til an vnwitti, vnkunning, or not willing goueren it, is gilty of &thorn;e schip and alle &thorn;ings content &thorn;er in; and he &thorn;at letti&thorn; not silk &yogh;euing wen he is holden a may, is strenid bi &thorn;e same gilt. A how bitter luf and vauncing ganging and koward, &thorn;at he reys his luf at a moment a boue a veyn &thorn;ing, and kast him|silf down in to &thorn;e vtterist murkenes. &THORN;is sei&thorn; he. Also &thorn;us sei&thorn; Odo: Prelats not preching are ra&thorn;er Pilats &thorn;an prelatis, spoilars<NOTE PLACE="marg">Odo.</NOTE> not biholdars, herodians of Heroud, not heyris of Crist, prelats wi&thorn; &thorn;er stafis and o&thorn;er ornaments are statuit ymagis, ful of kaff, wi&thorn; a bow to sley &thorn;e fowlis, and as a nap in &thorn;e rof, so a sole in &thorn;e heyre of honoris. If I were, he sei&thorn;, of &thorn;e noumbre of bischoppis, I were of &thorn;e noumbre of men to be dampnid. &THORN;is sei&thorn; he. &THORN;e gospel sei&thorn;, &thorn;at Ihu cam in to &thorn;e coostis of Cesarie of Philip, and<NOTE PLACE="marg">Matt. xvi<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> he axid his disciplis, seying, Wham sey men to be &thorn;e sone of man? And &thorn;ei seid, Sum Jon baptist, sum Hely, sum Jeremie, or oon of &thorn;e prophetis; &thorn;an he seid to hem, Wham sey &yogh;e me to be? Peter ansuerid and seid, &THORN;u art Crist, &thorn;o sone of quik God. Ihu an|suerid and seid to him, Blessid be &thorn;u Peter, dowue sone, for flesch nor blod schewid not &thorn;is to &thorn;e, but my Fadre. And I sey to &thorn;e, &thorn;u art Peter, and on &thorn;is ston I schal bigge my kirk, and &thorn;e &yogh;ats of helle schal not be mi&yogh;ty a&yogh;en &thorn;e; and I schal &yogh;eue to &thorn;e keys of &thorn;e kyndom of heuen, and what &thorn;ing &thorn;u bindest up on &yogh;er&thorn; schal be bounden in heuen, and what &thorn;u lowsist vp on &yogh;er&thorn;e, schal be lowsid in heuen. And &thorn;an he bad hem &thorn;ei schuld not sey to ani man &thorn;at he was Crist. And he be gan to schew to hem &thorn;at it be houid him to go to Jerusalem, and &thorn;ole many &thorn;ings of &thorn;e olde men, scribis, and princis of prestis, and to be slayn, and rise a&yogh;en &thorn;e &thorn;rid day. And Peter tok him be side, and be gan to blam him, and seid, Lord, God schild &thorn;is fro &thorn;e, &thorn;is schal not be to &thorn;e, be merciful to &thorn;isilf. And he turnid and seid to Peter, Go o bak 
<PB REF="00000121.tif" N="57"> after me Sathanas, and &thorn;u art sclaunder to me, for &thorn;u sauerist not &thorn;ing &thorn;at is of God, but of men. Now &thorn;an, we&thorn;er ani folowing Peter in &thorn;is office of prelacye, is blessiddar or perfitar &thorn;an Peter, &thorn;erfor if Peter after his blessing, and silk behi&yogh;t, is seid of Crist Sathan, whi not &thorn;ei &thorn;at are in to sclaunder to God, and lesser saueren &thorn;ings &thorn;at are of God, and more &thorn;ings &thorn;at are of men, syn &thorn;is is writun to our lore. And howe &thorn;e name of God is sclaundrid and blasfemid bi iuel prelatis and techers, it is opun oft in &thorn;e scripture. Poul sei&thorn;, &THORN;u &thorn;at prechist to not steyl, stelist? &thorn;u &thorn;at<NOTE PLACE="marg">Rom. ij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> biddist do no lechery, dost lechery? &thorn;u &thorn;at wlatis idols, dost sacrilege? &thorn;u gloris in &thorn;e lawe, wnworscippist God be breging of &thorn;e lawe? &thorn;e name of God is blasfemid bi &yogh;ow among &thorn;e folk. And after, &thorn;e prophete; &THORN;ei filid me to my peple for a lumpe of<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ezek. xiij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> bred, and a handful of barly, &thorn;at &thorn;ey slee sowl &thorn;at di&yogh;e not, quiken sowl &thorn;at lyuen not, lying to my peple, trowing to lesing. And Parisiensis sei&thorn;, Wan any auerous or couetous is canoni&yogh;id in &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">Parisiens.</NOTE> kirk, or maad cheef, &thorn;an may &thorn;e o&thorn;er chanouns of &thorn;e chirche sey, our moder ha&thorn; gotun to vs a moldewarp for a bro&thorn;er. And wan a bacbitar is canoni&yogh;id, &thorn;an ha&thorn; &thorn;at kirk gendrid a serpent. And wan an vndiscret is maad bischop in &thorn;e kirk, &thorn;an is an hornid asse born &thorn;er in. And Odo sei&thorn; &thorn;us, &THORN;ey are byars and sellars in &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">Odo.</NOTE> temple, &thorn;at wenun winning to be pite, and byen to selle &thorn;e derar. We se now alle &thorn;e lif of &thorn;e kirk bryn to defend dignite to mul|tipli possessiouns, al is &yogh;euen to honor, no &thorn;ing to holynesse; wer for it is seid, triacle is turnid in to venyn, and &thorn;is &thorn;at was foundun to remedie, is foundun to de&thorn;. But and of &thorn;e riches of clerkis &thorn;at &thorn;ei misuse, &thorn;e Lord bad &thorn;e sonis of Leuy &thorn;at &thorn;ei schuld haue no part a mong &thorn;e sonis of Israel. But &thorn;ei dispicing, folouun worldly wynning, &thorn;e auteris of Crist are maad &thorn;e bordis of chaungis bi couetous men, for messis &thorn;ey syng for money, &thorn;ei putt out for money, and swilk messis &thorn;ey sing as &thorn;ei hope moost wynning, in &thorn;ey are sellars of dowuis, for &thorn;ei selle spiritual &thorn;ingis. And &thorn;of 
<PB REF="00000122.tif" N="58"> &thorn;ey crie not wi&thorn; &thorn;e mow&thorn;, neuer&thorn;eles in dedis &thorn;ei sey wi&thorn; Judas, Wat wil &yogh;e &yogh;eue me, and I gif him to &yogh;ow? &THORN;us crien monkis, and o&thorn;er religious, selling &thorn;er habits and suffragijs, and prestis singing for money; &thorn;e walle of &thorn;e kirk &thorn;at schuld be &thorn;e hird is brokin; swyn and houndis are gone and filun &thorn;e kirk; doumb doggis, prelats corrupt, &thorn;at may not bark, and onclen suyn, fyling o&thorn;er, lyfing bestly, are sett in &thorn;e kirk. What more abhominacoun of desolacoun in holi place &thorn;an &thorn;at a swyn do vpon &thorn;e holy vestiment, and sing Goddis holy office? houndis and woluis roryn &thorn;e psalmis, os were woluis criyng ilk to o&thorn;er; &thorn;e lioun of prid ha&thorn; lordid &thorn;e clergy, disposing al &thorn;ing at his list; &thorn;e serpent of enuy&yogh;e hissi&thorn;, &thorn;at bakbiti&thorn; to al and enflaumi&thorn; &thorn;e grete; &thorn;e hound of wrechfulnes grenni&thorn; wi&thorn; his te&thorn;; &thorn;e feldhasser of dyerynes labori&thorn; to swernes; &thorn;e wolue of rauyn opuni&thorn; his chekis, &thorn;at multiplien messis and gospells for offring; &thorn;e bere of glotonie romist a bout, &thorn;at singi&thorn; wi&thorn; hie voys, for to fille &thorn;e wombe; &thorn;e swyn of vnclennes drowni&thorn; himself in &thorn;e mig of lecherie; &thorn;e tood of gile hauing mani pursis schal minister to alle. And wen &thorn;e riche man die&thorn;, &thorn;e processioun of bestis is maad; &thorn;an in figeris was depeyntid in &thorn;e walle, and &thorn;e swyn and &thorn;e wolf and o&thorn;er bests berun &thorn;e cros and &thorn;e sergis, and ryngun &thorn;e bellis; sir Beringary &thorn;e bere syngi&thorn; &thorn;e messe; &thorn;e lioun wi&thorn; o&thorn;er bestis schal be best fed, but &yogh;er &thorn;e more &thorn;at &thorn;ey &thorn;ole, ai &thorn;e more schal &thorn;e fendis torment. &THORN;is sei&thorn; Odo.</P>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="16" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XVI. Of Cristis Vicar.</HEAD>
<P>An o&thorn;er poynt &thorn;at is putt is &thorn;is, &thorn;at &thorn;er is no pope ne Cristis vicar, but an holy man. &THORN;is may &thorn;us be prouid; for him be howui&thorn; to be halowid wi&thorn; &thorn;e sacrament of baptem, and of presthed, and of dignite. And oft is bidun to prestis in &thorn;e lawe to be holy and halow o&thorn;er; and for hoyle of halowing of &thorn;e Lord is vp on hem. Also &thorn;us prayi&thorn; Crist for alle his, Fader, halow hem in trow&thorn;,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Joh. xuij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> &thorn;i word is trow&thorn;, as &thorn;u hast send [me] in to &thorn;e world, so haue I send hem in &thorn;e world, and for hem I halow myself, &thorn;at &thorn;ei be halowid in trow&thorn;. And &thorn;us is hadde in decreis; Lo it aperi&thorn; how &thorn;ei<NOTE PLACE="marg">Decrt.</NOTE> 
<PB REF="00000123.tif" N="59"> schal schap &thorn;e perel of &thorn;e charge, &thorn;at &thorn;ey be &thorn;olid to minister prestly o&thorn;er sacraments, for &thorn;ey are remeuid fro &thorn;is not only for heresy, or o&thorn;er ilk gretter syn, but also for negligens. In wilk &thorn;ingis bysily it is to not, &thorn;at &thorn;e sacrament of presthed befor o&thorn;er, more wor&thorn;ily, and wi&thorn; cure, is to be &yogh;euen and tane; for but if it be so &yogh;euen and tane, it schal fuyle to be rate or ferme, os it is not perfitly done. O&thorn;er sacramentis are &yogh;euen to ilk man for himsilf, and silk &thorn;ey are to ilk man as &thorn;ei are tane wi&thorn; hart and concience; but &thorn;is is not only &yogh;euen for hem silf but for o&thorn;er, and &thorn;erfor is nede it be tane wi&thorn; verrey hart and clene concience for him self, and as to o&thorn;er, not only wi&thorn; out ilk synne, but also wi&thorn; out ilk name of fame, for schunder of bre&thorn;er, to was profit presthed is &yogh;euen, not only &thorn;at men prest, or be boun, but &thorn;at &thorn;ey prophet. &thorn;is &thorn;e decre. Lo it semi&thorn; &thorn;at he is not li&yogh;tly nor profi&yogh;tly Crists pope ne his vicar but if he be holi, ellis whi is he callid holiest fadir? Jerom sei&thorn;,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Jerom.</NOTE> &THORN;ei &thorn;at ordeyn of &thorn;er assessory in to prestis, and putten hem &thorn;er lif in to sclaundre of &thorn;e peple, &thorn;ei are gilty of &thorn;e vnfei&thorn;fulnes of hem &thorn;at are sclaundred. For so&thorn; &thorn;ei are chosun to &thorn;is to be prestis to &thorn;e peple, as &thorn;ei ordeynid befor to dignite, so &thorn;ey hau&yogh;t to schine be for in holines, ellis whi are &thorn;ei preferrid to o&thorn;er &thorn;at passun in grace of meritis. And &thorn;erfor sei&thorn; &thorn;e pope Symachus, He<NOTE PLACE="marg">Symachus.</NOTE> is to be countid most vile, &thorn;at is befor in dignite, but if he pre|celle in sciens and holines. &THORN;e Lord sei&thorn; bi &thorn;e prophet, for &thorn;u hast<NOTE PLACE="marg">Osee iu<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> putt a wey sciens, I schal put &thorn;e a wey &thorn;at &thorn;u vse not presthed to me. &THORN;e dede of &thorn;e bischop houwi&thorn; to passe a boue &thorn;e lif of &thorn;e peple, as &thorn;e lif of &thorn;e &yogh;erd transcendi&thorn; &thorn;e lif of &thorn;e schep, as Gregori sei&thorn;.<NOTE PLACE="marg">Gregori.</NOTE> And Bernard sei&thorn; to pope Eugeni, &THORN;i felawis bischops lere &thorn;ei at<NOTE PLACE="marg">Bernard.</NOTE> &thorn;e to haue not wi&thorn; hem childer so curhid, nor &yogh;eng men kembid or compert; certeyn it semi&thorn; not chapletid men to ren among &thorn;e mytrid vncorteysly; &thorn;of &thorn;u desire to be prest, or be befor to hem &thorn;at &thorn;u coueitist not to profi&yogh;t to, ouer proudly in coueiting subieccoun of hem, of &thorn;e wilk &thorn;u hernist not &thorn;ere &yogh;ele.</P>


</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="17" TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000124.tif" N="60">
<HEAD>XVII. A juge &yogh;e|uing a sen|tens a&yogh;en a innocent man, sin|nith dedly.</HEAD>
<P>&THORN;is is a no&thorn;er poynt: a juge &yogh;euing a sentens a&yogh;en a innocent man after allegiaunce and prouid, sinni&thorn; deadly. And me &thorn;inki&thorn; &thorn;at he synni&thorn;. And for to proue &thorn;at, I suppose &thorn;at he be innocent &thorn;at ha&thorn; not noyed; &thorn;e secound be &thorn;is supposid, &thorn;at juge is ordey|nid &thorn;at he sey and schew to &thorn;e folk &thorn;e ri&yogh;t, &thorn;at is wat ilk man howi&thorn; to haue or to &thorn;ole bi &thorn;e ri&yogh;t of God, and &thorn;at he discusse ri&yogh;tly and pronounce and witnes and schew to &thorn;e folk wat ilk man howi&thorn; to haue, and how to be punischid and to be lyuirid; &thorn;e &thorn;rid be &thorn;is supposid, &thorn;at noy&thorn;er &thorn;e deposing of &thorn;e witnes, nor &thorn;e entens &yogh;euing of &thorn;e juge, be it self maki&thorn; a &thorn;ing ri&yogh;tful originaly, nor maki&thorn; not man synful, ne wor&thorn;i to be dead; syn &thorn;ei are but schewars and witnessars: of &thorn;is was hed be for. And if &thorn;ei go not after &thorn;e trow&thorn; going bifor, but &thorn;er a&yogh;en, &thorn;an &thorn;er witnessing is fals, and &yogh;ifi&thorn; no ri&yogh;t. &THORN;is semi&thorn; bi &thorn;is, &thorn;at in mennis lawe oft men falsen domis, and appelen &thorn;er fro, and prouen a&yogh;en &thorn;e witnes. &THORN;an &thorn;us, as Isidor sei&thorn;, A iuge is seid for he diti&thorn; ri&yogh;t to &thorn;e peple, or<NOTE PLACE="marg">Isidor.</NOTE> discussi&thorn; ri&yogh;t; to discusse ri&yogh;t is to iuge ri&yogh;tly; to iuge ri&yogh;tly is to iuge after Goddis ri&yogh;t; for God is al ri&yogh;tfulnes in himseluen, and he is al mannis ri&yogh;tfulnes; sin mannis ri&yogh;tfulnes is but trow&thorn; directly vp on God, and ellis it is not ri&yogh;tfulnes, so he is no juge in whom is no justice or ri&yogh;tfulnes. And &thorn;an if he be not juge, he do&thorn; wrong in &thorn;is &thorn;at he synni&thorn; so iuging. But to iuge iustly is to iuge bi Goddis ri&yogh;t; for as &thorn;e fei&thorn; techi&thorn;, God is iuge of alle bo&thorn; quik and dead, and he is witnes, and he iugi&thorn; all &thorn;ingis iustly. And &thorn;us sei&thorn; Jamis, &thorn;at on is iuge and &yogh;euer of &thorn;e law, &thorn;at may<NOTE PLACE="marg">Jamis iu<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> bo&thorn; dampne and saue. And bi him kingis regnun, and makers of<NOTE PLACE="marg">Prov. uiij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> lawe discernen iust &thorn;ingis. And he ha&thorn; &yogh;euen to Ihu Crist &thorn;e sone<NOTE PLACE="marg">John u<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> al dome, and ha&thorn; &yogh;euen him power to mak and do dome, for he is mannis sone; &thorn;us ha&thorn; he &yogh;euen to him al dome, for he ha&thorn; &yogh;euen to him al manner of cause to ordeyn and discusse all &thorn;ingis, and to mend and punische all wrongis, and to susteyn and mend alle good &thorn;ingis. And &thorn;us schuld al domis be led bi him, and &thorn;us is it &yogh;euen 
<PB REF="00000125.tif" N="61"> to him &thorn;ow God ordeynd him not seculerly to execut seculer domis, as he sei&thorn;, &thorn;at he is not ordeind juge ne departar vp on men, ne<NOTE PLACE="marg">Luc. xij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> cum not to deme hem, ne to be cause of &thorn;er harme ne strif to be maad a mong hem. Neuer&thorn;eles al dome is &yogh;euen to him in maner be for seid, to be rewlid bi him, and he to discusse al &thorn;ingis. And for &thorn;is sei&thorn; Poule, &thorn;at Crist is end of &thorn;e lawe to ri&yogh;tfulnes to ilk<NOTE PLACE="marg">Rom. x<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> man trowing. As Austeyn sei&thorn;, Bo&thorn; of lawe of kind, and of<NOTE PLACE="marg">Austeyn.</NOTE> law writun, and law of grace, he is &thorn;e first begining al ri&yogh;t mad, he is &thorn;e midyl, end, ordeyning, and gouerning, he is endfully consuming and keping, and to wam al laws strekyn; and he kepi&thorn; in to lawfuly doing al &thorn;at go&thorn; bi him, and he is end of &thorn;e oolde lawe, filling and ending and avoyding after &thorn;at ri&yogh;twisnes axi&thorn;. And Poul sei&thorn;, &THORN;oo &thorn;at vnknawen &thorn;e ri&yogh;twisnes of God,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Rom. x<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> and seken to ordeyn ri&yogh;twissnes to hem, &thorn;ey are not soget to Goddis ri&yogh;twisnes. And &thorn;an are &thorn;ei proud apostatais and wrong doars. And Crist himsilf biddi&thorn; &thorn;us, Wel &yogh;e not deme, and &yogh;e schal not<NOTE PLACE="marg">Luc. uj<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> be demid; &thorn;at is, wyl &yogh;e not of &yogh;or silf mak domis, ne&thorn;er vse ani domis, not but as God schewi&thorn; to &yogh;ow to do, and os he wirki&thorn; be &yogh;owe; for o&thorn;er wis demi&thorn; not Crist &thorn;e sone, bi cause to ani man to be vndur syn, bondage, nor damping nor desese, nor do&thorn; wrong in ani dome, somoun or priuat, nor supprisi&thorn; nor eni&thorn; nor demi&thorn; not after &thorn;e face, but demi&thorn; iust dome. Be he fairar, be he strenger, &thorn;er schal be no distaunce of persoun, he schal &yogh;ere &thorn;e smale als wel as &thorn;e grete, and accept no mannis persoun, nor take no &yogh;eftis, for &thorn;e dome is Goddis; se&thorn; wat &yogh;e do, vse &yogh;e not &thorn;e dome to oftun but of God. And &yogh;e deme it schal turne a&yogh;en to &yogh;owr mede, if &yogh;e deme iustly. And &thorn;an if &yogh;e do wrong and syn, &thorn;e dred of God be wi&thorn; &yogh;owe, and do&thorn; all &thorn;ingis wi&thorn; diligence; at our Lord God is not accepting of personis, nor couetous of &yogh;eftis, nor wickidnes;<NOTE PLACE="marg">Exod. xxiij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> &yogh;e schal not tak &thorn;e vois of lesing, nor tak to hond to sey fals wit|nes for &thorn;e vnpitous, &thorn;u schal not folow &thorn;e rowt to do iuel, nor &thorn;u schalt not in dome folowe &thorn;e sentence of vile money, &thorn;at &thorn;u go a 
<PB REF="00000126.tif" N="62"> wey fro &thorn;e so&thorn;e; but iustly dome &thorn;i neibor, help him &thorn;at is sup|prisid, helpi&thorn; in &yogh;or dome to &thorn;e faderles and moderles, and defendi&thorn; &thorn;e widow; demi&thorn; not wickidnes, &thorn;at is to sey, helpi&thorn; it not vp, nor taki&thorn; not &thorn;e face of synnars, helpi&thorn; &thorn;e nedy and &thorn;e faderles, and maki&thorn; &thorn;e meke and &thorn;e pore to haue ri&yogh;t, and pulli&thorn; out and deliuer &thorn;e pore fro &thorn;e hand of &thorn;e synnar; if &thorn;er be ani cause to &thorn;e dome, enquere diligently &thorn;e so&thorn;, and wham &thorn;u seest iust, &yogh;ef him &thorn;e victory of ri&yogh;tfulnes, and wam &thorn;u fynd wickid &thorn;u schall condempne of vnpite. Now &thorn;an wan iugis gon in to &thorn;e contrary of &thorn;is, who schuld dowte &thorn;at &thorn;ei not syn in mani case and in mani a wise? And wan &yogh;e do not after God, ne after charite, nor hope, nor fei&thorn;; also wan &thorn;ei do not after his wisdam ne ordre, but gon biside reclesly, and enquiren not til &thorn;ey wit &thorn;e so&thorn;, as bo&thorn;e &thorn;e law of God and man teche&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;ey schuld; &thorn;e &thorn;rid, wan &thorn;e cause perteni&thorn; not to hem but to hiar iuge, but in ilk cause God schuld iuge befor, and o&thorn;er as he biddi&thorn; hem, and no for&thorn;er; for Poul sei&thorn;, Wat art &thorn;u<NOTE PLACE="marg">Rom. ij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> &thorn;at demist an o&thorn;er mannis seruaunt? &THORN;us wan jugis bowen fro &thorn;is, doutles &thorn;ei syn, and are reprouid of God, for &thorn;us sei&thorn; &thorn;e Salm, &thorn;u hast<NOTE PLACE="marg">Salm.</NOTE> dispicid al bouning doune fro &thorn;er domis, for &thorn;er &thorn;inking is vniust. And &thorn;erfor sei&thorn; Crist, &thorn;at &thorn;e Hooli Goost schal argu &thorn;is world of<NOTE PLACE="marg">Joh. xiu<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> dome, bo&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;ei mak and demen and causen; sin &thorn;e prince of &thorn;is world is demid and founden &thorn;at he is vniust, and &thorn;erfor is he put vnder, and man maad fre to serue God if he wil, and &thorn;an mai no man blam him iustly, nor he schal not be temptid ouer &thorn;at he<NOTE PLACE="marg">Cor. x<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> mai, but God schal make peruiaunce wi&thorn; &thorn;e temptacoun &thorn;at man may susteyn. And bi &thorn;e wise man; Here &yogh;e kingis and vnder|<NOTE PLACE="marg">Sap. uj<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> stondi&thorn;, and lere &yogh;e &thorn;e iugis of endis of &thorn;e world; &yogh;eftis &yogh;ere &yogh;e &thorn;at haldun to gidre, and plesun to &yogh;ou in routis of actouns; for power is &yogh;euen of God to &yogh;ou, and vertu of &thorn;e heiast, &thorn;at schal ask al &yogh;or dedis, and serch al &yogh;or &thorn;outis, for &yogh;e wse &thorn;e ministeris of his regn, &yogh;e iugid not ri&yogh;tly, nor kepid not &thorn;e law of ri&yogh;tfulnes, nor &yogh;ed not after &thorn;e wille of God; hedously and sone he schal apere to 
<PB REF="00000127.tif" N="63"> &yogh;ou; for hardist dome schal be don in hem &thorn;at are chefe. And for &thorn;is sei&thorn; Ysaie, Woo to hem &thorn;at maken wickid lawis, and writun<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ysa. x<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> writtis of vnritfulnes; &thorn;at &thorn;ei oppresse &thorn;e pore in dome, and don violence to &thorn;e cause of &thorn;e meke of my peple; &thorn;at veniaunce schuld be &thorn;er prey, and schuld snyb &thorn;e moderles, and iustifie &thorn;e wickid man for his &yogh;eftis, and take a wey &thorn;e ri&yogh;tfulnes of &thorn;e ri&yogh;tful man from him.</P>
<P>Nor &thorn;is excusi&thorn; not to sey, &thorn;at he demi&thorn; after &thorn;e lawe, and do&thorn; no &thorn;ing aftur his oune arbitracoun, but obeyschi&thorn; to &thorn;e lawe, as seynt Ambrose sei&thorn;, and so he do&thorn; to his knowing as far as man<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ambrose.</NOTE> may knowe, he may not know as God. &THORN;is excusi&thorn; not; for Poul<NOTE PLACE="marg">Rom. xiu<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> sei&thorn;, &thorn;at ilk &thorn;ing &thorn;at is not of &thorn;e fei&thorn; is synne; and ilk &thorn;ing &thorn;at is not of God, nor bi him, nor in him, is synne; also he sei&thorn;, law is not but to &thorn;e iust man, &thorn;at is to sey to punische him, but ra&thorn;er to susteyn him, and rewle him in ri&yogh;tfulnes, and to punisch mis|doars, and to swilk lauis and to swilk maneris schuld ilk iuge obey, and do &thorn;erby, and no &thorn;ing biside of his oune wille, nor no &thorn;ing falsly, nor be fals lawis, nor be error, is not he excusable; sin Daniel sei&thorn; &thorn;us: Sey &yogh;e sonis of Israel folis, noi&thorn;er knowing nor<NOTE PLACE="marg">Dan. xiij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> deming &thorn;ing &thorn;at is verrey, turni&thorn; a&yogh;en to &thorn;e dome, and I schal deme hem wisely, for &thorn;ei han seid fals witnes a&yogh;enis her. In wilk is to be notid wel, &thorn;at fals dome may be reuokid, and &thorn;o iugis not<NOTE PLACE="marg">Nota.</NOTE> excusid, bi &thorn;er witnes, but more gilty for wickid consent; and in &thorn;is &thorn;ei consent, &thorn;at &thorn;ei werk wickidly; for &thorn;e man schal not vndir go &thorn;e peyn, befor &thorn;at &thorn;e juge &yogh;eft &thorn;e dome; nor it helpi&thorn; not to sey &thorn;at he schal be excusid bi &thorn;is, &thorn;at God sei&thorn;, &thorn;at ilk word schal stond in &thorn;e mou&thorn; of two or of &thorn;re, for &thorn;at may not implye &thorn;at al &thorn;ing is so&thorn;e for &thorn;ey sey it, but it is seid for &thorn;is, &thorn;at no man schal be condempnid bi on seying witnes a&yogh;en him, os &thorn;e scripture de|clari&thorn; itsilf. And &thorn;us sei&thorn; Crist, &yogh;e erre mikil, not knowing &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">Matt.xxij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> writingis, ne &thorn;e vertu of God; &thorn;erfor bi &thorn;e vertu of God clere knowing of ilk &thorn;ing, and be for men know a &thorn;ing, bi &thorn;at men know 
<PB REF="00000128.tif" N="64"> it not, as Gregori witnessi&thorn;, for he sei&thorn;, &thorn;at men know not a &thorn;ing<NOTE PLACE="marg">Gregori.</NOTE> bifor &thorn;at he know it be fei&thorn;; &thorn;erfor as God &yogh;eui&thorn; knowing, and techi&thorn; al profitable &thorn;ingis, and enformi&thorn; alle and ledi&thorn; hem, for al abel are tau&yogh;t of God, so &thorn;at man schal not stond only in &thorn;e teching of man, but in teching of God a boun man, and &thorn;an he schal vnderstond a boun his enemies, and ouer his techars, and ouer &thorn;e hold, as &thorn;e Salm sei&thorn;, and now God &yogh;eui&thorn; his lawe in &thorn;e hertis of<NOTE PLACE="marg">Salm. cxuiij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> men, and writi&thorn; it in &thorn;er bowelis, and not wi&thorn; enk, ne parchemyn,<NOTE PLACE="marg">2 Cor. iij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> but wi&thorn; &thorn;e Spirit of God, and kenni&thorn; hem in al &thorn;ingis, os &thorn;e prophet sei&thorn;, and Jon in his epistil, nor for&yogh;eti&thorn; hem not in tyme, nor<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Joh. iij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> confoundi&thorn; hem, so schuld he &thorn;e jugis, if &thorn;ei bowid not from him, nor he schuld not fail to hem nowe ne more &thorn;an he dede to Salo|mon, and o&thorn;er iugis. But now for men lefun, and don domis, and not bi his Spirit, nor do not bi his counseil, but regnun and not of him, but gon bi o&thorn;er weyes, &thorn;erfor &thorn;er oune findingis begon hem aboute, and bi gernyn hem &thorn;at &thorn;ey may not out, and &thorn;ey bigilun o&thorn;er men. Nor sey &thorn;u not &thorn;at bi &thorn;is ani law mi&yogh;t not stond, nor no domis and polycye were for done, and misdoars schuld not be punischid: &thorn;is is not so&thorn;; but bi &thorn;is schuld law be stablid, and ilk man schuld be suget as God biddi&thorn;, and ilk man schuld do ri&yogh;t to o&thorn;er, and iust men schuld be holden in ri&yogh;t, and schrewis schuld be punischid as ri&yogh;t axi&thorn;, and mikil bettar &thorn;an &thorn;ei are now; for as God biddi&thorn; &thorn;eis &thorn;ingis to be don, so schuld he &yogh;ef bo&thorn;e witt and wille and mi&yogh;t &thorn;erto; and mikil bettar it schuld be &thorn;an is nowe, for now are iust men oft wrongid, and schrewis vnpunischid, and maynteynd, and born vp in iuel, bo&thorn; bi wilis, and streng&thorn;, and falsnes, and fayntise of &thorn;eis &thorn;at schuld do ri&yogh;t; and &thorn;us synne is aggregid mani fold, and if ani haue good &thorn;er by &thorn;er falli&thorn; vp on an o&thorn;er side to mak harmis.</P>
<P>And if &thorn;u sey, it semi&thorn; &thorn;at man may juge a&yogh;en &thorn;e innocent, bi &thorn;is God himsilf condempni&thorn; bo&thorn; &thorn;e iust and vnpitouse, and Crist &yogh;af himsilf to &thorn;e de&thorn;. And Abraham is blessid of God, for he was 
<PB REF="00000129.tif" N="65"> redy to sle his sone. And Sampson slow himsilf in sleyng of &thorn;e Philisteis, and so do&thorn; mani o&thorn;er and mani wise. Also Dauid slow<NOTE PLACE="marg">2 Reg. i<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> a man, for he seid &thorn;at he had slayn a man, and slow him not. And &thorn;us bi &thorn;eis it semi&thorn; &thorn;at man may &yogh;eue sentence &yogh;ea to sle &thorn;e innocent. To &thorn;eis obieccouns me semi&thorn; &thorn;us; God may do what<NOTE PLACE="marg">Responsio ad object.</NOTE> he wel, and &thorn;erfor in sum &thorn;ingis it is not inow to vs, God do&thorn; &thorn;us, &thorn;erfor we mai do &thorn;us; but do we as he biddi&thorn; us, for &thorn;us sei&thorn; Crist, &yogh;e cal me lord and mayster, and &yogh;e sey wel, forso&thorn; I am,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Joh. iiij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> but wil not &yogh;e be callid maisteris. Also he condampni&thorn; in o&thorn;er maneris, as wan he &thorn;oli&thorn; &thorn;e creature to falle in to synne, or ellis in to peyn; &thorn;e secound, wan he ordeynit ani to be punischid or con|dempnid; &thorn;e &thorn;rid, wen he schewi&thorn; &thorn;e gretnes of his wisdam, power, goodnes, mercy, paciens, be wilk he schewi&thorn; &thorn;at alle crea|turs in regard are not, nor wor&thorn;i to appere in his si&yogh;t. And bi &thorn;is &thorn;ei schuld be confoundid in hem silf, and leue al hemsilf, and folow him, and stond in his grace, and &thorn;us mend. Blessid be &thorn;is confu|sioun and dampning; and so &yogh;ef God bed condempne, or &yogh;eue sentence, wirk fast as God biddi&thorn;, but it is in veyn to go be for. And for so&thorn; of Abram it is opun &thorn;at he was not in wil to sle his sone, not but after &thorn;e bidding of God, and &thorn;erfor cam God befor and bad him sle not &thorn;e child, and for &thorn;is wil he blessid him; and in &thorn;is he techi&thorn; &thorn;at his wil is not &thorn;e ded of man &thorn;at is innocent,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ezek. xxxiij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> for he sei&thorn; &thorn;at he wel not &thorn;e de&thorn; of &thorn;e synnar, if he wil turne and lif, as he sei&thorn; bi &thorn;e prophet. And in &thorn;is he schewi&thorn; vs how he wil cum befor to saue &thorn;eis &thorn;at tristun in him, and do&thorn; in simple hert and purte of handis. And of Sampson men seyn &thorn;at o&thorn;er he hadde bidding of God, or repentid ofter. And os to Dauid, men seyn &thorn;at alle his dedis are not to be folowid, wi&thorn; out mikil auto|rite; nor &thorn;is man was not innocent in &thorn;e si&yogh;t of God, for he went to haue plesid Dauid wi&thorn; &thorn;e sleyng, and for his lyeing he was manslear. And &thorn;us Dauid, led bi &thorn;e priuete of prophecye, dede &thorn;e dome of God to him, schewing to vs how God demi&thorn; vs after 
<PB REF="00000130.tif" N="66"> our hartis, and schal deme ilk man after &thorn;e wordis of his mow&thorn;. And &thorn;erfor men schuld be warer &thorn;at &thorn;ei lere not, nor sey not &thorn;at &thorn;ey wet a &thorn;ing to be &thorn;at is not; for &thorn;an schal God condempne hem of &thorn;er own mow&thorn;, wen &thorn;e &thorn;ing mai not be prouid, wan nor were &thorn;at it was don, as Daniel did &thorn;e prestis; for &thorn;is wil be at &thorn;e day<NOTE PLACE="marg">Dan. xiij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> wen al &thorn;ing schal be demid after trow&thorn;. And her be howuen &thorn;ei be war &thorn;at are chargid to sey &thorn;e so&thorn;e to &thorn;er witing. And wen o&thorn;er seyn a&yogh;en &thorn;er witing, &thorn;ei holde hem stille, and &thorn;olun &thorn;e to&thorn;er to &yogh;eue &thorn;e dome, and &thorn;us &thorn;ei are for sworne, and cause of &thorn;e mannis harme &thorn;at &thorn;ei schuld leit os &thorn;ei are sworne to do. And error excusi&thorn; not, os is schewid oft, nor vnkunning; sin Balaam<NOTE PLACE="marg">Num.xxij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> seid to aungel, I haue synnid, not witing &thorn;at &thorn;u stod a&yogh;en me; and in &thorn;e law was bidun &thorn;at if ani synnid bi error or vnkunning,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Lev. vij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> and did ani &thorn;ing &thorn;at &thorn;e law forbed, &thorn;at he schuld mak an ofring, and &thorn;e prest schuld pray for him, and it schuld be for &yogh;euen him, for he fautid be error and be vnkunning.</P>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="18" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XVIII. A prest assoil|ing a feynar sinnith.</HEAD>
<P>An o&thorn;er poynt is &thorn;is; a prest assoiling a feyner synni&thorn; deadly. So&thorn;ly me semi&thorn; &thorn;at he synni&thorn;, for if he soile him neligently, &thorn;ow God asoyle him not, me semi&thorn; he synni&thorn; greuously, we&thorn;er a presum, as autor, to assoile him, and bring him out of sin of peyn, or to mak him fre &thorn;erof; whe&thorn;er he denounce him so as a minster, or he hi&yogh;t him &thorn;at God do&thorn; so; we&thorn;er he do it of luf, or hat, or drede, or o&thorn;er vniust or vnordinat cause; we&thorn;er he do it vnwysly, reclesly, or bi error, or be vniust ordre or maner, and wen &thorn;e cause perteni&thorn; not to him, for he schuld send him to his soueren. And &thorn;us wyle he reformi&thorn; not &thorn;is man to lefe &thorn;is syne, nor to mak a mendis &thorn;erfor, as he schuld, and ellis telle him &thorn;at he mai not asoyle him, he synni&thorn;, and namli, wan &thorn;e man tresti&thorn; of &thorn;is absolu|coun, wening him siker, and contuni&thorn; for&thorn;, and mendi&thorn; not, os he schuld, if &thorn;e prest refusid him as he au&yogh;t, for &thorn;an he wold schame, and dred, and mend. And in &thorn;is defaut is be gilid, and &thorn;e prest beri&thorn; fals witnes, and sei&thorn; him to wit and do &thorn;ing &thorn;at he noi&thorn;er 
<PB REF="00000131.tif" N="67"> wot nor do&thorn;, and refi&thorn; God his regaly, and maki&thorn; &thorn;e man to tryst in lesing, and so do sacrifice to &thorn;e fend. Of swilk prestis God pleyni&thorn; &thorn;us bi &thorn;e prophet Ezechiel, Who wor&thorn; &thorn;eis &thorn;at sewen<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ezech. xijj<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> cursing vnder &thorn;e hewow of iwan, and maken pillewor&thorn;is vnder &thorn;e hedis of ilk age, for to tak soulis; and wan &thorn;ei tuk &thorn;e soulis of mi peple, &thorn;ei quikynd &thorn;er soulis, and foilid me to mi peple, for an hanful of barly, and on gobe&thorn; of bred, &thorn;at schuld sle soulis &thorn;at dien not, and quiken soulis &thorn;at lyuen [not]; lying to my peple, trowing to lesingis; &thorn;erfor sei&thorn; &thorn;e Lord, lo I to &yogh;or cursing be wilk &yogh;e tak soulis fleing, and I schal reue hem fro &yogh;or armis, and &thorn;e souls &thorn;at &yogh;e tak I schal to fli&yogh;t; and I schal reue &yogh;or quyschinis, and liuer my peple fro &yogh;our hand, &thorn;ei schal no more be in &yogh;our handis to robbe; and &yogh;e schal wit for I be Lord. For &thorn;at &yogh;e lyingly han maad &thorn;e hertis of &thorn;e iust man to be euy, wam I euid not, and han comfortid &thorn;e hert of &thorn;e vnpitous, &thorn;at he turnid not from his iuel wey and lyue, &thorn;erfor he schal no lengar see veyn &thorn;ingis nor deueyn lesing. And vpon &thorn;is sei&thorn; Gregor &thorn;us, Oft it falli&thorn; &thorn;at he haldi&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="marg">Gregor.</NOTE> &thorn;e sted of a iuge, to wam &thorn;e lif a cordi&thorn; not. And is don oft &thorn;at o&thorn;er he dampni&thorn; &thorn;e vnwor&thorn;i, or louse o&thorn;er &thorn;at are bound; and oft he folowi&thorn; his steringis, and not &thorn;e meritis of causis in sugetis to be lousid or bound. And &thorn;us is don &thorn;at he priue himsilf power of bynding and lowsing, &thorn;at vsi&thorn; it after his lustis, and not after meritis of sugetis. Oft is don &thorn;at &thorn;e hirid be sterid a&yogh;en his ne&yogh;|bor bi hat or grace, and &thorn;erfor &thorn;ei may not iuge ritly of &thorn;er sugetis &thorn;at in &thorn;er causis folawen hat or grace; werfor rit is seid bi &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ezek. xiij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> prophet, &thorn;ey quikid soulis &thorn;at liuid not, and slen &thorn;e soulis &thorn;at died not; forso&thorn; he sle&thorn; him &thorn;at die&thorn; not, &thorn;at dampni&thorn; &thorn;e iust man; and he enforci&thorn; to quiken him &thorn;at liui&thorn; not, &thorn;at enforci&thorn; to asoyle fro torment him &thorn;at dwelli&thorn; in his gilt. &THORN;erfor &thorn;e causis are to be peysid, and &thorn;an power of bynding and soiling is to be vsid; &thorn;erfor it is to see wat synne went be forn, and wat for&thorn;inging folowi&thorn; after &thorn;e synne; &thorn;at &thorn;e sentens of &thorn;e chepherd asoile &thorn;eis 
<PB REF="00000132.tif" N="68"> &thorn;at Almi&yogh;ty God visiti&thorn; bi for bi grace of compunccoun. For &thorn;an is &thorn;e asoiling of &thorn;e president verrey, wen it folowi&thorn; &thorn;e dome of &thorn;e innar juge. &THORN;at &thorn;ei reysing of La&yogh;ar fowr daies dead tokuni&thorn; wel and schewi&thorn;, for first &thorn;e Lord reysid and sterid and quiknid &thorn;e dead man, seying, La&yogh;ar cum for&thorn;e, and after he &thorn;at was bounden<NOTE PLACE="marg">Joh. xi<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> &yogh;ed out, and was lowsid of &thorn;e disciplis, as is writun, wan he was gon out &thorn;at was bound wi&thorn; bondis, &thorn;an seid Ihu to his disciplis, Vnbyndi&thorn; him, and lat him go. Lo &thorn;e disciplis lowsid him liuing, wam dead &thorn;e maister had reisid; for if &thorn;e disciplis had lowsid him dead, &thorn;ei schuld schew more stynk &thorn;an vertewe. Of wilk consi|deracoun it is to see, &thorn;at we owe to lowse bi autorite of herd wam we know our autor to haue quicknid be grace resing. And so &thorn;e dead man cum out, &thorn;e synnar knowleche his synne; &thorn;e disciplis lowse &thorn;e comar out, for &thorn;e schepherdis of &thorn;e kirk owe to moue to him &thorn;e penaunce &thorn;at he deserui&thorn;, &thorn;at lettid not for schame to knowleche &thorn;at he dede. &THORN;is haue we seid schortly of &thorn;e wordre of lowsing, &thorn;at schepherdis of &thorn;e kirk ow to bind and lowse vnder gret moderacoun. &THORN;is sei&thorn; Gregor. And &thorn;us sei&thorn; Bede; Now is<NOTE PLACE="marg">Bede.</NOTE> &thorn;is office committid in bischopis and prestis of &thorn;e kirk, &thorn;at &thorn;e causis of &thorn;e synnars knowen, &thorn;ei doing mercy assoyle hem fro &thorn;e dred of perpetual de&thorn;, wen &thorn;ei able and verrey repentaunt; and &thorn;at he schewe hem to be bound wi&thorn; ai lasting tormentis, &thorn;at he knawi&thorn; to stond tou&yogh;ly in &thorn;er synnis &thorn;at &thorn;ei han don. And to &thorn;is acorden mani o&thorn;er seingis of doctors and decreis of &thorn;e kirk; &thorn;erfor be &thorn;ei ware &thorn;at asoylun feynars &thorn;at God forbedi&thorn; to asoyle for harmis &thorn;at folowen; for &thorn;us sei&thorn; God bi &thorn;e prophet E&yogh;echiel, A<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ezech. xiu<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> man of &thorn;e house of Israel, &thorn;at ha&thorn; sett his vnclennes in his hert, and ha&thorn; set of his wickidnes a&yogh;ens his face, and comi&thorn; to &thorn;e prophet, asking me bi him, I &thorn;e Lord schal ansuere to him in &thorn;e multitude of his vnclennes, &thorn;at &thorn;e hous of Israel be tan in &thorn;er hert, in wilk &thorn;ei han gon a wey fro me, in al &thorn;er idols. &THORN;erfor be &yogh;e turnid, and departi&thorn; fro alle &yogh;our idols, and turni&thorn; awey &yogh;our facis fro al &yogh;our 
<PB REF="00000133.tif" N="69"> folthis; for &thorn;e man wat euer he be &thorn;at be alienid fro me, and sett his idols in his hert, and &thorn;e sclaunder of his wickidnesse a&yogh;en his face, and cum to &thorn;e prophet &thorn;at he aske me bi him, I &thorn;e Lord schal answere him bi my self, and I schal sett mi face vp on &thorn;at man, and mak him in to prouerb and ensaumple, and schal scater him fro &thorn;e middis of my peple; and &thorn;e prophet wan he schal erre in speche of word, I &thorn;e Lord haue ben fro him, and he schal bere his wickydnes; after &thorn;e wickydnes of &thorn;e ascar schal be &thorn;e wickidnes of &thorn;e prophet; and I schal streke out my hand on him, and do him a wey fro &thorn;e middis of mi peple; &thorn;at &thorn;e house of Israel erre no more fro me, but be mi peple, and I &thorn;er God; and &thorn;at &thorn;ei be no more polutid in all &thorn;er trespasses. By &thorn;is man is vnderstondyn feynar &thorn;at is fals, and lufi&thorn; his synne, and sei&thorn; he wel forsak it and lie&thorn;, and cumi&thorn; to &thorn;e prest to be asoylid, and to ask mercy. But wan &thorn;e prest erri&thorn;, and behyti&thorn; suelk an absolucoun a&yogh;en &thorn;e bid|ding of God, he schal bere &thorn;e wickidnes wi&thorn; &thorn;e synnar; for &thorn;i &thorn;at he is cause &thorn;at &thorn;e synnar contuni&thorn; in his iuel, and mendi&thorn; nout, os he schuld, if &thorn;e prest putt him be syd til &thorn;at he be mendid. To &thorn;is sentens acordi&thorn; Seynt Ambrose, as is put in decreis, wer he<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ambrose.</NOTE> sei&thorn; &thorn;us; If ani man be mouid bi prayors of sonis, or teris of &thorn;e wif, and wen him to be soylid, to wam &thorn;e affeccoun of steyling biddi&thorn; &yogh;et, schal he not be tak innocentis to distruccoun, &thorn;at ben fre &thorn;at &thorn;enkun to distroy many? Forso&thorn; if he lay doun &thorn;e suerd, or lousi&thorn; &thorn;e bondis, he opuni&thorn; &thorn;e distroyingis. Wy pulli&thorn; he not a wey, in &thorn;e mekist wey &thorn;at he may, faculte of steyling, &thorn;at mi&yogh;t not bow &thorn;e wille? Also bi twix two, &thorn;at is &thorn;e accuser and &thorn;e gilty, striuing of euen perel of &thorn;e hed, &thorn;e ton if he had not prouid, &thorn;e to&thorn;er if he were conuictid of &thorn;e accusing, if &thorn;e iuge folow not &thorn;is &thorn;at is of ri&yogh;tfulnes, but ha&thorn; mercy of &thorn;e to&thorn;er, oi&thorn;er he schal dampne &thorn;e prouar, or til he fauor &thorn;e accusar, &thorn;at mi&yogh;t not proue, schal iuge &thorn;e vngilty; &thorn;is mai not be seid iust mercy. In &thorn;at kirk wer ani owe to do mercy, and how most to be holden in &thorn;e forme 
<PB REF="00000134.tif" N="70"> of ri&yogh;tfulnes, &thorn;at non draw a wey fro &thorn;e comyn of fei&thorn;fulmen, get wrongly, of &thorn;e li&yogh;tnes of &thorn;e prest, comyn wi&thorn; schort ter and dred|ful, a tyme &thorn;at he ow to axe wi&thorn; mo tymis and plentiuous teris. We&thorn;er not wan he for&yogh;eui&thorn; &thorn;e vnwor&thorn;y, he prouoci&thorn; al to &thorn;e smit of falling; li&yogh;tnes of &yogh;euing &yogh;eui&thorn; kyndling of trespassing. &THORN;is sei&thorn; Ambrose. &THORN;e prest may wit &thorn;at he ha&thorn; not power to soyl, but as God &yogh;eui&thorn; him bidding; but God sei&thorn; &thorn;us, If &thorn;i bro&thorn;er synne,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Matt. xuiij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> blame him; and if he leue his synne, leue &thorn;u to blam him, and if [he] wil not leue his syn, proced for&thorn; a&yogh;en him bifor witness. And if he wyl not her &yogh;owe, be he &thorn;an to &thorn;e as a he&thorn;en or publi|can. And wam &thorn;at &yogh;e &thorn;us bynd, schal be bound, and wam &thorn;at &yogh;e bring out of synne, &thorn;e peyn schal be for&yogh;euen hem. He biddi&thorn; not here to curse him &thorn;at synni&thorn; not, nor to asoyle him &thorn;at bidi&thorn; in synne; but a&yogh;enword to asoile him &thorn;at leui&thorn; his synne, and put him out of cumpany &thorn;at lasti&thorn; in his synne.</P>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="19" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XIX. Ma|riage mad in third degre.</HEAD>
<P>An no&thorn;er is &thorn;is, &thorn;at mariage mad in &thorn;rid and ferd degre, a&yogh;en &thorn;e ordinaunce of &thorn;e kirk, is rate and stable. And to &thorn;is I haue seid, &thorn;at it is so confermid &thorn;at it mai not be departid; &thorn;e man to wed ani o&thorn;er woman, wyle &thorn;at sche lyui&thorn;, nor scho to be weddid to ani o&thorn;er man. And &thorn;is semi&thorn; me prouable &thorn;us; we&thorn; &thorn;e lefe or conferming of &thorn;e kirk, swilk mariage is rate, &thorn;an it is rate or stable; and &thorn;e kirk mi&yogh;t not ratifie it, but if it be first ratified of God; and if it be ratified of God, &thorn;an &thorn;e kirk mai not depart it, for no man may depart &thorn;e &thorn;ing &thorn;at God ha&thorn; joinid. And as men seyn &thorn;e ratifying of &thorn;e pope, or of &thorn;e kirk, is a chaunging &thorn;at God ha&thorn; ordeynd to be don, and if &thorn;is mariage were a&yogh;en &thorn;e bidding of God, &thorn;an &thorn;e conferming of &thorn;e kirk were not wor&thorn;, nor &thorn;ei mi&yogh;t not &yogh;eue leue &thorn;er to; for &thorn;ei mai not &yogh;eue leue to breke &thorn;e bidding of God, nor leeue a man to lyue in ani degre a&yogh;en &thorn;e bidding of God, nor charge him &thorn;er to. Now &thorn;e decre sei&thorn; &thorn;us; &THORN;e wedding<NOTE PLACE="marg">Decre.</NOTE> of prestis, or of cosynis in &thorn;e &thorn;rid or ferd degre, is not forfendid bi &thorn;e autorite of &thorn;e oolde lawe, nor bi &thorn;e autorite of &thorn;e gospel, nor 
<PB REF="00000135.tif" N="71"> of &thorn;e epistil, but it is only defendid bi law of &thorn;e kirk. And after sei&thorn; &thorn;e decre, &thorn;ow &thorn;e apostil addid sum &thorn;ingis counseyling, &thorn;at<NOTE PLACE="marg">Decre.</NOTE> were [not] found in bidding of &thorn;e gospel diffinid, &thorn;erfor [nei&thorn;er] &thorn;ey are putt a wey of &thorn;e to&thorn;er apostols as foly or superflu; so and &thorn;e kirk, after &thorn;e statutis of &thorn;e apostil, ha&thorn; addid sum &thorn;ingis of counseil of perfeccoun, os of continence of prestis, and of making of goostly misteris, of &thorn;e synging of officis, &thorn;at no wey are to be put a wey, but to be tan wi&thorn; diligent worschip; &thorn;erfor &thorn;e wed|dingis of cosyns, &thorn;ow &thorn;ei be not found for bidyn bi &thorn;e gospel, nor bi &thorn;e pistel, neuer&thorn;eles &thorn;ei are to be fled, for &thorn;ei are forbydun bi &thorn;e ordinaunce of &thorn;e kirke. &THORN;is sei&thorn; &thorn;e decre. And so I graunt &thorn;at it is good to kep fro hem, but neuer&thorn;eles me semi&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;ei mai not be departid, wen &thorn;ei are maad, not but in swilk degre os God leeui&thorn; not to bide to gidre, and &thorn;at is no matrimone. But in &thorn;is &thorn;e decre sei&thorn;, &thorn;eis &thorn;at are found weddid in &thorn;eis degrees, and wi&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="marg">Decre.</NOTE> in schort tyme done, be &thorn;ei departid; &yogh;et &thorn;e decre leeui&thorn; not a man to wed an o&thorn;er, nor &thorn;e woman noi&thorn;er, wil &thorn;ey two lyuen. And so if &thorn;e kirk wil not suffur &thorn;is man and woman dwel to gidre, what may &thorn;ey do, but ei&thorn;er dwel stille bi hem silue, til &thorn;ei may fynd better grace, and tak &thorn;e certayn and leue &thorn;e vncerteyn, &thorn;at &thorn;ei synne not a&yogh;en God, and abid til &thorn;ei be formid wi&thorn; holy writ, how hem is best to do? And if ani sey matrimoyn to be leful in &thorn;eis degreis, speki&thorn; a&yogh;en &thorn;e Fadre and Sone and Holy Goost, be &thorn;u ware; for &thorn;e pope and &thorn;e kirk sei&thorn; &thorn;at it is leful wen &thorn;ei leefe it, solempni&yogh;e it, confermi&thorn; and approui&thorn; it.</P>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="20" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XX. The kirk so|lempni|zing matri|moyn in degre for|biden er|rith.</HEAD>
<P>&THORN;is is a no&thorn;er, &thorn;at &thorn;e kirk solempni&yogh;ing matrimoyn in degre forbiden erri&thorn;, consenting to synne, as it semi&thorn;, and autori&yogh;ing synne. &THORN;is semi&thorn; so&thorn; bi &thorn;is: Matrimoyn of cosyns in &thorn;rid and ford degre is not forbiden, not but bi &thorn;e kirk; and so it is no synne, not but &thorn;er forbedyng; and as Poul sei&thorn;, Were is not lawe, &thorn;er is not breking of lawe, and eft he sei&thorn;, If I bigge ageyn &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ro. v<SUP>o</SUP>. Gal. ij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> &thorn;ing &thorn;at I ding doun, I mak mesilfe a trespasor; and bi &thorn;e same 
<PB REF="00000136.tif" N="72"> resoun, if &thorn;e kirk, wi&thorn; out oole autorite, solempni&yogh;e matrimoyn forbidun of &thorn;e general kirk, &thorn;is kirk &thorn;at &thorn;us solempni&yogh;i&thorn; synni&thorn;, &yogh;he a&yogh;en &thorn;e ordinaunce, and so a&yogh;en God, in als mikil as it do&thorn; a&yogh;en Goddis wille in &thorn;at ordinaunce. And if &thorn;at mariage is maad only but in autorite of &thorn;e kirk, and neuer&thorn;eles is no very mariage, but synne vp on ilk side, in &thorn;e making and in &thorn;e holding, it semi&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;us &thorn;is kirk is autor of &thorn;is, and bi &thorn;us mykil &thorn;e makar at [as?] &thorn;e kirk maki&thorn; lawis; and schuld wern men &thorn;er of, &thorn;at &thorn;ei offendid not &thorn;er in, and felle in to synne. And sin &thorn;ei wern not men as &thorn;ei schuld, &thorn;ei are cause of &thorn;e fallyng of o&thorn;er men, and &thorn;at blud schal be sout out of &thorn;er hand; as God sei&thorn; bi &thorn;e prophet, Son of man, if<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ezek. iij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> &thorn;u schewe not to my peple &thorn;at &thorn;ei be ware, &thorn;ei schal falle in &thorn;er wickidnes, and I schal seke &thorn;er blude of &thorn;in hand. &THORN;erfor be ware of making of mariagis, and of diuorsis, or departingis; for &thorn;is &thorn;ing is so&thorn;, &thorn;at no man may depart &thorn;e &thorn;ing &thorn;at God ha&thorn; jonid, no man may joyn, but if &thorn;at God joyn bi forn; forso&thorn;, as &thorn;e doctor sei&thorn;,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Doctor.</NOTE> In ilk bodily mariage is vnderstond a goostly mariage, wilk &thorn;e bodily copling performi&thorn;. And of &thorn;eis bodily weddingis are &thorn;re good &thorn;ingis, os Austeyn sei&thorn;, fei&thorn;, entent to bring for&thorn; barnis, and<NOTE PLACE="marg">Austeyn.</NOTE> &thorn;e sacrament of mariage. And hard it were to depart &thorn;is mariage &thorn;us maad. And for &thorn;is are &thorn;e bannis askid bi fore, to warn men to fle in weddingis couetous lustis, and pride, and swilk o&thorn;er vices vnpertinent to &thorn;e mariage. And &thorn;us schuld men be warnid in wat degre &thorn;ei mai not cum to gidre, and how &thorn;ei schuld be fei&thorn;ful, and lif honestly and holyly to gidre, in on entent to bring for&thorn; barnes. And for &thorn;e kirk do&thorn; not &thorn;is, and oft solempni&yogh;i&thorn; matri|moynis &thorn;at are maad for lust, and be &thorn;wen &thorn;eis &thorn;at knowen hem silf vnable to bring for&thorn; frut, in &thorn;eis cases it semi&thorn; &thorn;e kirk consenti&thorn; to synne. And also in &thorn;eis &thorn;at are solempni&yogh;id, and after departid, for &thorn;at &thorn;ei were not jonid bi God; for dowtles ilk &thorn;ing &thorn;at is not of &thorn;e fei&thorn; is synne, as Poul sei&thorn;. And it is but foly to sey &thorn;at ani<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ro. xiu<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> erri&thorn; in doing a&yogh;en &thorn;e bidding of God, and synni&thorn; not, for Crist 
<PB REF="00000137.tif" N="73"> himsilf reproui&thorn; hem &thorn;at erren vnknowing &thorn;e scripture and &thorn;e vertu of God.</P>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="21" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XXI. Law canoun contrary to God's law. Decretests. Egipcyans. Goddis law blasfemid.</HEAD>
<P>An o&thorn;er poynt is &thorn;is; &thorn;at law canoun is contrary to Goddis lawe, and &thorn;at decretistis, as to &thorn;at part of wysdam &thorn;at &thorn;ei haue of &thorn;e worldis wisdam, are Egipciens. And &thorn;at bi sciens of canoun holy writ is blasfemid, &yogh;he God himsilf, &thorn;at is &thorn;e lawe &yogh;efar. And &thorn;at it were nede &thorn;is sciens as kaf for gret part to be clensid out of &thorn;e chirche. In &thorn;eis &thorn;ingis I knowleche &thorn;at I haue rehersid &thorn;e seyngis of doctoris, Parisiens and o&thorn;er. Of &thorn;e wilk on sei&thorn; &thorn;us,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Parisiens.</NOTE> &thorn;e lawe to be contrary to &thorn;e gospel moraly, wan it is not wi&thorn; it to help to &thorn;e perfeccoun of &thorn;ing &thorn;at &thorn;e gospel schewi&thorn; and biddi&thorn; to be done, but in ani maner is &thorn;er a&yogh;en, in ani tyme, for ani cause letting or troubling, or tarying after &thorn;e sentence of Crist, &thorn;at sei&thorn;,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Matt. xij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> he &thorn;at is not wi&thorn; me, he is a&yogh;ens me, and he &thorn;at gedre&thorn; not wi&thorn; me, he sckateri&thorn; a brod. And so, syn &thorn;e law of &thorn;e gospel is cha|rite, ri&yogh;tfulnes, trou&thorn;, euenhed, mercy, clennes, and pes of God, were &thorn;at ani law in ani maner helpi&thorn; not &thorn;is, but to strif and debat, to wrong, prid, and lust, and to swilk o&thorn;er, dowtles it is a&yogh;en &thorn;e lawe of God. Goddis law is ri&yogh;t ordeynd be God alone, explanid bi Crist in word and dede, as law of &thorn;e gospel; and &thorn;us law of &thorn;e gospel is callid multitud of trew&thorn;is &thorn;at Crist ha&thorn; tawt, namli, to rewle his peple; law canoun is callid law ordeynid of prelats of &thorn;e kirk, and pronounce to constreyn rebell bi holy rewl, and it may be vnderstondyn as &thorn;ei ben contrari to &thorn;e lawe of &thorn;e gospel, as are many decretal epistlis, and generaly alle &thorn;e tradicouns of &thorn;e dowing of &thorn;e kirk fro &thorn;e tyme of Constantyn; or as &thorn;ey comoun to &thorn;e law of &thorn;e gospel os articlis of &thorn;e fei&thorn;, in holy seyno&yogh;is and counseils, for os man is &thorn;e same in clo&thorn;is and deedis, bringing in knowing, so &thorn;e sam is &thorn;e law or trow&thorn; of &thorn;e gospel inpli&yogh;ed or opunid bi &thorn;e kirk after ward, o&thorn;er wise, but not contrari, explanit. As it semi&thorn; bi &thorn;e fei&thorn; &thorn;at we trowe nor &thorn;e lawe canoun taki&thorn; not inpungning of &thorn;e law of God as to &thorn;is part, but as to &thorn;e to&thorn;er part, 
<PB REF="00000138.tif" N="74"> is comonning mikil wi&thorn; law cyuil, and &thorn;us it gedre&thorn; in itsilf two lawes, and of &thorn;is commixtioun of &thorn;e vsing of &thorn;eis two lawis &thorn;us is diuersly sown gret seed of discord in &thorn;e kirk of God. Crisostom<NOTE PLACE="marg">Crisostom.</NOTE> sei&thorn;, Mannis law ha&thorn; bodily wynningis to cum, but Crist beheti&thorn; goostly &thorn;ingis to cum; at fleschly men ar ay present &thorn;ingis putt befor &thorn;ingis to cum, and bodili &thorn;ingis to gostly &thorn;ingis; &thorn;is sei&thorn; he. And &thorn;us as &thorn;e flesche and &thorn;e spirit are contrari, so &thorn;eis twey lawis, namly, wil &thorn;e fleschly &thorn;ingis lettun &thorn;e spirit. Werfor &thorn;e doctor Parisiens sei&thorn;, Aduocatis in &thorn;er office geytun hem ay last|<NOTE PLACE="marg">Parisiens.</NOTE> ing de&thorn;; &thorn;at semi&thorn; to be figerid in Goddis lawe; were Sichem, &thorn;at is interpretid a foul, louyd Dyna, &thorn;at is interpretid cause, by was occasioun he was slayn after. Notably is Sichem callid &thorn;e son of Emor, &thorn;at is interpretid an asse, for men hard as assis, &thorn;at mi&yogh;t not profit in o&thorn;er sciens, were wont to heer decrees and decretals. &THORN;e loue of Goddis lawe, and &thorn;e condicouns of sciens of decres schuld streyn men fro &thorn;is office. Of&thorn;e loue of Goddis lawe Gregor<NOTE PLACE="marg">Gregor.</NOTE> sei&thorn;, he &thorn;at loui&thorn; a kyng he loui&thorn; his lawe. In &thorn;e Salme, his ee<NOTE PLACE="marg">Salme x<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> ledis asken reson of men; ee lydis &thorn;at sum tyme are opun, and sum tyme clos, tokeni&thorn; holy writ, &thorn;at is derk to sum, and opun to sum, &thorn;at axen &thorn;o sonis men we&thorn;er &thorn;ey louen God. A tokyn of Goddis luf is wan ani stodie&thorn; gladly in holy writ; holy writ is mikil dispicid for &thorn;e sciens of decrees. Werfor scho may sey &thorn;at Sara seid to Abraam, &THORN;u dost vneuenly a&yogh;ens me, I hau &yogh;euen myn<NOTE PLACE="marg">Gen. xuj<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> handmayd in &thorn;i bosum, and scho seing &thorn;at sche ha&thorn; conseyuid ha&thorn; me to despit; &thorn;e wench of holy writ is sciens of decrees, &thorn;at ha&thorn; holy writ to despit, for &thorn;e frut of wynning &thorn;at folowi&thorn; &thorn;er of; and in Goddis lawe is figerid &thorn;e supprising &thorn;at &thorn;e sciens of wynning do&thorn; in holy writ, be &thorn;e play in &thorn;e wilk Ismael oppressid Isaac; warfor as God bad bi Sara, Kast out &thorn;e wench and her son, so<NOTE PLACE="marg">Gen. xxj<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> haply it were need &thorn;is sciens in gret part to be excludid fro &thorn;e kirk; not only is holi writ despisid bi &thorn;at sciens, and blasfemid, but God himsilf &thorn;at is &thorn;e law &yogh;euar, &thorn;at semi&thorn; figerid in Goddis 
<PB REF="00000139.tif" N="75"> lawe, wer it is red, &thorn;at &thorn;e son of a woman of Israel, &thorn;at scho bar of<NOTE PLACE="marg">Lev. xxiu<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> a man of Egipt, stroue wi&thorn; a man of Israel and blasfemid God of Israel; &thorn;us in &thorn;e decretistis, &thorn;at are Israelitis in party, os to &thorn;e part of sciens &thorn;at &thorn;ey han tane of Godis lawe, and Egipcians as to &thorn;e part &thorn;at &thorn;ey haue of worldly wysdam, &thorn;ei blasfemen God of Israel, wil &thorn;ey calle &thorn;e lawe &thorn;at he &yogh;af kafe, as vnprophitable, wen he sei&thorn; himsilf, I &thorn;i Lord God toching &thorn;e profitable &thorn;ingis; &thorn;erfor &thorn;ei are<NOTE PLACE="marg">Isa. xluiij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> ra&thorn;er chaffe of wilk &thorn;e gospel sei&thorn;, I schal brenne &thorn;e chaffe wi&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="marg">Matt. iij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> fire vnslekable; &thorn;e prophet sei&thorn;, He &thorn;at ha&thorn; a dreme, telle it as a<NOTE PLACE="marg">Jer. xxiii<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> dreme, and he &thorn;at ha&thorn; my wordis, telle he my wordis verryli; wat is &thorn;e chaf to &thorn;e corn, sei&thorn; &thorn;e Lord? And Austeyn sei&thorn;, If &thorn;u folow<NOTE PLACE="marg">Austeyn.</NOTE> chaf &thorn;u schalt be chaf. And Odo sei&thorn;, Jeroboam was dampnid, for<NOTE PLACE="marg">Odo.</NOTE> he held &thorn;e peple abak by two kalfis &thorn;at &thorn;ei worschipid not God in Ierlm; &thorn;eis two kalfis are lawis and decrees, bi wilk clerkis are haldun doun, &thorn;at &thorn;ey sacrificy not to God in &thorn;e si&yogh;t of holi writ; &thorn;is sei&thorn; he. And &thorn;us sei&thorn; an o&thorn;er, Men occupied in mannis lawis,<NOTE PLACE="marg">An other.</NOTE> and putting be hend &thorn;e helful lawe of Goddis comaundmentis, schuld tak hed how in &thorn;is same &thorn;ei ren in &thorn;e curse of God; for in &thorn;e Salm it is writun, Cursid be &thorn;ei &thorn;at bowen doun fro &thorn;i bid|<NOTE PLACE="marg">Salm. cxuiij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> dingis. God biddi&thorn; vs do dedis of kynd, and alle moralls are goostly dedis, or dedis of maneris bi &thorn;e lawe of maneris. And God ha&thorn; &yogh;euen to vs &thorn;e newe lawe, compendiosar and more com|plet and more profitablar &thorn;an ani o&thorn;er lawe; more ful, for &thorn;er is not &thorn;at mai be put to mak it perfitar or compendiosar, for it is in a word of charite profitablar, for non o&thorn;er law profiti&thorn;, not but in as miche as it meue to &thorn;is. And here rehersi&thorn; Austeyn, speking of<NOTE PLACE="marg">Austeyn.</NOTE> &thorn;e multitude of tradicouns of &thorn;e kirk, &thorn;at sei&thorn; &thorn;us: Sum supprise wi&thorn; seruil chargis our religioun &thorn;at our Lord Ihu Crist wold to be fre, in so wast halowing of sacramentis, so &thorn;at &thorn;e condicoun of Jewis is more suffurable, &thorn;at is sogetid not to mannis tradicoun, but to Goddis ordinaunce. But wat trow we &thorn;is seynt to cry &thorn;is day, if he liuid, a&yogh;ennis &thorn;e multitude of lawis of &thorn;e kirk incorporat 
<PB REF="00000140.tif" N="76"> and extriuagaunt, wat a&yogh;en batails, a&yogh;en reseruacouns, a&yogh;en furst frutis, and o&thorn;er spolingis of goodis of &thorn;e kirk; I trow he schuld sey, &thorn;is reprouid Crist to &thorn;e phariseis, wi&thorn; more &yogh;he ful of raneyn. And &thorn;is sei&thorn; an o&thorn;er, &thorn;at &thorn;e sciens of aduoketis is detestable semi&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="marg">An other.</NOTE> bi &thorn;is, &thorn;at in many &thorn;ings it is contrari to &thorn;e law of God. For &thorn;e law sei&thorn;, &thorn;at it is leful to &thorn;eis &thorn;at maken couenaunt to gidre, to disseile ei&thorn;er o&thorn;er, wil &thorn;ei passe not &thorn;e midil of iuste price; but Goddis law sei&thorn;, &thorn;u schal do no &thorn;ing &yogh;euelfuly to &thorn;i ne&yogh;bor in his nedis to be releuid, and &thorn;at no man bigyle his bro&thorn;er in no caas. Efter &thorn;e lawe to him &thorn;at breki&thorn; sei&thorn;, to him &thorn;at breki&thorn; fei&thorn;, fei&thorn; schal be brokun to him; &thorn;e gospel a&yogh;en &thorn;is biddi&thorn; do wel to &thorn;in enemy. Eft an o&thorn;er witti in &thorn;at sam law sei&thorn; &thorn;us: It is to see<NOTE PLACE="marg">An other.</NOTE> how now lawis of &thorn;e seculer clerkis are contrari to holy writ, and to hold lawis of seyntis, and general counseils of hold holy clerkis. <I>First in this.</I> &THORN;o gospel biddi&thorn; al men &yogh;eld to &thorn;e emperor &thorn;ingis &thorn;at are his, and to God &thorn;o &thorn;ingis &thorn;at are Goddis, and Crist obeyed<NOTE PLACE="marg">Matt.xxij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> to princes of &thorn;e world vndirgoing &thorn;e dede; and so ded &thorn;e apostlis and seyntis. But now new law techi&thorn; &thorn;at no prest nor clerk ow to soget to no seculer lord. &THORN;e secound. Crist payid tribut for him and for Petre, and Ambrose acordi&thorn; &thorn;at feldis of &thorn;e kirk pay<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ambrose.</NOTE> tribut. But nowe newe lawe techi&thorn; &thorn;at wi&thorn; out consent of &thorn;e bischop of Rome &thorn;ei schal pay no tributis nor taliagis. &THORN;e &thorn;rid. Crist sei&thorn; in &thorn;e gospel to his disciplis, &thorn;e kyngs of folk lorden vp<NOTE PLACE="marg">Luc. xxij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> on hem, and &thorn;ei &thorn;at vsun power upon hem are callid &yogh;efars of benefices, but &yogh;e not so; but he &thorn;at wil a mong &yogh;ow be &thorn;e more, be he as &thorn;e minister. And Austeyn, Gregor, Ciprian, Jerom, and<NOTE PLACE="marg">Austeyn. Gregor. Ciprian. Jerom. Isidor.</NOTE> Isidir, kennen, as is put in &thorn;e law, &thorn;at it perteni&thorn; to seculer princes to punisch &thorn;eis &thorn;at synnen opunly. But nowe clerkis bi &thorn;er new lawis chalungen to hem &thorn;at only it perteni&thorn; to hem to punisch symony, heresy, vsur, auoutry, and periury. &THORN;e fourt. &THORN;e apostil sei&thorn;, we hauing fode and hyling hald vs payed. And bi &thorn;e sawis<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Tim. uj<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> of Jerom, Ambrose, and Bernard, clerkis how to be content of<NOTE PLACE="marg">Jerom. Ambrose. Bernard.</NOTE> 
<PB REF="00000141.tif" N="77"> liflod, and haue al &thorn;ingis in comyn. But now bi new lawis, clerkis propriun to hemsilf temporal &thorn;ingis as seclereis, and not only to liflod and hyling, but to lust and worldly hynes. Werfor it folowi&thorn;, &thorn;at oi&thorn;er &thorn;eis seyntis bar fals wittnes, or &thorn;at swilk lawis, bi wilk &thorn;is maner of hauing is defendir, ar contrari to hem, and to holy writ; or ellis &thorn;at clerkis now are fals witnes a&yogh;en &thorn;er lawis, and &thorn;efis, and refars, and fals intrewsars. &THORN;e fifth. &THORN;e apostil sei&thorn;, no man halding bi kni&yogh;thed to God, inpli&yogh;e&thorn; him to worldly<NOTE PLACE="marg">2 Tim. ij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> bisines; and doctors a cordyn, as is put in &thorn;e law. But now al most is no worldly bysines &thorn;at ministres of &thorn;e auter are not inplied in, as is opun in &thorn;er dedis; werof it folowi&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;ei lif contrari to holy writ, and to &thorn;e decrees of hold fadres; and if &thorn;ei haue ani law defending hem in &thorn;is, &thorn;an is &thorn;e law contrari as &thorn;er lif is; if &thorn;ey haue not, &thorn;an &thorn;ei lif vnlawfuly in &thorn;is. &THORN;e <I>sixst.</I> &THORN;e apostil sei&thorn;, no man tak honor to him, but if he be callid of God. And<NOTE PLACE="marg">Heb. v<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> after &thorn;e decrees of senctis, as is opun in canoun, as it schal be &yogh;euen to him &thorn;at is callid and forsaki&thorn;, so it schal be naytid him &thorn;at offre&thorn; himsilf. But now new lawis kennen &thorn;at he &thorn;at most offri&thorn; him, and most persewi&thorn; wi&thorn; &yogh;eftis of hand, tunge, or seruise, he schal be preferrid to &thorn;e holiar and abler, bi vertu of a ded bulle. &THORN;e <I>seuynt.</I> God biddi&thorn; &thorn;u schalt not do &thorn;eft, nor coueyt &thorn;e goodis of &thorn;i nei&yogh;bor, but &yogh;eld to ilk man &thorn;at is his; and of &thorn;e de|<NOTE PLACE="marg">Exod. xx<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> crees of seyntis, if &thorn;u haue foundun ani &thorn;ing and not restorid it, &thorn;u hast reft it. And eft, synnis are so mykil &thorn;e greuowsar as &thorn;ey hold and schuld lengar bynd. But now new lawis kennyn prescrip|coun, &thorn;at if ani be in possessioun of o&thorn;er mennis &thorn;ingis by a cercle of &yogh;eris, he schal ioi it as his oune, as is brokyn of Goddis bidding mak ri&yogh;t. &THORN;e <I>heyt.</I> Crist biddi&thorn; in &thorn;e gospel to his vicar, turn &thorn;e swerd in to &thorn;e sche&thorn;; and wordis of doctors and decrees acordyn<NOTE PLACE="marg">Joh. xuiij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> &thorn;at prestis how not to vse &thorn;e bodily swerd wi&thorn; &thorn;er oune hand, and mani peynis are enioinid in new lawis for breking of &thorn;is. But &thorn;is not a&yogh;enstonding, &thorn;ei han founden a new ordinaunce and indul|gencis 
<PB REF="00000142.tif" N="78"> and remissiouns, if &thorn;ei sle cristun men wi&thorn; &thorn;er oune handis. &THORN;e <I>nynt.</I> &THORN;e apostil sei&thorn;, &thorn;e bischop be howui&thorn; to haue good wit|nes of &thorn;eis &thorn;at are wi&thorn; out; and Jerom techi&thorn; &thorn;at in chesing of &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Tim. iij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> prestis requiri&thorn; &thorn;e assent of &thorn;e peple. But now bi new lawis &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">Jerom.</NOTE> peple schal not wit &thorn;er of. &THORN;e <I>tente.</I> It is seid to prelatis, &yogh;e are li&yogh;t of &thorn;e world, and eft, snybbe &thorn;e synnar be for alle; and<NOTE PLACE="marg">Matt. u<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> after &thorn;e decrees of seyntis, and of &thorn;e kirk, he &thorn;at correcti&thorn; not, schal be gilty as he &thorn;at ded &thorn;e dede. But now lawis &yogh;euen leef to tak money for gret synnis, and &thorn;at non schal let hem to contune in synne for &thorn;at feynid correccoun. &THORN;e <I>elleuynt.</I> It is seid to prestis, Frely &yogh;e han tan, frely &yogh;eui&thorn;; and to &thorn;is acordi&thorn; mani decres<NOTE PLACE="marg">Matt. x<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> of &thorn;e kirk, and doctors, wi&thorn; mani peynis. But now are found new constitucouns of procuracies and customis and o&thorn;er expensis, so &thorn;at noi&thorn;er sacrament, nor benefice, nor ministry, is &yogh;euun nor tan frely after Cristis bidding; but oueral go&thorn; symonie priualy or apert. &THORN;e <I>twelft.</I> &THORN;e prophet sei&thorn; to prelatis, Crie, cese not, hie &thorn;i voyce as a troump, and schew to my peple &thorn;er synnis; cursid<NOTE PLACE="marg">Isa. luiij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> be he &thorn;at forbedi&thorn; his suerd fro blod, &thorn;at is his tong, and his traueyl fro correccoun of synne; and doctors cordyn, and hold decres. But now new law kenni&thorn; priuilegies and exempcouns fro iust correccouns of fai&thorn;ful prelatis and curatis, so &thorn;at &thorn;ey may not reise Sathanas out of his nest, nor hele &thorn;e seek. Vp on &thorn;is Lincoln crie&thorn; out opon &thorn;e pope and sei&thorn;, &thorn;at prelatis may not be<NOTE PLACE="marg">Lincoln.</NOTE> excusid, no but &thorn;ei happily wil lay al &thorn;e synne on &thorn;e pope. <I>xiij</I>. &THORN;e Lord biddi&thorn;e kepe matrimony vndefoylid, and do non aduowtry; but now new lawis kennen &thorn;at &thorn;e man and &thorn;e woman han bi twex hem drawen to gidre verray matrimony, &thorn;at if &thorn;e man after tret wi&thorn; a no&thorn;er woman, and lye bi her, if &thorn;e first woman may not proue her contract, &thorn;an &thorn;e secound schal be his wif, bi resoun of avowter, and he schal be cursid but if he tak to her as to his wif. And &yogh;et schal be enioynid bi &thorn;e law, in &thorn;e sacrament of schrift, vnder &thorn;e peyn of dedly synne, to tak &thorn;e first and touch 
<PB REF="00000143.tif" N="79"> not &thorn;e secound; experiens of dede proui&thorn; &thorn;at it is &thorn;us, and &thorn;us him be howui&thorn; to be cursid, but if he tak bo&thorn;e, and cursid if he tak oi&thorn;er &thorn;e ton or &thorn;e to&thorn;er. &THORN;e <I>fourtent.</I> God biddi&thorn; &thorn;u shalt not sey fals witnes a&yogh;en &thorn;i ney&yogh;bor, nor lye, nor forsuere &thorn;e, nor deme vniustly, nor a&yogh;en sey &thorn;e trow&thorn; in no maner; and mani lawis of &thorn;e kirk and sawis of doctors de|claryn &thorn;is, and enioynen mani peynis for &thorn;e trespassors her of. But now clerkis practisyn bi &thorn;er new lawis &thorn;at a iuge schal witnes bi his dome, &thorn;at an o&thorn;er mannis &thorn;ing is myn, and a&yogh;enword myn a o&thorn;er mannis, for &thorn;e fals witnes of two or of &thorn;re a&yogh;en &thorn;e trow&thorn;, and if [? &yogh;if] &thorn;e sentens to sle &thorn;e innocent and curse &thorn;e giltles, &yogh;a &thorn;ow he wit &thorn;at it is fals. Also if a man be falsly accusid bi two witnessis, if he deney it &thorn;at he is accusid of, and graunt &thorn;e so&thorn;, &thorn;an he schal be condempnid &thorn;er of as gilty. &THORN;e <I>xvj.</I> [xv]. Goddis law biddi&thorn; help &thorn;e supprissid, jugi&thorn; to &thorn;e fadirles, defendi&thorn; &thorn;e wydow, and how temporal lordis ow to &thorn;ole no wrong be don; and mani doctors and lawis and resoun acordyn to &thorn;is. But now crien clerkis bi &thorn;er new lawis, &thorn;at if a man be cursid fourty dayes, &thorn;ow he be cursid wrongly, and &thorn;at &thorn;an temporal lordis schal, bi &thorn;e bischops signifying or bidding, put him in to prisoun, til he suget him to &thorn;er dome, &thorn;ow it be vniust. &THORN;e <I>xvij.</I> [xvj]. If &thorn;at a man wed in to wif in &thorn;e face of &thorn;e kirk a cosyn of his, &thorn;e wilk God forbedi&thorn; him to towch, and after &thorn;is cosynage is knowen to him, but it may not be known formably bi proue after &thorn;e court of plete, &yogh;ef &thorn;e woman after axe &thorn;e fleschly det, &thorn;ow it be a&yogh;en &thorn;e bidding of God to pay it, he schal be cursid, but if he tret her as his wif. And if he do it, he breki&thorn; &thorn;e bidding of God, and in &thorn;is cas he schal not be cursid bi her dome, or ellis he schal dwel cursid &thorn;e daies of his lif, efter &thorn;e process of &thorn;e new decretal wi&thorn; Jon Andrewe. And &thorn;is inconuenient mai not be voydid w<SUP>t</SUP> mani moo o&thorn;er. &THORN;e <I>xviij.</I> [xvij]. &THORN;e apostil sei&thorn;, Ilk &thorn;ing &thorn;at is not of &thorn;e fei&thorn; is synne. And &thorn;e lawe acordi&thorn;, &thorn;at he &thorn;at do&thorn; a&yogh;en<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ro. xiu<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> 
<PB REF="00000144.tif" N="80"> conciens biggi&thorn; to helle. And &thorn;is not a&yogh;enstonding &thorn;en schal man do &thorn;ing a&yogh;en his consciens, and curse him but if he obey, and &thorn;is is contrari in itsilf and to God bo&thorn;e, &thorn;an &thorn;ei sey &thorn;at a man schal ra&thorn;er &thorn;ole &thorn;er sentence &thorn;an do a&yogh;en his consciens; but war profit wer &thorn;at if God curse al &thorn;at &thorn;ei curse, for &thorn;an God schuld curse &thorn;is man. And it is iuel seid to bid man lett not to his wil for &thorn;e curse of God. After &thorn;ey sey &thorn;at wat &thorn;ing &thorn;o bindi&thorn; in &yogh;er&thorn; or &thorn;e kirk, it schal be confermid in heuen; and &yogh;et &thorn;ei sey &thorn;ey &yogh;ef mani sentens &thorn;at bindun not anenst God. &THORN;e <I>xix.</I> [xviii.] Eft &thorn;e apostil biddi&thorn; men stond, and not be holden a&yogh;en wi&thorn; &thorn;e &yogh;ok of seruage,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Gal. v<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> for law bringi&thorn; no man to profit, not but &thorn;at &thorn;ing &thorn;at is maad opun in &thorn;e lawe, but he &thorn;at seki&thorn; to be iustified in &thorn;e law is fallen fro Crist, for man be howui&thorn; be iustified of &thorn;e fei&thorn; and grace and goodnes of Crist; in &thorn;is &thorn;at he frely and wilfully trowi&thorn; in to Cristis teching, and felli&thorn; his bidding. But now men seyn hem iust, if &thorn;ey do &thorn;e law after &thorn;er wit; an &thorn;ow &thorn;at &thorn;ei do &thorn;ing &thorn;at is a&yogh;en Crist, and a&yogh;en consciens, &thorn;e law schal excuse him, and is inow for him. Also &thorn;e pope sei&thorn; in his lawe, &thorn;at &thorn;er are two lawis, as law of &thorn;e spirit, and law maad of men; and who &thorn;at is led be &thorn;e law of &thorn;e spirit is fre, and is not wor&thorn;i &thorn;at he be dreuen vnder maad lawe, and &thorn;erfor go he fre bi oure autorite. But now are men lettid oftun bi maad lawis, rewlis, and constitucouns, to wirk after &thorn;e spirit, or to do &thorn;e merciful dedis or ri&yogh;tfulnes frely, bi autorite of Crist; &thorn;is is oft prouid many tymys bi deed, os bo&thorn; in religious, and o&thorn;er, wen it is not leful to hem to do &thorn;e dedis of mercy, noi&thorn;er bodily, nor gostly, if &thorn;er ouer man bid hem be stille, and lefe alle &thorn;eis or ani o&thorn;er lawis, rewl, or customis, wat euer &thorn;ei be, wan &thorn;ei ar not wi&thorn; &thorn;o gospel in ani maner substauns formid or vsyng in to perfeccoun of fredum of &thorn;e gospel, but are in ani maner, ani tyme, for ani &thorn;ing, letting, or trobling, or tarieng any &thorn;ing &thorn;at gospel biddi&thorn;, or counseyli&thorn; to be don; in &thorn;is &thorn;ei are a&yogh;en Goddis law, and a&yogh;enis God, aftur &thorn;e sentence of Crist befor seid, He &thorn;at is not wi&thorn; me, he is a&yogh;en me.</P>


</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="22" TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000145.tif" N="81">
<HEAD>XXII. Cristis dis|ciplis kepe Cristis counseil.</HEAD>
<P>An o&thorn;er poynt is &thorn;is; &thorn;at no man is Cristis disciple, but if he kepe Cristis counseil. &THORN;is me &thorn;ingi&thorn; wel is so&thorn;, bi diuerse resouns. And &thorn;erfor we schal first vnderstond, as bo&thorn; Goddis law, and experiens, and resoun techi&thorn;, &thorn;at Cristis counseilis are callid in two wise, as sum tyme &thorn;ing &thorn;at he counseili&thorn; to, and biddi&thorn; not to ilk man as o&thorn;er comaundments; as are &thorn;eis, &thorn;at men kepen in &thorn;e gospel bodily pouert, and keping fro bodily weddingis, and suylk o&thorn;er. On o&thorn;er wyse is callid his counseil &thorn;us, as he steri&thorn; oon to do &thorn;us, an o&thorn;er &thorn;us; as he seid to &thorn;e man, &yogh;if &thorn;u wilt be perfi&yogh;t<NOTE PLACE="marg">Matt. xix<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> go selle alle &thorn;at &thorn;u hast, and &yogh;ef to &thorn;e pore, and &thorn;u schalt haue mikil mede in heuen, and cum and folow me. And &thorn;us sei&thorn; Poul, &thorn;at he gaf counseil to &thorn;ingis as him &thorn;owt, but ilk man had his<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Cor. uij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> proper &yogh;eft of God, to go as God ha&thorn; callid him; and &thorn;us in ilk &thorn;ingis men nedyn euer &thorn;e counseil of God, to led hem in al &thorn;ingis to do as is leful and spedy and best, and &thorn;is is a &yogh;eft of &thorn;e Holy Goost. And &thorn;us is opun, &thorn;at non is Cristis disciple, but if he kep his counseil; for ellis he leri&thorn; not at him, nor is not &yogh;euen to his sciens, nor led &thorn;er by, nor fillid &thorn;erof, nor of &thorn;e sciens of God, but if he kepe his counseil; for &thorn;us sei&thorn; Crist, and rehersi&thorn; &thorn;e prophet,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Joh. uj<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> &thorn;at alle men able are taut of God. And God bi his prophet cursi&thorn; &thorn;eis &thorn;at wirken not bi his counseil, for &thorn;us he sei&thorn; bi Ysaye, Who<NOTE PLACE="marg">Isa. xxx<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> sonnis lifers, sei&thorn; &thorn;e Lord, &thorn;at &yogh;e schuld mak a counseil and not of me, and wef a web and not bi mi Spirit, &thorn;at &yogh;e schuld adde syn vp on synne, &thorn;at &yogh;e go doun in til Egipt and axid not mi Spirit, &thorn;er for &yogh;e schal mak counseil and it schal be schaterid, and as he han<NOTE PLACE="marg">Prov. i<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> left mi counseil and sett mi blamings at nout, I schal law&yogh;e in &yogh;our de&thorn;, and bymowe &yogh;ow wen &thorn;is schal cum to &yogh;ow &thorn;at &yogh;e dred. And many are &thorn;e witnessis &thorn;at kenun vs to do alle &thorn;ingis euer bi &thorn;e counseil of God. But neuer&thorn;eles ouer &thorn;is we schal vnderstond &thorn;at disciplis of Crist are seid in syndry maneris and degrees, as sum in general, sum in special. In general maner are al Cristis disciplis, &thorn;at after &thorn;e rewle of kynde folowi&thorn; his lore. And 
<PB REF="00000146.tif" N="82"> in an o&thorn;er special maner weren his disciplis &thorn;at folowid him bi &thorn;e kenning of Moyses lawe, and o&thorn;er writun lawis. In &thorn;e &thorn;rid maner are &thorn;eis his disciplis &thorn;at folowen his lore &thorn;at he taut in &thorn;e gospel; and &thorn;us sum are his disciplis in a degre &thorn;at are ordeynid and chosun to folow him in lyuing, and &thorn;oling, and teching; and sum in o&thorn;er degre &thorn;at are ordeynid to be taut. And of &thorn;eis sum are iuel, and gon o bak; and Judas was his disciple chosun, and his apostil, and mani of his disciplis went a bak. But and sin Crist sei&thorn;, Non may be his disciple but if he renounce alle &thorn;ingis &thorn;at he<NOTE PLACE="marg">Lue. xiu<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> ha&thorn;, and tak his cros and folow Crist, it folowi&thorn; pleynly, &thorn;at &thorn;ow [a] man be his disciple in sum degre, neuer&thorn;eles in sum degre he is not his disciple, but if he kepe his counseyl, and lef al &thorn;ing. And for &thorn;i &thorn;us sei&thorn; a doctor, Who &thorn;at euer he be, &thorn;at in &thorn;e last<NOTE PLACE="marg">A Doctor.</NOTE> our of his de&thorn; kasti&thorn; not al his bisines and his affeccoun in to God, kasting fro him al worldly bisynes, baldly I dar sey, &thorn;at he schal not after &thorn;is lif be Cristis disciple in heuen. Of &thorn;is schuld &thorn;ei be war &thorn;at occupien men toward her end a bout &thorn;e world, and de|parting and assining of &thorn;er goodis, and to mak her heyris grete after hem, and to mak pompous exequies and entermentis, biriel, and swilk &thorn;ingis, in to veyn nam after hem; and &thorn;ei &thorn;at occupien hem wi&thorn; japis, and remembren hem of &thorn;er old iuel, in to lyking &thorn;er of, and &thorn;at steri&thorn; men in to morning for &thorn;ei schal lefe &thorn;is world, and &thorn;ei mornyn for her frendis leuen it; and men &thorn;at are ocupied about testamentis, and schuld lok &thorn;at &thorn;e last wille of &thorn;e man wer kepid, not only wat he wil, but how his wille schuld be rewlid. Vp on &thorn;is schulde &thorn;enk prestis, prelatis, and religious, and o&thorn;er &thorn;at han vowid to kep bodily pouert, obediens, and chastite, how &thorn;at &thorn;ei schuld folow Crist to be his disciplis trewly wi&thorn; out ypo|crisie; &thorn;at &thorn;ei fille her vow, and mak it not voyd, nor renne not for &thorn;e brekyng and multiplieng of &thorn;er synne in to &thorn;at curse &thorn;at Crist biddi&thorn; to &thorn;e scribis and to &thorn;e phariseis &thorn;us, Wo wor&thorn; &yogh;ow,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Matt. xxiij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> he sei&thorn;, &thorn;at gon about &thorn;e see and &thorn;e lond to mak a nouys of &yogh;our 
<PB REF="00000147.tif" N="83"> ordre, and wan he is made &yogh;e mak him a son of helle double as &yogh;our silf.</P>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="23" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XXIII. Ilk man is holden to do the better.</HEAD>
<P>An o&thorn;er point is her put &thorn;us and axid, &thorn;at ilk man is holden to do &thorn;ing &thorn;at is &thorn;e better. And me &thorn;inki&thorn; &thorn;at ilk man is holden to do &thorn;e better; and for &thorn;e clerar vnderstonding of &thorn;is, I suppose, &thorn;at as Goddis byddyng and comyn speche bo&thorn;e, and as men vnder|stondyn &thorn;at bettar or best is seid by &thorn;re resouns, or moo, or ellis vp on &thorn;re maneris, as sum &thorn;ing is seid better, or best, &thorn;an an o&thorn;er in his kynd, form, and vertu; and &thorn;us is God seid &thorn;e best ouer alle o&thorn;er; and &thorn;us gostly createris are seid better &thorn;an o&thorn;er; and &thorn;us bi diuers resouns is on seid better &thorn;an an o&thorn;er. In &thorn;e secounde maner is on seid better &thorn;an an o&thorn;er, for &thorn;e maner and &thorn;e forme; and &thorn;us of &thorn;is is oft o &thorn;ing seid better &thorn;an an o&thorn;er. And &thorn;us if two men do a &thorn;ing, &thorn;e ton is oft seid to do better &thorn;an &thorn;e to&thorn;er. And &thorn;us is a man of harmis seid better &thorn;an an o&thorn;er, and a prest better &thorn;an an o&thorn;er, and a religious man better &thorn;an an o&thorn;er, and a housbond better &thorn;an an o&thorn;er, for he can better, and do&thorn; better &thorn;an &thorn;e to&thorn;er. In &thorn;e &thorn;rid maner is a &thorn;ing seid better &thorn;an an o&thorn;er, in &thorn;is, as it helpi&thorn; better by sum wey and mene to &thorn;e &yogh;end of a &thorn;ing, &thorn;an an o&thorn;er do&thorn;. And &thorn;us sum tyme a &thorn;ing &thorn;at is seid to be warst to sum man, is bi an o&thorn;er resoun sed best for sum a&yogh;enword. And &thorn;us seknes, and foul weder, and pouert is to sum men best, wan &thorn;ei are menis to him to kepe Goddis biddingis, and to geyt blis; and so &thorn;ei are better to him &thorn;an riches, or fair wedur, or hele, wen he schuld tak occasioun by hem to do synne, and displece God, and deserue peyn. And &thorn;us a&yogh;enword wan &thorn;eis &thorn;ingis are to man in to cause and help to plese God, &thorn;an are &thorn;ei &thorn;e better to him. And &thorn;us &thorn;ow it be better in heuen to seyntis to not traueyl, nor be peynid, as we are here, neuer&thorn;eles it is better as for &thorn;is tyme; for &thorn;us sei&thorn; Poule, forso&thorn; I am constreynid of two &thorn;ingis, hauing desir<NOTE PLACE="marg">Phil. i<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> to be dissoluid, and be wi&thorn; Crist, mikil better, certis to dwel in flesche is profit necessary for &yogh;ow. Also men seyn, &thorn;ow contem|platif 
<PB REF="00000148.tif" N="84"> lif be &thorn;e fairar, actif lif is &thorn;e profitabler; and al &thorn;ing as Crist did it so it was best, for he did ay &thorn;e best, and all &thorn;ingis wi&thorn; out defaut. And it is not to sey of alle &thorn;e warkis of God, &thorn;is is wars &thorn;an &thorn;at, and if any &thorn;ing &thorn;at Crist dede mi&yogh;t haue be don better, &thorn;an were not he best and wisest, nor &thorn;e mi&yogh;tyest; and &thorn;is were grete synne to sey; &thorn;erfor &thorn;e best &thorn;ing &thorn;at ani man may do is to do &thorn;at he biddi&thorn; and counseyli&thorn; to do, and to &thorn;at ende &thorn;at he biddi&thorn; and steri&thorn;; and &thorn;is is generaly ilk man holdyn to do, vndre gret peyn, &yogh;he bo&thorn; of synne, and of punisching, and better &thorn;ing may no man do, nor in better maner, nor to better ende. For &thorn;us is writun in Goddis law, No &thorn;ing is better &thorn;an to drede God and<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ecclus. xxiij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> kepe his biddingis, nor &thorn;ing more helfular &thorn;an lok in his biddyngis. And eft &thorn;us, Dred God and kep his biddingis, &thorn;at is ilk man. And<NOTE PLACE="marg">Eccles.xij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> Poul sei&thorn;, Noi&thorn;er prepuce nor circumcicoun is out, nor out wor&thorn;,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Gal. u<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> not but keping of &thorn;e biddingis of God; and ani &thorn;ing schal not profit to hem but in &thorn;is &thorn;at God biddi&thorn; him, or counseyli&thorn; him to do it, and as he do&thorn; it for &thorn;at bidding and counseyl; and &thorn;us is bidun in &thorn;e gospel, If &thorn;u wil enter in to lif kep Goddis biddingis,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Matt. xix<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> &thorn;at are &thorn;eis, &thorn;u schalt luf &thorn;i Lord God wi&thorn; al &thorn;in hart, in al &thorn;in soul, of al &thorn;i mynd, and &thorn;i ne&yogh;bor as &thorn;i silf; and &thorn;is is more &thorn;an alle brend offryngis and sacrifice, for in &thorn;is hangi&thorn; al &thorn;e law and prophetis. An syn &thorn;is is bidding of God, man is holden generaly for to do &thorn;is, for ellis he may not be saue, as Poule proui&thorn;, for no penaunce, ne purnes, ne chastite, ne o&thorn;er &thorn;ing &thorn;at he may do. And wi&thorn; out swilk o&thorn;er dedis many han comyn to heuen. Also<NOTE PLACE="marg">Heb. xiij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> &thorn;us sei&thorn; Poule, &thorn;at it is better to stable &thorn;e hert in grace &thorn;an in meytis, &thorn;at han not profitid to hem &thorn;at gon in hem. Also &thorn;us is writun, Obedience is better &thorn;an slayn offring, and for to assent is<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Sam. xv<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> better &thorn;an for to offer &thorn;e fatnes of schep; for it is os &thorn;e synne of wychis to repungne, and as &thorn;e synne of idolatrie to not assent; and to obey to Cristis biddingis is man euer holden, and not ay to offer. And many moo witnes are how a man is holdun to do &thorn;e 
<PB REF="00000149.tif" N="85"> best. Al so &thorn;us sei&thorn; Jerom, He erri&thorn; not menly &thorn;at of two good<NOTE PLACE="marg">Jerom.</NOTE> &thorn;ingis putti&thorn; &thorn;e lesse good be fore, and leui&thorn; &thorn;e better; and of &thorn;is it semi&thorn; &thorn;at he is holdun to do &thorn;e better.</P>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="24" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XXIV. Ymagis are not to be worschipid.</HEAD>
<P>An o&thorn;er is &thorn;is; &thorn;at ymagis of seyntis are not to be worschipid. &THORN;is haue I seid, and to sey &thorn;is steri&thorn; me, &thorn;at God sei&thorn; in his com|aundment, &thorn;u schalt not mak &thorn;e a grauyn &thorn;ing, noi&thorn;er in ilk liknes &thorn;at is in heuen a bouen, ne &thorn;at is in &yogh;er&thorn; be ne&thorn;, ne of &thorn;ingis &thorn;at<NOTE PLACE="marg">Exod xx<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> are in wateris vnder &thorn;e &yogh;er&thorn;; &thorn;u schalt not lowt, ne worschip hem. And Gregor sei&thorn; &thorn;us, If ani wil mak an ymage, as for a bok tul<NOTE PLACE="marg">Gregor.</NOTE> him, forbed him not, but to worschip &thorn;e ymage almaner wittirly forbeed &thorn;u him; but &thorn;i bro&thorn;erhed stere bisily &thorn;is, &thorn;at men tak of &thorn;e si&yogh;t of &thorn;e &thorn;ing &thorn;e more compunccoun, and be kesed in &thorn;e wor|schiping of &thorn;e Trinite a lone, for on is to honor &thorn;e &thorn;ing, a no&thorn;er is to se &thorn;er by wat is to be honorid. And for &thorn;is sei&thorn; a no&thorn;er, If<NOTE PLACE="marg">Another.</NOTE> ymagis be worschipid, not bi vicary worschip, but by &thorn;e same worschip of God, doutles it is idolatrie; for noi&thorn;er &thorn;e stok, noi&thorn;er &thorn;e craft of man is to be worschipid so. It is certeyn bi witnes of holy writ, and of seyntis, and of experiens, &thorn;at we awe not to arett swelk &thorn;ingis, or &thorn;ingis formid of mannis craft, heyar nor euen to man in kynd, wam God ha&thorn; maad to his ymage and similitude; ne we owe not to rett hem more lek to Crist, or to seyntis, in form or representacoun, &thorn;an man, ne wor&thorn;iar ne holyar gostly; ne we howe not to hope ne trist in hem more, ne luf hem better, ne &yogh;ef hem moo &thorn;ingis, ne grace. God biddi&thorn; vs honor man many fold, and for many causes; and it is not were he biddi&thorn; so worschip &thorn;er ymagis, but his forbeding to worschip hem is opunly found. And many veniaunces are schorid to her worschipars, for &thorn;us is writun in holy writ, Wat profiti&thorn; a grauen &thorn;ing? for his feynar ha&thorn; hopid<NOTE PLACE="marg">Hab. ij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> in his feynid &thorn;ingis, &thorn;at he schuld mak doumb simulacre. Wo to him &thorn;at sei&thorn; to a tre, be sterid, and a stil ston, arise; we&thorn;er it schal not ken sciens? Lo it is helid wi&thorn; gold, and ilk spirit is not in &thorn;e bowell. And eft, &thorn;e trees polist of forgars, and engilt, and<NOTE PLACE="marg">Bar. uj<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> 
<PB REF="00000150.tif" N="86"> siluerid, is fals, and may not speke; &thorn;ey are bout in ilk price, and in hem is no spirit. Wi&thorn; [out] feet &thorn;ey are born in schuldres, schewing to men &thorn;er on nobeley; &thorn;ey schal be confoundid &thorn;at worschipun hem. If &thorn;ei fal vn to &thorn;e &yogh;er&thorn;, &thorn;ey schal not rise of hem silf: if ani sett hem vp, &thorn;ey schal not stand. And if &thorn;ei &thorn;ole ani iuel or good of ani, &thorn;ei schal not quit; &thorn;ey may not ordeyn a king, ne do a wey, ne &yogh;ef riches, ne quit iuel. If ani vow a vow to hem, and quit it not, &thorn;ey schal not ax it; &thorn;ei schal not liuer a man fro de&thorn;, ne pulle a wey &thorn;e feble fro &thorn;e mi&yogh;tiare; &thorn;ei restore not &thorn;e blind to &thorn;e sy&yogh;t, ne liuer man fro need; &thorn;ey schal not haue mercy of &thorn;e wydowe, ne do wel to &thorn;e faderles; &thorn;ei han no feling; &thorn;ei are forgid of forgers, and of goldsmi&thorn;is; &thorn;ei schal not ellis be, not but os &thorn;e prestis wel; &thorn;ey schal lefe fals &thorn;ingis, and repreue &thorn;o &thorn;at are to cum after; &thorn;ey reyse not a king to regioun, &thorn;ey schal not &yogh;eue reyn to men; &thorn;ey schal not deme dome, ne liuer &thorn;e regioun fro wrong, for &thorn;ey may no &thorn;ing; &thorn;ey schal noi&thorn;er curse kyngis, ne blesse; &thorn;ei schal not schew tokunis in heuen, ne schyn os &thorn;e sunne, ne &yogh;ef li&yogh;t as &thorn;e mone; after &thorn;ei schal be rotun, and schal be repreue in &thorn;e regioun. Better is &thorn;e iust man &thorn;at ha&thorn; no simulacre, for he schal be far fro repreuis. &THORN;us sei&thorn; &thorn;e prophet Baruc. And<NOTE PLACE="marg">Baruc.</NOTE> &thorn;e wise man sei&thorn;, &THORN;ei are vnblessid, and her trist a mong &thorn;e ded,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Sap. xiij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> &thorn;at han callid goddis &thorn;e werk of mannis handis, gold, siluer, and fynding of craft. Or if &thorn;e carpenter hew doun of &thorn;e wode a tre, and graue it diligently, and forg it, and mak a dwelling for it, setting it in a wal, festining it wi&thorn; irne &thorn;at it fal not, loking to it, witing &thorn;at it may not help it silf, it is an ymage. And of his substauns, and of his sonis, and of his weddingis making a vow he enquiri&thorn;. He schami&thorn; not to spek wi&thorn; it, &thorn;at is wi&thorn; out sowle: and for hele he praye&thorn; &thorn;e seek, and for lif &thorn;e dede, and incalli&thorn; in to help it &thorn;at is vnprofitable; and for jurney axi&thorn; of it &thorn;at is vnprofitable in all &thorn;ingis. Blessid &thorn;e tre &thorn;at ri&yogh;tfulnes is don by; but &thorn;is &thorn;at is maad<NOTE PLACE="marg">Sap. xiu<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> an idol bi hand, is cursid, and he &thorn;at maad it. &THORN;erfor respice schal 
<PB REF="00000151.tif" N="87"> not be idols of nacouns; for &thorn;e createris of God are maad in to hate, and foundingis to &thorn;e soul of men, and to fot trappis in to feet of vnwyse men. For &thorn;e multitude brow&yogh;t to bi &thorn;e spice of &thorn;e warke, now &thorn;ei &yogh;eue to hold os God &thorn;at bi forn was honored as a man. And &thorn;is ha&thorn; ben &thorn;e desseit of mannis lif; for men deser|uing oi&thorn;er to affeccoun, oi&thorn;er to kyngis, &thorn;ey han &yogh;euen &thorn;e incom|municable name to trees and to stonis; and it sufficied hem not han errid about &thorn;e sciens of God, but lyuing in bateyl of vnkun|ning, &thorn;us many and gret iuel &thorn;ey calle pees; forso&thorn; oi&thorn;er sacrify|ing &thorn;er sonis, or making merk sacrifices, or hauing warks ful of wodnes, &thorn;ey kepe noi&thorn;er clene lif, ne wedding, but on sle&thorn; an o&thorn;er bi enemy [? envy], and vowtrand, or doing a vowtri, drying, and al o&thorn;er mengid to gidre, blud, mansleyng, &thorn;eft, feyning, corrupcoun, vnfei&thorn;fulnes, trouby, periury, noys, wasting of &thorn;e goodis of God, filyng of soulis, chaunging of ber&thorn;e, vnstedfastnes of wedding, vnkynd lechery, and vnchastite, &THORN;e worschiping of cursid idols is &thorn;e bikynning, cause, and ende of all iuel; for wil &thorn;ey joyen, oi&thorn;er &thorn;ei wax wode, or prophecyen fals &thorn;ingis, or lyuen vniustly, or for sweren hem sone. Wil &thorn;ei trist in &thorn;e idol &thorn;at is wi&thorn; out soule, swering iuel, &thorn;ey wen hem not be noyed; &thorn;er for bo&thorn; schal cum wor&thorn;ly to hem, for iuel &thorn;ei felid of God, tenting to idols. And vniustly &thorn;ei sware in idol, dispicing ri&yogh;tfulnes.</P>
<P>But &thorn;u sey a&yogh;en, &thorn;at &thorn;es, and o&thorn;er swilk, are seid of idols &thorn;at vnfei&thorn;ful men worschipid as &thorn;er god, and in wilk &thorn;ei worschipid deuel, and &thorn;at forgid to &thorn;e liknes of no &thorn;ing; for &thorn;e apostil sei&thorn;, An idol is no &thorn;ing in &thorn;e world; &thorn;ey are not seid of ymagis brout<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Cor. uiij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> in bi &thorn;e kirk. For &thorn;e decre sei&thorn;, Cristun men callen not worscipful<NOTE PLACE="marg">Decre.</NOTE> ymagis goddis, ne seruen not to hem as to goddis, ne put not hope of help in hem, ne abidi&thorn; not in hem &thorn;e dome of help to cum, but &thorn;ei worschip hem to &thorn;e memory and record of ra&thorn;er men, but &thorn;ei serue not hem wi&thorn; Goddis worschip, ne any creature; &thorn;us sei&thorn; &thorn;e decre. Forso&thorn; &thorn;e decre sei&thorn; wel, acording holi writ, &thorn;at cristun 
<PB REF="00000152.tif" N="88"> men serue not to hem, ne to ani creature, bi Goddis worschip; &thorn;at is &thorn;ei how not to serue to hem; ne verrey cristun men don not; &thorn;erfor &thorn;ei &thorn;at don are not verrey cristun. And it is to note, &thorn;at in diueris maners a man ha&thorn; a god. First alle we han God Almi&yogh;ti, &thorn;at is God to alle, and autor of lif, and &yogh;efar of alle goodis. &THORN;e secound, he ha&thorn; god &thorn;is &thorn;at he moost lufi&thorn;, and wer in he tristi&thorn;, as in God; and &thorn;us mani han mani goddis, &thorn;at &thorn;ei sett in &thorn;er affeccoun bifor God Almi&yogh;ti, and to serue &thorn;eym ra&thorn;er, and wam &thorn;ei more worschip; os it semi&thorn; of dedis, and of sawis of &thorn;e scrip|ture, and of seyntis. And in diuers maner do&thorn; man idolatre; first wan he setti&thorn; in his affeccoun ani &thorn;ing bi for God; &thorn;e secunde, of vndu ordre and cause: and &thorn;us on &thorn;re wise; first, &yogh;euing to &thorn;e creature &thorn;ing onli to God du; &thorn;e secound, honoring God vn|honestly; &thorn;e &thorn;rid, honoring &thorn;e creature for God, and vnhonestly. And &thorn;us man do&thorn; idolatre in hert synning; for als mani idols ha&thorn; a man, as he ha&thorn; dedly synnis. Also of his gold and siluer a man maki&thorn; an idol, wan he worschipi&thorn; it a boun God, for &thorn;e apostil sei&thorn;,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Col. iij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> &thorn;at auarice is seruice of idolis. And &thorn;us man hoping ouermikil or tristing in a ymage, or making o&thorn;er to trist &thorn;er in, &thorn;at he may coueytously geyt &thorn;er good, forso&thorn; he maki&thorn; to him &thorn;er of an idol, and &thorn;us in maner do&thorn; as foul idolatre as e&thorn;en men. And &thorn;is may not be noyed to be don, for many trowen &thorn;at ymage to be God, and many trowen Goddis vertu sogetly to be &thorn;er in, and &thorn;us &thorn;ey are more affect to o ymage &thorn;an to an o&thorn;er; &thorn;at doutles is idolatre, as trewe men seyn. And &thorn;us mani erren, and &thorn;is were to be mendid. For &thorn;us sei&thorn; Austeyn, Vtterly &thorn;ei han deseruid to erre,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Austeyn.</NOTE> &thorn;at han sowt Crist and his Apostlis, not in holy boks, but in peyn|tid walls. Also Clement sei&thorn;, If we wil verreyly worschip Goddis<NOTE PLACE="marg">Clement.</NOTE> ymage, doing wel to a man, honor &thorn;e verey ymage of God in him. In ilk man forso&thorn; is &thorn;e ymage of God, but &thorn;e similitud of God is not in alle, but were &thorn;e sowle is beninge, and to mynd pure. &THORN;erfor if &yogh;e wil verily worschip &thorn;e ymage of God, we opun to &yogh;ow &thorn;is &thorn;at 
<PB REF="00000153.tif" N="89"> is verrey, &thorn;at &yogh;e do wel to a man &thorn;at is maad to &thorn;e ymage of God, and &yogh;eue him honor and reuerens; &yogh;euit meyt to &thorn;e hungry, drink to &thorn;e &thorn;risty, clo&thorn;is to &thorn;e nakid, minstring to &thorn;e seek, herbarow to &thorn;e straunger, and necessarijs to &thorn;e prisouner. And &thorn;is is &thorn;at schal be gessid verrily done; &thorn;eis gon so myche in to &thorn;e honor of God, &thorn;at he &thorn;at do&thorn; not &thorn;eis &thorn;ingis, if he may, schal be trowid to do despit to &thorn;e ymage of God. Wat honor of God is &thorn;is, to ren a bout bi tre, and stone, and formis, and honor as God veyn figeris, and wi&thorn; out soule, and despice man, in wam is verily &thorn;e ymage of God. But and be&thorn; certeyn, &thorn;at if ani do mansleing, spowsbrekyng, or ani &thorn;ing of wrong to man, in &thorn;is &thorn;ing &thorn;e ymage of God is sylid; &thorn;is sei&thorn; Clement. &THORN;erfor now, as Poule biddi&thorn;, fle we for worschiping of idols; for<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Cor. x<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> now is God maad man, and perid ha&thorn; a man, and schewid to us al &thorn;ingis of his godhed &thorn;at are to lif, and to pite, and we are maad on wi&thorn; Crist, and his body, and his membris, and quiknid of his spirit; &thorn;at we schuld do no idolatre, ne worschip no &thorn;ing for no iuel ende; &thorn;at we schuld mak now no dead ymagis, ne idolis of our self, &thorn;at we do wan we are wi&thorn; out &thorn;e spirit of Crist, and lif in pride, lechery, and fals coueytis, and swilk o&thorn;er synnis; &thorn;an are we foul idols and foul fendis ymagis, as Crisostom merki&thorn; wel. And if<NOTE PLACE="marg">Crisost.</NOTE> we worschip and luf &thorn;eis &thorn;ingis, and o&thorn;er men for hem, doutles we are foul, doing idolatrie; and &thorn;us we do wi&thorn; o&thorn;er createris wan we honor hem a&yogh;en Goddis bidding, and a mis, and for foul ende, as Austeyn declari&thorn;. And &thorn;us we schuld flee idolatrie &thorn;at we do wi&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="marg">Austeyn.</NOTE> men, &thorn;at honor we mikyl more &thorn;an Ihu Crist; for wan a man is sett to do &thorn;e office of God, and ha&thorn; not in him &thorn;e vertu of God, ne wit, ne wil, ne dede, wat is he but ymage and idol maad of men. As Bernard sei&thorn;, A kynge vnwise is but a nape in &thorn;e house rofe;<NOTE PLACE="marg">Bernard.</NOTE> and &thorn;us it is of prestis, prelatis, and of o&thorn;er religioun, in &thorn;e same maner. Wil &thorn;u hast habit and schauin croun, and o&thorn;er signis wi&thorn; out vertu and lif of spirit, and wi&thorn; out &thorn;e dede; &thorn;u art but peyntid and lied ymage, as Jerom witnessi&thorn; wel, and idols and similacris.<NOTE PLACE="marg">Jerom.</NOTE> 
<PB REF="00000154.tif" N="90"> Archedeacoun sei&thorn;, As &thorn;e he&thorn;un men had sex kyndis of similacris,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Archedea|coun.</NOTE> cleyen, treen, brasun, stonun, silueren, and golden, so han lordis now sex kyndis of prelatis. Cleyen similacris are fleschli prelatis, of &thorn;e wilk &thorn;e Salme sei&thorn;, I schal do hem awey as &thorn;e cley of &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">Salme xuiij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> stretis. Treen similacris are prelatis rude in &thorn;er doctrin, and on|sensible of wit. Jerom sei&thorn;, &THORN;e tre is woundun in siluer, &thorn;ei are<NOTE PLACE="marg">Jerom.</NOTE> seid to be maad in to prelatis, for &thorn;ei are tan vp wi&thorn; out mater of dignite, bering vp in her schuldres &thorn;at are not but in opynioun. Brasyn prelatis are &thorn;ei &thorn;at han worldli eloquence; of wilk &thorn;e apostil sei&thorn;, I am maad as bras sounning, or as &thorn;e cymbal tynking.<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Cor. xiij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> Stonen prelatis are &thorn;ey endurid in temporal &thorn;ingis bi &thorn;e affeccounis of men &thorn;at &thorn;ey brek bi seculer power. Silueryn are &thorn;ey &thorn;at seyn wi&thorn; &thorn;er maister to &thorn;e persewars of Crist in his membris, Wat wil &yogh;e &yogh;eue vs and we schal betray him to &yogh;ow? Goldun prelatis are &thorn;ey &thorn;at are maad only for nobelay of kyn; &thorn;us sei&thorn; he. In swilk men schuld idolatre be fled, for &thorn;ei schuld desir no worschip, obediens, ne seruice, but as God biddi&thorn; hem; so &thorn;at in hem God be honorid, seruid, and obeyed, and neuer bid but his biddingis; nor put not his bidding be hynd, for keping of her, for &thorn;us doyng &thorn;ei don werst idolatri, and taken to hem &thorn;e honor &thorn;at God schuld haue, and putten him out. And &thorn;us men schuld obey hem, and trust and serue, os God biddi&thorn;, and no far&thorn;er; &thorn;at &thorn;ei do not ido|latrie wi&thorn; hem, if &thorn;ei obey to &thorn;er biddingis a&yogh;en Goddis biddingis, or trust to &thorn;er wordis, if &thorn;ey be not wordis of God.</P>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="25" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XXV. The Gospel writun not to be wor|schippid.</HEAD>
<P>&THORN;is is an o&thorn;er point; &thorn;at &thorn;e gospel writun is not to be worschipid. As to &thorn;is I haue rehersid &thorn;e sentens of Crisostom, were he sei&thorn; &thorn;us: Sum wil schew hem holiar &thorn;an o&thorn;er, &thorn;ei bind to gidre &thorn;e part of an hem, or of heris of seyntis, and hangen vp hem. O vnpite!<NOTE PLACE="marg">Crisost.</NOTE> &thorn;ei weling schew more holines in &thorn;er clo&thorn;es, &thorn;an in &thorn;e body of Crist; &thorn;at he &thorn;at &yogh;et &thorn;e body of Crist was not helid, schuld be sauid bi &thorn;e holines of &thorn;e hem of his clo&thorn;, &thorn;at he depering in &thorn;e mercy of God, trust in &thorn;e clo&thorn;is of men. And &thorn;e same sentens 
<PB REF="00000155.tif" N="91"> he ha&thorn; a&yogh;en hem &thorn;at han &thorn;e gospel writun hanging a bout &thorn;e neke for &yogh;ele. Wan &thorn;ei han hirid it in &thorn;e kirk and are not &yogh;elid, and axi&thorn; we&thorn;er is &thorn;e gospel in leuis of wordis, or in vertu. If it were in &thorn;e leuis, &thorn;u hangist it resounably, but now it is not in &thorn;e leuis of &thorn;e parchemyn, but in &thorn;e vertu; and bi hering &thorn;u art not &yogh;elid, &thorn;erfor in veyn &thorn;u hangist &thorn;e leuis a bout &thorn;i neke. And Jerom<NOTE PLACE="marg">Jerom.</NOTE> sei&thorn;, Wene we not &thorn;e gospel to be in wordis of writingis, but in wit, not in ouer face, but in &thorn;e merowe, not in &thorn;e leuis of wordis, but in rot of resoun; &thorn;us sei&thorn; he. But worschiping is tan on mani maner wis; I suppose &thorn;at we how not to honor &thorn;e gospel &thorn;us, &thorn;at is to sey, &thorn;e henk, or &thorn;e parchemyn, and &thorn;e figeris; wening werk|yng to be gostly in hem, or &thorn;e spirit of God, or &thorn;e godhed; noi&thorn;er &thorn;at swilk writing bi hem silf drif a wey fendis, or seknes, or kep fro harmis, as sum not vndirstonding wel gostly &thorn;ingis demun; &thorn;ow we, taking &yogh;ed to &thorn;e &thorn;ing, may after agre worschip such &thorn;ingis writun, as men seeng &thorn;e letter or selle of a lord, may bow him, or do of his hod; and to &thorn;is sentens I suppose Austeyn to<NOTE PLACE="marg">Austeyn.</NOTE> cord. If he comend hem &thorn;at worschipun &thorn;e gospel writun or o&thorn;er writingis, not for &thorn;ei rettid hem in hem self holiar or vertuosar, or more effectual, &thorn;an o&thorn;er, but for &thorn;e honor and reuerens &thorn;at &thorn;ei haue finaly in &thorn;e &thorn;ing takun bi hem. But if &thorn;u sey, bi &thorn;e towching of Cristis body mani were helid, and bi &thorn;e towching of his clo&thorn;is, as &thorn;e gospel schewi&thorn;, and &thorn;e apostle sent sudarijs to put on men schaking wi&thorn; fendis, and &thorn;ei were dryuen a wey. And it is seid, &thorn;at a woman maad an ymage of Crist, and an herbe bi touching &thorn;er of reyceyuid &thorn;e vertu of heling, &thorn;er for man may tryst in swilk &thorn;ingis. And to &thorn;is I seid &thorn;us, bi sentens of doctors, &thorn;at Crist is more excellent and vertuosar &thorn;an o&thorn;er createris; &thorn;e se|cound, &thorn;ei &thorn;at were helid were not helid sympli bi &thorn;e touching, but for &thorn;e trust &thorn;at &thorn;ei strechid finaly in to God. And for &thorn;is sei&thorn; Crist, &THORN;i fei&thorn; ha&thorn; maad &thorn;e saue. And eft sei&thorn; &thorn;e bok, &thorn;at noi&thorn;er<NOTE PLACE="marg">Marc. u<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> herb ne plaster helid hem, but &thorn;e word of God, &thorn;at heli&thorn; al &thorn;ing; 
<PB REF="00000156.tif" N="92"> and mani touchid and were not helid, noi&thorn;er to body nor to soule. To &thorn;e &thorn;rid it is seid, &thorn;at suilk &thorn;ingis were first &thorn;olid, and miraclis for rude men, and hem to be confermid in &thorn;e fei&thorn;. But now &thorn;e opun is opun, it is veyn and supersticion to &thorn;e peple to haue swilk &thorn;ingis. &THORN;us sei&thorn; Crisostom, Sum miraclis are of God, and sum of<NOTE PLACE="marg">Chrisos|tom.</NOTE> &thorn;e fend, for it is to kum power to be &yogh;euen to &thorn;e fend to do signis not of good part, &thorn;er for we how to seek if it be necessary after &thorn;e tyme or not. If Crist dede miraclis for &thorn;e conferming of &thorn;e vn|fei&thorn;ful, it is opun, wan non is vnfei&thorn;ful, it is no nede to do miraclis; &thorn;erfor he &thorn;at do&thorn; an vnprofitable signe is a fals profit, for he do&thorn; not to edifie o&thorn;er in &thorn;e fei&thorn;, but &thorn;at he boost him silf in his dede. &THORN;us sei&thorn; Bede, and rehersi&thorn; Gregor, &THORN;e tokunnis of miraclis, in &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">Bede.</NOTE> beginning of &thorn;e kirk, were only necessary &thorn;at sche schuld growe to &thorn;e fei&thorn;, norischid wi&thorn; miraclis, as we watteren plantis til &thorn;ey han ben rotid, and &thorn;an we cesser to watter.</P>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="26" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XXVI. Charmis.</HEAD>
<P>&THORN;eis are o&thorn;er two poyntis. On &thorn;at charmis on no maner are leful. An o&thorn;er, &thorn;at it is supersticious to hang wordis at &thorn;e nek. As to &thorn;eis I haue seid &thorn;us; In &thorn;e law of God is &thorn;us writun, Wan<NOTE PLACE="marg">Deut. xuiij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> &thorn;u cumyst in to &thorn;e lond &thorn;at &thorn;i Lord God schal &yogh;eue &thorn;e, be war &thorn;at &thorn;u wil not folow &thorn;e abhominacoun of &thorn;e folk &thorn;at &thorn;er be, ne be &thorn;er not found in &thorn;e &thorn;at compasi&thorn; his sone or dowter, drawing bi &thorn;e fire, ne &thorn;at aski&thorn; ariolers, nor dremis, ne chitering of briddis, ne &thorn;at &thorn;er be wiche, ne enchaunter, &thorn;at is chermar in our spech, ne &thorn;at axe counseil of hem &thorn;at han iuel sperits, noi&thorn;er at diuinar, ne seek of dead &thorn;ingis &thorn;e trow&thorn;; for &thorn;e Lord wlati&thorn; of &thorn;eis &thorn;ingis, and of &thorn;eis maner of felonies he schal do &thorn;eis folk a wey in &thorn;i entry; &thorn;u schalt be perfit, and wi&thorn; out spot wi&thorn; &thorn;i Lord God. And eft, Bow &thorn;u<NOTE PLACE="marg">Lev. xix<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> not to &thorn;er wicchis, ne axe no &thorn;ing of &thorn;er ariolers, &thorn;at &yogh;e be not polut be hem. &yogh;e schal not a wat dremis, ne diuyn bi criing of briddis, ne clip &thorn;e hed in to round, ne schaf &thorn;e hed, ne calle vp on &thorn;e dead; &yogh;e schal not prik &yogh;or flesch, ne mak to &yogh;ow ani figeris, ne stigmes, &thorn;at are woundis. But if &thorn;ey sey to &yogh;ow, seek of Phi|<NOTE PLACE="marg">Isa. viij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> 
<PB REF="00000157.tif" N="93"> toneris and of diuineris, &thorn;at gnasten wi&thorn; &thorn;er te&thorn; in her chauntingis, we&thorn;er not a peple schal seek visioun of her God, for &thorn;e quek and &thorn;e dead? &THORN;erfor go&thorn; more to &thorn;e lawe and to &thorn;e witnes, &thorn;at if &thorn;ei sey not after &thorn;is woord, morow li&yogh;t schal not be to hem. Also &thorn;us writi&thorn; Austeyn, and is put in decrees, Fei&thorn;ful prestis ammonest<NOTE PLACE="marg">Austeyn.</NOTE> &thorn;e peple, &thorn;at &thorn;ei wit &thorn;er wichecraftis and enchauntingis to may do no &thorn;ing of remedy to ani seknes of man, ne of best, noi&thorn;er to best langering, halting, or sare, or doing to lech ani &thorn;ing, but &thorn;at &thorn;ei are panteris of &thorn;e wold enemye, bi wilk &thorn;e fals fend enforci&thorn; to deceywe mankynd. If ani clerk vse &thorn;eis &thorn;ingis be he degradid, and &thorn;e lewid man &thorn;at vse &thorn;eis &thorn;ingis be cursid. And eft &thorn;us, A<NOTE PLACE="marg">Austeyn.</NOTE> wayti&thorn; not &thorn;eis Egipcian daies, &thorn;at we call dysmal, ne kalendis of Janiuer, in wilk sum seyingis, and comessacouns, and &yogh;eftis, are &yogh;euyn to gidre, as in to begynning of good &yogh;ere, ne mon&thorn;is, ne tymys, ne &yogh;eris, ne dayes, ne course of &thorn;e sunne, ne &thorn;e mone, for &yogh;e &thorn;at a waytun &thorn;eis or ani o&thorn;er diuiningis, desteneys of auguris, or tenten to hem, or consenten to &thorn;e waytars vnprofitably, and wi&thorn; out cause, he howi&thorn; more to his dampnacoun &thorn;an to his saluacoun; or &thorn;ei &thorn;at seek bi noumbre of lettres, or of &thorn;e men [moon?], and figer of nigramauncy, &thorn;e lif or de&thorn; of &thorn;e seek, or wel&thorn; or disess to cum, or &thorn;ei &thorn;at tentun to dremis writun, and falsly tytlid in Daniel's name, or canelis &thorn;at are callid of &thorn;e holy apostolis, or chitering of briddus, or sich o&thorn;er, for hous to be maad, or weddingis to be couplid, or in gedering of herbis, sei&thorn; ani charme but &thorn;e <I>pater noster</I>, or &thorn;e crede, or putti&thorn; ani strowis wi&thorn; figeris writun on men for any infirmite, or vp on bestis, or tenden to wiche falsnes in hailes or tempestis, &thorn;ey &thorn;at trowen to swilk &thorn;ingis, or gon to &thorn;e hous of hem, wite &thorn;ei hem to haue brokyn &thorn;e cristun fei&thorn;, and &thorn;e baptem, and to be paynims and apostatais, &thorn;at is goyng o bak, and to be &thorn;e enemyes of God, and greuowsly to haue incurrid his wra&thorn;, be [but?] if &thorn;ei mend bi &thorn;e penaunce of &thorn;e kirk be recounsilid; for &thorn;e apostil sei&thorn;, We&thorn;er het &yogh;e or drynk or do ani o&thorn;er &thorn;ing, do all<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Cor. x<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> 
<PB REF="00000158.tif" N="94"> &thorn;ingis in &thorn;e name of our Lord Ihu Crist, in wam we lifin, are sterid, and ben. &THORN;eis sawis and sich o&thorn;er like are trow&thorn; endles, and bidun to us to be kepid wi&thorn; out dispensacoun bo&thorn; of God and of &thorn;e kirk; as &thorn;e decre sei&thorn;, &thorn;at &thorn;ow no &thorn;ing of iuel be schewid to<NOTE PLACE="marg">Decre.</NOTE> be in swilk &thorn;ingis, neuer&thorn;eles &yogh;et &thorn;ei are defendid of &thorn;e kirk to fei&thorn;ful men, &thorn;at &thorn;ei go not a&yogh;en vnder &thorn;e spice of diuining to &thorn;e wold worschipping of idols. And &thorn;us &thorn;ei are bidun to vs to kepe &thorn;at we how not to rette &thorn;eis &thorn;ingis in to God til vs, noi&thorn;er &thorn;is to cause in vs goostly vertues ne maners, noi&thorn;er &thorn;ei may &yogh;eue til vs grace ne hele, but if we kepe Cristis biddingis; ne &thorn;ei may not harme vs, if we do his biddingis, for non aduersite schal noy vs, if wickidnes lord not in vs. And if we do his biddingis, al &thorn;ingis schal obey to vs, os &thorn;ei are maad to serue vs, and to be soget and boner to vs, and we how not to vse &thorn;eis on ani maner, not but as God biddi&thorn;, and counseili&thorn; vs; &thorn;erfor &thorn;is semi&thorn; helful, if ani be vexid wi&thorn; seeknes, or greuid wi&thorn; vniust nei&yogh;bor, or on ani o&thorn;er seid greuid in ani maner, &thorn;at he say wi&thorn; Job to God, How many<NOTE PLACE="marg">Job. xiij<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> wickidnes haue I and synnis, schewe me my felownies and my defaultis, &thorn;at I wit wat me lacki&thorn;, and &thorn;at I mend my sarow, and haue mend &thorn;e &thorn;ingis &thorn;at I haue misdon, o&thorn;er be vnkunning, or infirmite, or be maleyce, and tak &thorn;eis disessis for mending and mercy of God, and mikil less &thorn;an I haue deseruid; and tak &thorn;an swilk medicynis os God ha&thorn; maad, and bidun, and desseyue not veynly himsilf, ne incur not more indignacoun, for it is certeyn &thorn;at God ha&thorn; don many veniaunce for &thorn;eis felownies, and al are writun to our disciplin, correccoun, and warning. And who &thorn;at nedi&thorn; ani wisdam, or help for ani &thorn;ing, axe of God, as seynt Jame<NOTE PLACE="marg">Jac. i<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> sei&thorn;, and al &thorn;at is spedful schal plentiuowsly be &yogh;euun to him. But neuer&thorn;eles, as comyn spech techi&thorn; vs, and Goddis lawe, and clerkis charmis are callid in diuers maner. And &thorn;eis &thorn;ingis may be vsid in syndre maner, &thorn;erfor it semi&thorn; to me spedy to clere sum wat &thorn;is maner; &thorn;erfor I suppose her, &thorn;at charmis and enchaunt|mentis 
<PB REF="00000159.tif" N="95"> for bidun &thorn;at &thorn;e it are &thorn;at are brout in bi fendis curst, and bi stering of fendis, a&yogh;en &thorn;e bidding of God, and also be mannis vanite and foly, wi&thorn; out ground of God Almi&yogh;ti, and in wilk men trystun of help wi&thorn; outun him, and oftun a&yogh;en as &yogh;e&thorn;un and vn|fei&thorn;ful don; &thorn;us we callid charmers &thorn;o &thorn;at wil bi &thorn;er curst haue a &thorn;ing &thorn;ow it plece not God. And &thorn;is schewi&thorn; what is a charme, we&thorn;er it be charme maad or writun, or &thorn;e wirking of &thorn;e charmar. And enchauntors are &thorn;oo &thorn;at in callun fendis to ken hem &thorn;ingis, or to telle hem &thorn;ingis be for, or to help hem, we&thorn;er &thorn;ei do it bi preyor, or bi sacrifice offrid to hem, or bi ani o&thorn;er vnleful maner. And swilk we callen phitoners. Also ariolers &thorn;oo &thorn;at maken placis to here God, or wenun to bow God to do for &thorn;e place, as Balaam &thorn;at sowt to curse &thorn;e peple a&yogh;en Goddis bidding: and wan he mi&yogh;t not curse hem in o place, he sout to curse hem in a no&thorn;er, and went &thorn;at God wold haue bowed tul hem. And ruspiceris are &thorn;oo &thorn;at loken to horis or tymis, are goddis or o&thorn;er gouernoris, or wen &thorn;at &thorn;ei may bowe God to do &thorn;ing in on houre, &thorn;at he wil not do in an o&thorn;er. An augurreris we calle &thorn;oo &thorn;at tentun to &thorn;e garring and fliyng of briddus, as if &thorn;ei brout good or harme, or God be led o&thorn;er wise &thorn;er bi, to do o&thorn;er wyse &thorn;an as is iust, and good, and merciful, and trewe. And dremridars we calle &thorn;oo &thorn;at tentun to dremis, os if &thorn;ey drem bi original and principal cause of God; or iuil or good bi led bi &thorn;e drem to do veynly, or vniustly, or to be chongid. Nigramauncers are &thorn;ei &thorn;at bi figeris or markyngis vp on &thorn;e dead body of best or of man, &thorn;us enforci&thorn; to geit wityng, or to wirk, or &thorn;us to bow God. And on &thorn;is maner God forbedi&thorn; to clep &thorn;e hed in to round, or to schaf &thorn;e berd, or to mak &thorn;us ani figeris on &thorn;e dead, os to geit ani &thorn;ing &thorn;er by, but if God wel, or ellis to bow him or chong him &thorn;er bi; &thorn;us we callen &thorn;e magis, &thorn;oo &thorn;at calculun bi &thorn;e sternis &thorn;ingis to cum, wening as &thorn;ei were Goddis gouernours, chef of &thorn;is world, or ellis &thorn;at God may be chaungid, and led bi hem. And &thorn;us are callid geomanceris, &thorn;at werkun bi 
<PB REF="00000160.tif" N="96"> &thorn;e &yogh;er&thorn;. And idromauncers, &thorn;at &thorn;us wirkun bi &thorn;e watir. Ayero|mauncers &thorn;at wirkun bi &thorn;e eyre. Piromauncers &thorn;at wirkun bi &thorn;e fire. And spices are content vnder &thorn;eis maney, as doctors declarun wel; Austeyn, Gregor, Basil, and Isidor, Crisostom, Lincoln, and o&thorn;er. And holy writ in many places dampni&thorn; &thorn;eis &thorn;ingis. And &thorn;us sortilegers &thorn;at settun &thorn;er curst finaly in &thorn;e cauil, and wenun &thorn;at &thorn;is ledi&thorn; or bowi&thorn; ani &thorn;ing finali to profit ende. And &thorn;us Austeyn<NOTE PLACE="marg">Austeyn.</NOTE> sei&thorn;, &thorn;at &thorn;er are &thorn;owsand spices of veyn supersticoun, &thorn;at is, &thorn;ing veynly ordeynid, and veynly vsid, and veynly &thorn;at men atristun in, and all silk &thorn;ingis are forbidun &yogh;e in &thorn;is, &thorn;at &thorn;u schalt not tak his name in veyn. And syn God ha&thorn; forfendid &thorn;eis &thorn;ingis, and holi doctoris bo&thorn; and &thorn;e kirk, as is oft declarid, it is veyn and supersti|coun, and &thorn;e kind of idolatrie to vse such &thorn;ingis a&yogh;en &thorn;us mani biddingis, autoritees, witnes and counseilis, be for &thorn;at man may proue bi holy writ, and wittnes of seyntis, for &thorn;is is so&thorn;, &thorn;at is not contrari to himsilf, ne holy writt contrary to itsilf, ne fei&thorn;ful doc|toris contrary her to, &thorn;at seyn to us how &thorn;eis &thorn;ingis are iuel. And if men sey &thorn;at swilk &thorn;ingis are spedeful, for God ha&thorn; &yogh;euun vertu in herbe, in word, and in ston, and men seen oft at ee &thorn;at swilk &thorn;ingis help, it is so&thorn; &thorn;at God ha&thorn; &yogh;euen vertu in all &thorn;ingis, &thorn;at he ha&thorn; maad and ordeynid how &thorn;ei schal be vsid, and in to wat ende. And so how ilk man to vse hem as he ordeyni&thorn;, but not a&yogh;en his ordinauns, ne wi&thorn; out. And so &thorn;is &yogh;eui&thorn; not proue, &thorn;at &thorn;ei profit hangid a bout &thorn;e nek; bi for &thorn;ei men fyndun writun and bidun. And &thorn;an men seyn swilk &thorn;ingis help; &thorn;is is no certeyn wi&thorn; outen bettar proue, or grounde; for as doctors declarun wel, sum tyme men wen to see a &thorn;ing wan &thorn;ei see it not, os is schewid bi jogulors, dremers, and rafars. And sum tyme man is holpun bi treyst &thorn;at he ha&thorn; in o &thorn;ing, or bi dred entrid, and not bi &thorn;at &thorn;ing as phisek techi&thorn; and experiens. And sum tyme men wenun to be helpid, whan he is mikile more hendrid. And wan &thorn;e fend ha&thorn; men in daunger, sum tyme he deseiui&thorn; hem tul &thorn;ey do him sacrifice, and 
<PB REF="00000161.tif" N="97"> &thorn;an he cessi&thorn; to harme hem, or fendi&thorn; hem ouer wyl. And &thorn;us &thorn;ei are seid to help. But wan &thorn;is is lokid fei&thorn;fuly, &thorn;ey are wel more hendrid &thorn;an helpid, wyl &thorn;ei are brout in to mis trow&thorn;, and hopi&thorn; to haue helpe wi&thorn; out God. As &thorn;e decre declari&thorn; wel: And<NOTE PLACE="marg">Decre.</NOTE> if &thorn;ei sey it be semi&thorn; bi holy writ &thorn;at enchauntmentis are good, for &thorn;e Salm sei&thorn; &thorn;us, Synnars are alienid fro &thorn;e wombe, &thorn;ei haue errid<NOTE PLACE="marg">Salm. luii<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> fro &thorn;e wombe, &thorn;ei spek fals &thorn;ingis; wodnes to hem vp on &thorn;e simi|litude of &thorn;e serpent, os of def heddir stuppend her &yogh;eris, &thorn;at he here not &thorn;e voyce of &thorn;e enchaunter, and of &thorn;e venyn maker, en|chaunting wisly. To &thorn;is we sey &thorn;at God bi his ensaumpel re|proui&thorn; synnars &thorn;at stoppun her &yogh;eris, and wil not here his word, ne cast out &thorn;e wold venyn, and be helid, and reseyue vertu to &yogh;ele o&thorn;er. It folowi&thorn; not of &thorn;is, wi&thorn; out more ground, &thorn;at he approui&thorn; her charm forbydun. For in holy writ he enformi&thorn; men and prestis bi similitudis, and &yogh;et he forbedi&thorn; men to vse hem; as he sei&thorn;, &thorn;e oxe knowi&thorn; his weldar, and &thorn;e as &thorn;e crib of his lord; leding vs bi<NOTE PLACE="marg">Isa. i<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> hem to know our God, and reprouing vs if we know him not. And neuer&thorn;eles be biddi&thorn; vs, Wel &yogh;e not be maad as hors or mule; in<NOTE PLACE="marg">Salm. xxxi<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> wam is not vnderstonding. And &thorn;e apostil sei&thorn;, Wil &yogh;e not be<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Cor. xiu<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> maad barnes in wit, but in malice be &yogh;e litil. &THORN;erfor seek &yogh;e a pleynar ground, &thorn;at wil stable &thorn;eis charmis, &thorn;at men usen amis. But God for his endles mercy kepe fro &thorn;e malice of &thorn;er charmis, and charmers, and coniurars, wichis, sortilegeris, and o&thorn;er &thorn;at are put in &thorn;e general sentens and cursing of &thorn;e kirk, fro all &thorn;at wirkun bi fendis curst, or veynli wi&thorn; out God, and to wickid ende, and namly fro hem &thorn;at enforcen to charme in to iuel dedis, or not to obey to Cristis gospel, ne to &thorn;e teching of &thorn;e apostlis, and prophetis, and fei&thorn;ful doctors. Ne &thorn;at we schuld know it, ne lif &thorn;er after, seying &thorn;at we may not understond it, ne &thorn;e holy doctoris &thorn;at han expound it, wilk &thorn;e kirk ha&thorn; canoni&yogh;id, but wil led us after o&thorn;er dremis, and her ymaginacouns, blouing veynly wi&thorn; fleschli wit, tul &thorn;ei hold not Crist &thorn;e hed, ne go after him, ne sett in him &thorn;er 
<PB REF="00000162.tif" N="98"> ground; but can sey &thorn;at wordis of holy writt, and &thorn;at are canoni&yogh;ed of al holy kirk, soundun not wel, and wel lede vs bi a kirk &thorn;at &thorn;ey seyn erri&thorn; oft, and disseyui&thorn; and is deseyuid, begili&thorn; and is bigilid. God Almi&yogh;ty kepe vs fro &thorn;e malice of &thorn;er charmis, and fro &thorn;er supersticiositeis, vanites, errors, and desseytis; &thorn;at we no&thorn;er be disseyuid bi hem, ne disseue o&thorn;er men, ne bow not fro Crist tul a no&thorn;er, ne hold gospel o&thorn;er &thorn;an is; for &thorn;er is non o&thorn;er. And comfort he vs in &thorn;e power of his vertu, and in himsilf; and clo&thorn; he vs in his armor, &thorn;at we may a&yogh;enstond &thorn;e sautis of &thorn;e fend; for<NOTE PLACE="marg">Eph. ui<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> to vs is no wrestling a&yogh;en &thorn;e flesch and &thorn;e blud; but a&yogh;en princis and powers, a&yogh;en reulers of &thorn;is world, of &thorn;eis merknes, a&yogh;en gostlynes of wrechidnes, in heuenly &thorn;ingis; &thorn;erfor tak we &thorn;e armor of God, &thorn;at we ma a&yogh;enstond in iuel day, and stand perfit in all &thorn;ingis; gird &thorn;e lendis in trow&thorn;, clo&thorn;id &thorn;e habarioun of rit|fulnes, &thorn;e feet schod in &thorn;e making redy of Cristis gospel of pes, taking &thorn;e scheld of &thorn;e fei&thorn;, in &thorn;e wilk we may sleckun all &thorn;e firun dartis of the enemy. And &thorn;e helm of hel, and &thorn;e swerd of &thorn;e Spirit, &thorn;at is &thorn;e word of God; in ilk tyme preying, and biseking in spirit, and wakyng &thorn;er in ilk tyme, &thorn;at we may wet how it is to lif, and to answere to ilk, and to &yogh;eue resoun of &thorn;at fei&thorn; and hop &thorn;at is in vs. &THORN;us be comfortid in &thorn;e Lord. For now is no wrest|ling to vs a&yogh;en flesch and blud, noi&thorn;er to do fleschly batayl, noi&thorn;er to sle mennis bodies, nor &yogh;et to stryfe for fleschly &thorn;ingis, &thorn;at are but after &thorn;e flesch. Our wrestling is not only, ne principaly, a&yogh;en &thorn;eis &thorn;ingis, but a&yogh;en princis and powers, rewlars of &thorn;is world of &thorn;eis merknes, &thorn;ei are not only fendis and swilk wickid speritis, but &thorn;ei are also wickid men &thorn;at ledun &thorn;is world in blindnes, and error, and foli, and malice, and lettun hem to know Crist, and behetun hem grace, wan &thorn;ey mak hem sikir, ne wit not for &thorn;ei schal haue it. Wyl &thorn;ei hemsilf lyuen in &thorn;er corrupcoun, wot not how &thorn;ei may mak hemsilf sikir; &thorn;ey are rewlars of &thorn;e world of &thorn;eis derknes, for &thorn;ei hi&yogh;t men assoyling, wan &thorn;ei wit not if it be, and &thorn;ey led 
<PB REF="00000163.tif" N="99"> bo&thorn; himsilf and &thorn;eis &thorn;at &thorn;ey assoyl in blindnes, and desseyue bo&thorn;. And &thorn;us wan &thorn;ei condemp vniustly a iust man on many sidis, &thorn;ei led men in blindnes, and &thorn;us wan &thorn;ei erre are desseyuid and dis|seiuen, all &thorn;is is in mirknes. And &yogh;et &thorn;ey deny to men &thorn;e undir|stonding of &thorn;e gospel, and seyn men may not undirstond it, and &thorn;ei graunt &thorn;at &thorn;ei undirstond it not, and &thorn;ei wel bi deneris. And &thorn;us &thorn;ey may not deme but &thorn;at &thorn;ei lede &thorn;is world in mirknes. But it is scham to hem to sey &thorn;us, &thorn;at ere kirk erri&thorn;, sin he and his kirk is o persone, and also if &thorn;e kirk err, men may be in dout of her dedis, wan scho erri&thorn;, and wan not; and were it vnsikir to trow to her canoni&yogh;ing, approuing, or afferming, or autori&yogh;ing bifor &thorn;at &thorn;ei proue hem bi sikirar ground; &thorn;erfor as God ordeynid men to strif a&yogh;en &thorn;eis princis, &thorn;at all be drifun in to &thorn;e seruice of Crist, and groundid and formid bi him. And o&thorn;er goostly &thorn;ingis of schrewdnes in heuenly &thorn;ingis, &thorn;at are &thorn;ei &thorn;at feynun in ypocrisy and color &thorn;ingis &thorn;at &thorn;ei tak and understond misser, as bo&thorn; holy mennis lif, and o&thorn;er vertuous werkis, &thorn;at men mis vndirstonden now, and turnen al in to pride and coueteys, and vndir lustis. And &thorn;us turnen sacramentis &thorn;at are gostly &thorn;ingis, for gostly &thorn;ing don, vse &thorn;ei more in fleschlynes &thorn;an in to gostlynes, as in to couey|teis of &thorn;e flesch and &thorn;e world. A&yogh;en &thorn;eis &thorn;ingis bihoue men to wrestil in &thorn;o maner, as Crist himsilf ded and his apostlis. And &thorn;erfor it behoui&thorn; to tak &thorn;e armor of Crist, and gird our lindis in his trow&thorn;, &thorn;at our affeccoun and al our lif and wark be led bi him, for he is &thorn;e first trow&thorn;. And &thorn;an we be clo&thorn;id &thorn;e habarioun of ri&yogh;twisnes, to held to ilk man, &thorn;at we howe bi his lawe to frend and fo, to suffreyn and suget, and &thorn;at we deme non man, but as God biddi&thorn;; for who is he &thorn;at sei&thorn; &thorn;is &thorn;ing schal be don, and &thorn;e Lord comaund not, but Balaam seid he mi&yogh;t not spek, but &thorn;at &thorn;e Lord<NOTE PLACE="marg">Num. xxiii<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> put in his mou&thorn;, and &thorn;erfor wan he wold haue cursid hem in anger, he blessid hem; and mak &yogh;or feet to be shod in arayng of &thorn;e gospel of pees, &thorn;at al our wark and our wille be to mak pees; and<NOTE PLACE="marg">Eph. vi<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> 
<PB REF="00000164.tif" N="100"> take we &thorn;e helme of &yogh;ele, &thorn;at is good hope, and &thorn;e swerd of &thorn;e Spirit, &thorn;at is Goddis worde, bo&thorn; to strik wi&thorn;, and to vndirnem misdoars, and to defend hem of. But if &thorn;ei sei may we not vndir|stond, appily &thorn;ei wot not, for God may &yogh;eue vndirstonding to wam he will. And if &thorn;ei suppose hem to han, and of God, so may God delen it til an o&thorn;er, and &thorn;erfor may &thorn;e first wit if &thorn;ei sey &thorn;ei haue not, &thorn;an are &thorn;e foolis to deme men. And &thorn;an dar I wel sey, &thorn;ei vndirstond not &thorn;eis men, &thorn;at &thorn;ei wet we&thorn;er &thorn;ei sey wel or iuel. If &thorn;ei sei we can not, or we vndirstond amis, pray we hem, for Ihu sak, to enform us, bi &thorn;e trow&thorn; of holy writt, and trow&thorn; brout out bi resoun, &thorn;at may not fayle, and bi sensible trow&thorn;, and be we euer more redy to be mendid bi &thorn;e trou&thorn; of Crist, for we are not so sikir &thorn;at we be wi&thorn; out faut, error, and vnkunning. &THORN;erfor &thorn;at we may cum out, and cum to &thorn;e knowing of trow&thorn;, and lif &thorn;er after, euer pray we to Ihu Crist.</P>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="28" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XXVIII. Of vowe.</HEAD>
<P>An o&thorn;er is put and is askid &thorn;us; &thorn;at &thorn;e vowe of religioun is a&yogh;en Cristis gospel. To &thorn;is I haue seid &thorn;us, &thorn;at &thorn;e name of religioun is takun in mani maneris; os sum tyme for &thorn;e trow&thorn; &thorn;at rewli&thorn; a man to serue duly his makar. And sum tym for &thorn;e act and &thorn;e state procedyng of &thorn;is religioun. And &thorn;e &thorn;rid, materialy, for &thorn;e personis &thorn;us enclinid. And &thorn;us &thorn;e keping of Cristis lawe is callid religioun, bi holy writ, and holy doctors. In &thorn;e secound maner are religious callid &thorn;oo &thorn;at departun from o&thorn;er puple bi sectis foundun, and bi tradicouns, and o&thorn;er sensible ritis. And in &thorn;is maner wer &thorn;er &thorn;re sectis among &thorn;e Jury, Phariseis, and Esseis, and Saduceis. Eft it be howui&thorn; to not, &thorn;at to a wowe is a resonable creature to obey him to his souereyn, to kep sum hard &thorn;ing &thorn;at is sensible, or vnsible, a bout &thorn;ing ay lasting or temporel, wise or vnwyse; wise, wan it is acording to God, efter his lawe to &thorn;e worschip of God, and profi&yogh;t of &thorn;e vowar; vnwise, wan it is only about temporal &thorn;ingis, or vnhonest, or vnprofitable to soule hele; werfor it be howui&thorn; &thorn;e vowar be in fredam, hauing feruor to do plesing Goddis 
<PB REF="00000165.tif" N="101"> &thorn;ingis, &thorn;at are to soule hele; and &thorn;at he entend to fulfil, ellis he synni&thorn; in vowing, and so his vow is synne; as if it be more for lust of flesch, pride of world, or to geit temporel riches, or in to harm of ani man, or swilk o&thorn;er, &thorn;an for honor and worschip of God. &THORN;erfor it is seid &thorn;us, four &thorn;ingis are requirid to ilk vowe &thorn;at oblischi&thorn;: first, principaly, &thorn;at it be maad to God, sin it is &thorn;e worschipful dede only to be &yogh;euen to God. &THORN;e secound, &thorn;at is bi &thorn;ingis only good and profitable to hele of soule, and not iuel &thorn;ing, nor of fil&thorn;, nor vnleful, ne noyes to ani man, ne letting of ani maundment of God, or counseil of Crist, efter &thorn;e decre of Isidor,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Isidor.</NOTE> seing &thorn;us: In iuel hi&yogh;tis, kut &thorn;e filling a wey of &thorn;ing &thorn;at is hi&yogh;t. In fowl vowe, chaunge &thorn;i decret, and do not &thorn;is &thorn;at &thorn;u hast vowid unwarly. &THORN;e &thorn;rid, &thorn;at it be made wi&thorn; deliberacoun, &thorn;at &thorn;e purpos or entent be not misrewlid, for if it be foly, or vniust, or vndiscret, or letting &thorn;ing more profitable, it is not to be kepid, but vtterly to be brokin, after &thorn;is &thorn;at Ecclesiastes sei&thorn;, An vnprofitable and a<NOTE PLACE="marg">Eccles. u<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> foul hi&yogh;t displeci&thorn; God. And as he is seid vnfei&thorn;ful &thorn;at do&thorn; not &thorn;is &thorn;at he hi&yogh;t, so is he &thorn;at do&thorn; not of &thorn;e fei&thorn;, &thorn;at is of &thorn;e ground of God, or not of good in witt or ordre, for ilk &thorn;ing &thorn;at is not of<NOTE PLACE="marg">Rom. xiu<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> &thorn;e fei&thorn; is synne. And in a o&thorn;er place it is seid, &thorn;o vowis of foolis are to be broken. And wilk &thorn;ei are Hugo declari&thorn;, in his book of<NOTE PLACE="marg">Hugo.</NOTE> sacramentis, seying &thorn;us, &THORN;o fowl wowis vndirstond al &thorn;at are iuel of hem silf, or ellis &thorn;of &thorn;ei be good, &thorn;ei are not ordinat. Or wan more iuel is of hem &thorn;an good is in hem. &THORN;e fourt requirid to a vow is, &thorn;at it be wilful. &THORN;an if &thorn;e vowe of religioun is circum|staunsid, &thorn;an it is plesing to God, and wi&thorn; &thorn;e gospel; ellis if it be contrarili be gunne, led, or contenid, who douti&thorn; &thorn;at ne it is synne? &THORN;erfor iuge religiouse men in &thorn;er consciens, if &thorn;ei ground hem &thorn;us in her vowis, and ilk fei&thorn;ful man loking in holy writt, and &thorn;e lif of Crist and his apostlis, and her dedis, after &thorn;ingis &thorn;at are seid semyn to be contrary. Certeynly if &thorn;e vow of religious men, or of ani man, is not wi&thorn; &thorn;e gospel, to &thorn;e perfeccoun of &thorn;e fredam &thorn;er of, 
<PB REF="00000166.tif" N="102"> but in ani maner letting or trobling or tariing &thorn;ing &thorn;at &thorn;e gospel biddi&thorn;, or counseili&thorn;, &thorn;an certeynly al so it is a&yogh;en &thorn;e gospel; after &thorn;e sentens of Crist, &thorn;at sei&thorn;, He &thorn;at is not wi&thorn; me, he is a&yogh;en me,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Luc. xi<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> and he &thorn;at gedre&thorn; not wi&thorn; me, he scateri&thorn;. As if ani person obeyed him wi&thorn; wickid stering, or onordinatly, to do ani &thorn;ing &thorn;at is forbedun bi &thorn;e law of God, or to lef &thorn;ing &thorn;at God biddi&thorn; do, as sum wil mak her awowe &thorn;at &thorn;ei wil not do &thorn;e dedis of mercy, oi&thorn;er &thorn;at &thorn;ey wil not ehyt flesch, tul &thorn;ei be vengid of sum man, but if he ouer tak, &thorn;ei wille o&thorn;er mak a vow to fast, or to go pilgrimage, for to do &thorn;er lechery, or veniaunce of sum man. Also &thorn;oo &thorn;at byndun hem to kepe ani staat or degre, or rewle more for cause of hi&yogh;nes of &thorn;e world, or worldly riches, or lust of flesch, or to do ani &thorn;ing, oi&thorn;er bi her causis, or ellis wan he is lettid bi &thorn;e vow to do &thorn;e ded &thorn;at God wold him to do, as &thorn;us his vowe is a&yogh;en &thorn;e gospel. And ilk &thorn;at vowi&thorn; ani &thorn;ing to do in any maner for ani cause, wi&thorn; out mening of &thorn;e Holy Gost to do so, he synni&thorn; in &thorn;at vowing; &thorn;erfor if religious vowen in &thorn;is maner, doutles &thorn;er vow is synne, and a&yogh;en &thorn;e gospel; as if possessioneris to kep &thorn;e religioun of monk, or chanouns, more to be partiners of temporal goodis, and to lif in delitis, and hi&yogh;nes of &thorn;e world, &thorn;an to lif in wilful pouert, dewe obediens, and chastite. Who douti&thorn; &thorn;at ne as &thorn;us &thorn;ey synne a&yogh;en &thorn;e gospel? And if &thorn;ei do not &thorn;at &thorn;ei hi&yogh;t, it is &thorn;e more a&yogh;en &thorn;e gospel, and &thorn;e biddingis of God, seying, Wan &thorn;u hast vowid a vow<NOTE PLACE="marg">Eccles. u<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> to &thorn;e Lord, &thorn;u schalt not mak it void, but fil &thorn;is &thorn;at &thorn;u hast hi&yogh;t, for an vnfei&thorn;ful man and a foole hi&yogh;t displeci&thorn; God; as if freris obeyid hem &thorn;at &thorn;ei beg, for al &thorn;er tyme is in begging, &thorn;at is a&yogh;en &thorn;e gospel, as it is seid in o&thorn;er placis, or wan &thorn;ey obey hem to absteyn from meytis, a&yogh;en Cristis fredam, &thorn;at biddi&thorn; his disciplis<NOTE PLACE="marg">Luc. x<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> eyte swilk as men settun to hem. If &thorn;ey bynd hem in &thorn;e con|trary, &thorn;at &thorn;ey be not in fredam to do &thorn;us, but if Crist had for bedun it hem, ellis it is a&yogh;en &thorn;e gospel, for swilk are reprouid of &thorn;e apostil seying &thorn;us, &THORN;e spirit sei&thorn; opunly, &thorn;at in &thorn;e last tyme<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Thi. iu<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> 
<PB REF="00000167.tif" N="103"> sum schal depart fro &thorn;e fei&thorn;, tenting to spiritis of error, and to kening of fendis, speking lesing in ypocrisy, and hauing &thorn;er con|sciens iren brondit; forbeding men to be weddid, and abstening fro metis, &thorn;at God ha&thorn; maad to be tan of fei&thorn;fulmen, and &thorn;oo &thorn;at knowun &thorn;e so&thorn;, wi&thorn; doing of gracis, for it is halowid wi&thorn; &thorn;e word of God and by prayoris; for ilk creater of God is good, and no &thorn;ing to be castun a wey, &thorn;at is hawid bi &thorn;e doing of grace. And neuer&thorn;eles &thorn;e meyt comendi&thorn; vs not to God, nor fili&thorn; vs not, but frely it may be tan, and frely left. Also if &thorn;ei vow hem to hold an abit, or o&thorn;er ritis, and God behiti&thorn; no meed for &thorn;e keping, but ra&thorn;er reproue, as he dede sum tyme &thorn;e Phariseis, doutles &thorn;at is a&yogh;en &thorn;e gospel. It semi&thorn; &thorn;us, wan it is not groundid &thorn;ere, and is wi&thorn; out med aylasting; for &thorn;is is pleinly a&yogh;en &thorn;e gospel bidding, &THORN;u schalt not tak &thorn;e name of &thorn;i Lord God in veyn, and &thorn;is bidding he breki&thorn; &thorn;at do&thorn; ani &thorn;ing wi&thorn; out God ordeyning it, or &thorn;at lefi&thorn; his bidding, or do&thorn; ani &thorn;ing for wilk he is not to be medid in blisses for euer. And if religiouse men bindun &thorn;us to be obedient, and puttun &thorn;er will under mannis will, more &thorn;an under &thorn;e will of God, so &thorn;at it behowui&thorn; to do &thorn;e will of man, be it hout wor&thorn; or nout, and wat &thorn;at God biddi&thorn; hem do &thorn;ey may not do it, if &thorn;er ouer|man bid hem cerse, or to do &thorn;e contrari, certis &thorn;is is a&yogh;en &thorn;e gospel; and &thorn;at we axe in our <I>pr. nr.</I> Our fader &thorn;at art in heuen,<NOTE PLACE="marg">Luc. uj<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> &thorn;i wyl be it don, in &yogh;er&thorn; as it is in heuen. And &thorn;us wan religiouse men are lettun bi &thorn;er vow fro &thorn;er preching of Goddis word, and fro filling of &thorn;e dedis of mercy, and fro ri&yogh;twisnes manifold, as &thorn;ei knowlech, and are nedid bi al &thorn;er tyme to comyn wi&thorn; &thorn;er bre&thorn;er, &thorn;ow &thorn;ei be symonientis and synnars, &thorn;at God forbedi&thorn; tak meyt wi&thorn;, or hald felischip wi&thorn;; it is certeyn &thorn;at in swilk casis her vow is a&yogh;en &thorn;e gospel. And wan &thorn;e vow of religious is to wilful bodily pouert, and obediens, and chastite, to be kepid, but now our religious lifi&thorn; and flowi&thorn; among all men most in delitis, and ha|bundi&thorn; in worldly riches, and taki&thorn; to hem worldly honoris: 
<PB REF="00000168.tif" N="104"> certeynly oi&thorn;er &thorn;ey han feynidly and falsly a no&thorn;er vow a&yogh;en &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">Nota.</NOTE> gospel, or ellis &thorn;ey brek &thorn;er vow. And we&thorn;er it be so or so, &thorn;e toon or &thorn;e to&thorn;er, &thorn;e vow is a&yogh;en &thorn;e gospel, and dampnable; werfor Prosper, in his book of contemplatif lif, sei&thorn; &thorn;us, It is to sarow he<NOTE PLACE="marg">Prosper.</NOTE> sei&thorn;, &thorn;at &thorn;er sum in &thorn;eis daies &thorn;at wel be ooneris, but in express maneris &thorn;ei kast no &thorn;ing a wey, &thorn;ei chaunge not &thorn;e mynde but &thorn;e clo&thorn;, &thorn;ei are &thorn;at forsakun &thorn;e world only in word, but not in werk, &thorn;ei lifen worldly, and hidun &thorn;er bicis wi&thorn; a veyn hi&yogh;t of better lif, and mantel it wi&thorn; a name of ymaginid religioun, &thorn;ey tak for vertu, &thorn;e opiniun of vertu, &thorn;ey wil be seen a mong men dredy and just, &thorn;ei diuerse fro &thorn;e puple, not in mynd, but in clo&thorn;, not in lifing, but in habit only, in liknes, but not in effect, &thorn;ei study to be seen gret, but not to be, &thorn;ei preeche gret &thorn;ingis but &thorn;ei do hem not, &thorn;ei accuse vices, but &thorn;ey do not a wey, &thorn;ei ben in wordis, but &thorn;ei do not in dedis. In opun &thorn;ei feyn hem to be displecid of &thorn;ingis &thorn;at &thorn;ei don in hid; &thorn;ei knowlech to know and luf God, but in dedis &thorn;ey deney. In habite and lifing &thorn;ei han &thorn;e form of pite, but &thorn;ei deney &thorn;e vertu &thorn;er of. And for &thorn;is &thorn;ei disseyue &thorn;e moo, for &thorn;ei transfiger hem in to an aungel of li&yogh;t, and wi&thorn; face and tonsur pretendun a schadowe peyntid of religioun. Werfor it is don &thorn;at &thorn;ei are maad desseyuable ypocritis, and lurkyng woluis of ref under a schepis flees; of wam it is seid bi &thorn;e prophet, &THORN;e dred of<NOTE PLACE="marg">Ps. xxxu<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> God is not bi forn &thorn;er een. Alien sonis han li&yogh;ed to me, alien sonis han &yogh;eldid and crokid fro &thorn;i pathis, arett &thorn;u &thorn;er lifing damp|nacoun, &thorn;at lufun &thorn;e maner of &thorn;e world for &thorn;e cloyster, and dispice for Crist a fewe facultes, and couetun moo a&yogh;en Crist, and inword coueyteis resti&thorn; or lurki&thorn; under dispicyng of temporal &thorn;ingis. Of &thorn;eis sei&thorn; Bernard to Eugeny &thorn;e pope, &THORN;ei are &thorn;at suffur not to be<NOTE PLACE="marg">Bernard.</NOTE> vnder lowtid, &thorn;ei kan not be abouen, &thorn;ei are vnfei&thorn;ful to &thorn;er soue|reyns, vneuyn to &thorn;er lowar, vnschamful to axe, bolde to denay, vnrestful tul &thorn;ei tak, vnkynd wan &thorn;ei han tane, &thorn;ei ken &thorn;er tongis for to spek gret &thorn;ingis, wan &thorn;ei do but litil &thorn;ingis; &thorn;ei are largist 
<PB REF="00000169.tif" N="105"> bihi&yogh;tars, and scarsist geuars; glosandist flaterars, and bitandist bacbitars; simplist glosars, and warst willid traytoris. And Lin|<NOTE PLACE="marg">Lincoln.</NOTE> coln sei&thorn; &thorn;us, A cloystrer of priuat ordre, and specialy a frere wandring voyd in the world, is a ded careyn, gon out of &thorn;e graue, woundun in dedly clo&thorn;is, schaken of &thorn;e fend a mong men: &thorn;ei are tokunid bi &thorn;e wif of Loth, &thorn;at, after &thorn;e going out of Sodom, loking<NOTE PLACE="marg">Gen. xix<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> a&yogh;en, was turnid in to an image of salt. An image ha&thorn; &thorn;e similitud of a man, but not &thorn;e trow&thorn;. So swilk similitudis of religious efter habit, and ypocrit signis, and neuer&thorn;eles not hauing &thorn;e vertu of Cristis religioun; werfor &thorn;e messangeris of Saul, seking Dauid in<NOTE PLACE="marg">1 Reg. xix<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> &thorn;e bed, fond a simulacre and geyt skinnis. And Peter and Jon<NOTE PLACE="marg">Joh. xx<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> seking &thorn;e graue, fond but a sudary. And of wilk sei&thorn; &thorn;e Lord, No<NOTE PLACE="marg">Luc. ix<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> man leying hand to &thorn;e plowe, and loking a&yogh;en, is able to &thorn;e kyn|dam of God. And &thorn;e epistil of Jude, Erring sternis, to &thorn;e wam<NOTE PLACE="marg">Jude.</NOTE> wirlwynd of mirknes is kepid vn to wi&thorn; outen ende; &thorn;us sei&thorn; he. We&thorn;er &thorn;e vow of religioun is not veyn, Seynt Jam sei&thorn;, If ani wen hem to be religious, not refreyning his tong, but disseyuing his hert, his religioun is veyn. Religioun clene at God, and at &thorn;e Fader, is &thorn;is, to visite &thorn;e fadirles and madirles, and wydowis, in &thorn;er tribula|coun, and kep hem silf vnfilid of &thorn;is world.</P>
